title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Blend until smooth.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: pizza beans
directions: Brown bacon.
Drain and crumble.
Add chopped onions, chopped green peppers and chopped celery.
Cut in half the pepperoni and add with chopped mushrooms.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add beans, brown sugar, barbecue sauce and flour.
Simmer in crock-pot or slow cooker.

title: fruit cup
directions: Stir all together and mix while freezing.
Will keep frozen a long time.
Thaw to slushy stage.
Serves 25.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind all vegetables and add other ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes and seal while hot.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix together.
Keep in tightly covered glass jar.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg. Blend in dry ingredients.
Fold in pulp, raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apricot bars
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt; stir in rolled oats and sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Pat 2/3 of crumb mixture in 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Spread with preserves.
Cover with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake in oven at 375°
about 35 minutes or until browned.
Cool.
Cut in bars or squares.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen (3 x 1-inch) bars, or about 6 dozen (1-inch) squares.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni 25 minutes in boiling water to which a teaspoon of salt has been added.
Drain; rinse with cold water and drain again.
Butter baking dish and put in layer of macaroni.
Add milk, salt, pepper, butter, dry mustard, chopped peppers and 3/4 cup grated cheese.
Add remaining macaroni and mix well.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top; garnish with paprika and bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes or until done.
Serves 6.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Combine melted butter and dry cake mix.
(Let butter cool a couple of minutes before adding to dry mix.
Mixture should be crumbly.
If butter is too hot, the result will be a sticky mass instead of a crumbly mixture.)

title: holly candy
directions: In double boiler, melt margarine and marshmallows.
Add green food coloring and vanilla; stir until glossy.
Add the cornflakes; stir.
Dampen fingers.
Shape mixture into trees, leaves, etc. Put red hots in center.

title: anniversary punch
directions: Blend together, stirring well, until sherbet is basically melted.
Float thin slices of oranges or sprigs of mint.
Set punch bowl in crushed ice.
Serves 12.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown beef, onion, salt and pepper.
Blend in flour.
Add Worcestershire sauce, ketchup and water.
Simmer; stir frequently for 20 minutes or when thick.
Serve over hamburger buns.

title: microwave chili
directions: Crumble ground beef in 2-quart casserole.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook uncovered on High for 4 minutes or until browned. Drain meat and break up with a fork.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 8 minutes or until heated hot.
Stir once during cooking.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: quick oyster stew
directions: Cook butter and oysters together only until good and hot and butter is melted. Add milk, salt and pepper.
Heat only until good and hot. Do not boil.

title: steak bites appetizer
directions: Prepare steak with meat tenderizer as label directs.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, mix wine and garlic.
Add steak; cover. Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours.
Turn once.
Preheat broiler.
Place steak on rack in broiling pan.
Reserve marinade.
About 5 inches from source of heat, broil steak 10 minutes.
Turn; broil 8 minutes more.

title: lynda's red velvet cake with frosting
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into a greased and floured 9x13-inch pan.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese and peanut butter.
Blend well.
Add sugar and milk; mix well.
Fold in 2 cups whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Chill and top with remaining whipped topping.

title: lemon crackers
directions: Beat sugar and lard together. Add beaten eggs.
Pulverize ammonia; dissolve in milk.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add oil of lemon and lemon extract.
Add flour until dough is stiff enough to roll out.
Cut cookies and bake on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Some ovens vary in temperature.

title: sausage balls
directions: Blend all ingredients, form into ball (quarter size).
Put on cookie sheet and set in freezer overnight.
Put in bags and use as desired.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in refrigerator for 12 to 18 hours.
When ready to bake, sprinkle with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8.

title: butter biscuit(cookies)
directions: You will also need a pan 24 cm (9 1/2-inch).

title: leftover roast special
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Mix noodles, roast and soup, add pepper as desired.
Pour into casserole and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken fruit and party salad
directions: Toss together, then mix in mayonnaise.
Chill thoroughly.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well.
Use 1 tablespoon mix to one cup of hot water.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Put 1/2 cup chopped pecans in bottom of pan.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes in pan before pouring on topping.

title: shrimp linguini
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain.
While pasta is cooking, saute garlic, green onions and broccoli in the chicken broth.
Add salt, pepper and parsley.
Add shrimp and cook until pink.
Serve shrimp over pasta with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4, approximately 375 calories per serving.

title: farm cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift the flour, salt, soda and baking powder together. Add to creamed mixture.
Add to the mixture the cornflakes, oatmeal, coconut, nuts and vanilla. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes until done.

title: slow cooker stuffing
directions: Crumble sausage in pan. Add next 3 ingredients. Cook until done; drain. Pour over bread cubes in large bowl. Add seasoning and toss together. Pour in enough broth to moisten. Add beaten eggs and mix well. Put stuffing into slow cooker and cover. Set to high for 45 minutes. Reduce to low and cook 6 to 8 hours.

title: cranberry festival ham
directions: Cook ham with wine and water.
Bring to a boil, then reduce to simmer.
Cover and simmer 1 hour (or more), turning ham several times.
Remove ham; trim fat, if necessary.
Score ham; place in roasting pan.

title: jalapeno corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square baking pan. Combine first 7 ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Turn half of the batter into pan. Cover evenly with half of the cheese, then peppers, then remaining cheese.
Top with remaining batter. Bake 1 hour.
Let cool 15 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: easy low-fat mexican chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking pan.
Cover with beans, then salsa.
Bake, covered with foil, at 350° for one hour.
Uncover and bake another 10 minutes.
Can add cheese and sour cream, if you like.

title: enchiladas suizas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat half of cream cheese and onions in small mixing bowl at medium speed with mixer until well blended. Reserve for topping.
Beat remaining cream cheese, 1 1/4 cups Cheddar cheese, 1 1/4 cups Monterey Jack cheese, chilies and cumin in large mixing bowl at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.

title: muffins taste like do-nuts
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased or paper lined muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve plain or roll in powdered sugar first.
Yields 1 dozen muffins.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix flour with sugar. Beat egg yolks.
Add milk, butter, vanilla and sugar mixture. Cook until thick.
Put a layer of sliced bananas, then a layer of filling. Top with beaten egg whites to which 4 or 5 tablespoons of sugar has been added. Brown in a 425° oven.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute the first 4 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Heat and serve over rice.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine breadcrumbs and beaten eggs; stir cream into eggs. Cook onion in butter in large skillet and add to egg mix.
Add in beef, veal, pork, allspice, salt and pepper; mix.
Next, shape into 1-inch balls.
Melt butter in skillet and brown meatballs slightly. Add boiling water and cover skillet.
Bring to boil and lower heat. Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove meatballs.
Blend flour with fat from pan.
Thicken sauce 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over meatballs.

title: pork chop-vegetable casserole
directions: In heavy skillet, melt shortening.
Add chops and brown well on both sides
(about 15 minutes).
In greased casserole, alternate
layers
of
potatoes,
carrots
and onion.
Arrange chops
over
vegetables.
Stir flour in skillet.
Add salt and pepper.
Slowly
add
milk.
Cook,
stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Pour over vegetables and meat.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 45 minutes, covered.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: reese cup pies
directions: Coarsely
chop Reese cups.
Mix cream cheese and peanut butter, then add 10x sugar.
Fold in Reese cups and Cool Whip. Pour into pie shells.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.	Freezes well.

title: spinach fruit salad
directions: Toss and add Seven Seas Creamy Italian dressing.

title: farmer's omelet
directions: Fry bacon; let cool.
Use bacon grease to fry potatoes.
Add crumbs.
Add eggs.
Keep stirring.
Put into casserole dish. Crumble bacon over top.
Crumble cheese over top.
Put in oven to melt cheese.
Can refrigerate overnight.
Bake in slow oven.

title: chocolate coconut crust
directions: In a medium-size heavy saucepan, melt butter and chocolate over low heat, stirring occasionally, 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in coconut and walnuts, mixing well.
Press mixture into bottom and up sides of a lightly buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: uncooked boiled custard
directions: Mix pudding mix, sugar and milk.
Pour in covered container. Refrigerate overnight.
This mixture will be thick.
Beat with mixer until creamy.
Serve.

title: raspberry chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
In top of double boiler, beat egg yolks. Add 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Cook over boiling water, stirring until thickened, about 10 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in softened gelatin. Add crushed raspberries and a few drops red coloring.
Mix well.
Chill until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon. Beat egg
whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add remaining sugar, beating until stiff. Fold in raspberry mixture. Spoon into baked pie shell. Chill until set.

title: spinach brownies
directions: Drain spinach in a colander and squeeze out moisture; combine cheese, spinach and onion in a large bowl, mixing well.
Stir salt, baking powder and nutmeg into flour.
Then mix with spinach. Mix together beaten eggs, melted butter and milk.
Stir into other ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Rinse well and drain.
Chop and dice vegetables, meat and cheeses.
Mix noodles, meat, cheese and vegetables.
Add 8 ounces (1/2 bottle) salad dressing.
Mix well.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving. Serve with additional salad dressing (per individual taste).

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar.
Add oil, nuts, eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add these to batter and mix until well blended. Grease and flour 8 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tea puffs
directions: Blend butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour and pecans.
Mix all together.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch rolls.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: berkeley's potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla; blend in flour.
Add potato chips.
Drop dough by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fork dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Remove; cool slightly and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: bleu cheese stuffed lettuce salad
directions: Hold lettuce, core end down, and tap core on countertop; twist and remove core.
Rinse lettuce and drain.
Set aside.
Combine cream cheese, Bleu cheese, milk, dry mustard, red pepper, salt and pepper.
Spoon into cavity of lettuce.
Wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate 8 hours.
Cut into 6 wedges and serve with Italian dressing.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.

title: hilda's special barbecue(my barbecue always sold out in my cafeteria.)
directions: Pour the milk into a double boiler.
In a separate dish, melt oleo (this can be done in a microwave), then add cornstarch and flour, and mix well.
Stir this mixture into hot milk and add cheese.
Stir often, and cook until sauce is thickened.
(More or less cheese may be added, depending on desired thickness.)

title: beef barbecue
directions: In large Dutch oven, sear meat on all sides over high heat. Reduce heat.
Add water to cover meat.
Add onion and garlic. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer, covered, for 2 hours. Remove meat and reserve pan juices.

title: grandma's bread pudding
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into buttered baking dish. Bake with a pan of water beneath dish at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Good with ice cream on top, or Orange Sauce.

title: pick-your-own-flavor-cookies(kids recipe)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Measure 3/4 cup frosting.
(You'll use the remainder later to frost cookies.)
Mix baking mix, egg and 3/4 cup frosting in bowl.
(The dough will be stiff.)
Drop dough by teaspoon, about 2-inches apart on the cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until almost no impression remains with touched lightly.
Cool on wire rack, then ice with remaining frosting.

title: sour cream ugly biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients. Put in ungreased muffin pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: impossible cheese pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Put all ingredients into a blender; blend until no streaks remain.
Pour batter into the prepared pie plate and bake 30 to 35 minutes. Turn off oven heat and allow pie to remain in oven for 1 hour before removing; chill.
Serve plain or with your favorite fruit topping.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: beef stew
directions: Place the stew in a large pot.
Add potatoes (cut potatoes in halves or thirds).
Heat through.
Prepare Minute rice per package instructions for 2, 4 or 6 servings.
Serve stew on bed of rice.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage.
Drain.
Heat cheese slowly. (Use microwave, slow cooker or double boiler.)
Add ground beef and sausage.
When cheese gets creamy, add Ro-Tel tomatoes and chilies. Heat slowly.
Stir well.
Try with deli nacho chips.

title: "lazy lady's" spice cake
directions: Make batter for Chocolate Malt cake as directed, except add cinnamon, cloves and ginger to mix.
Add lemon extract and orange extract.
Pour into prepared layer pans.
Bake as directed.
Frost with Chocolate Butter Icing.

title: butter pecan sauce
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt butter. Add pecans and heat till lightly toasted and butter lightly browned. Stir in sugar, cream and syrup. Cook gently till sugar is completely dissolved. Do not over cook. Makes 2 cups.

title: nonfat cornbread
directions: Mix the corn meal, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together. Add the beaten egg whites and buttermilk. Pour into a prepared 8-inch square pan. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes until the top is golden and toothpick comes out clean. Serve warm.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on box.
Add soup, green pepper, Worcestershire sauce, lemon, mustard and cheese.
Add canned or sauteed mushrooms.
Mix together.
Add shrimp and cook for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: frosty freeze
directions: Mix well and pour into ice cream freezer.
Process until frozen.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Sprinkle sugar on blueberries; set aside.
Combine condensed milk and lemon juice, stirring until smooth.
Combine whipped topping, pecans, and blueberries, fold into milk mixture, stirring until smooth.
Spoon into graham cracker crust.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Yields 1 9-inch pie.

title: chicken biscuit pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Heat margarine in 2-quart saucepan over low heat until melted.
Mix in 1/3 cup baking mix, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups water, milk and chicken bouillon.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and frozen vegetables.
Heat through.
Keep over warm heat while making crust.

title: punch
directions: Place sherbet in punch bowl; pour Hi-C carefully over the sherbet, then add 1 liter of ginger ale or as much as is needed to fill the punch bowl.
You may add Hi-C and ginger ale to punch bowl as long as sherbet lasts.

title: hot cranberry wine cup
directions: Combine cranberry juice, water, sugar, cinnamon stick, whole cloves and lemon peel in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add Port wine and lemon juice; heat gently.
Do not boil.
Sprinkle nutmeg over top of each serving.
Makes 28 (3 ounce) servings.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Slice and boil carrots.
Combine the rest and pour over carrots.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sara lang's chocolate brownie pie
directions: Beat thoroughly with a rotary beater.
Stir in 1 cup of broken nuts, if desired.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken in rice
directions: Mix rice, sherry, cream of celery soup and mushroom soup.
On bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, lay 6 chicken breasts on top
with mixture and sprinkle over it 1 package dry onion soup mix.
Cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: priscilla's apple crisp
directions: Put the butter in the microwave and cook until softened. Crumble the butter and brown sugar together in a bowl.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Place crushed Doritos in bottom of casserole dish.
Place chicken over Doritos.
Mix soups and tomatoes together and pour over chicken.
Spread cheese over top and sprinkle onions over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift cocoa with cake flour mixture (red "B" packet).
Prepare.
Bake and cool cake as directed on package. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: dairy dip
directions: Over low heat, melt butter.
Add flour and stir for 1 minute. Quickly add all spices.
Mix well.
Add milk and cheese.
Simmer slowly for about 20 minutes or until as thick as you like.

title: lemon lust pie
directions: Mix together and pat out into a large baking dish.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender-crisp.
Combine milk and soup and fold in vegetables in a casserole.
Prepare stuffing as directed and place on top of vegetables.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° (until bubbling well).

title: potato gnocchi(biba restaurant)
directions: Bake potatoes until tender.
Remove insides and discard skins. Mash hot potatoes in a ricer into a large bowl.
Let cool slightly. Add egg yolk, salt and flour.
Mix well.
Put mixture on a working surface or wooden board and knead into a ball.
Mixture should be soft, pliable and slightly sticky.
If too sticky, add more flour. Lightly flour the working surface and break dough into small egg size pieces and roll into ropes, about 1-inch thick and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Hold a fork with tines down and press the dumpling quickly up along the tines.
Fill large saucepan with salted water; bring water to a boil.
Add 1 tablespoon oil.
Carefully put gnocchi into pan.
Remove with slotted spoon when they come to surface.
Place in warm dish and serve with your favorite sauce.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together first six ingredients. Blend in flour.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on cookie sheet.
Dip a fork in flour and press across top of each cookie. Repeat in opposite direction.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 minutes or until cookies are brown.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Slice the venison into thin strips. Coat the strips in flour mixed with salt and pepper.
In a large skillet, brown the strips in as much butter as needed. Remove and set aside.
In the same skillet, saute the onions, sliced mushrooms and minced garlic in the butter.
Add the flour to the mixture, then gradually pour in the beef broth, stirring until smooth.
Bring this mixture to a boil, then simmer for 5 minutes.
Over low heat, add the wine, sour cream and dill.
Put the venison strips in and
heat thoroughly.
Prepare egg noodles as directed on package.
Serve over noodles.

title: pineapple dressing
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom and sides of a 2 1/2-quart baking dish with a portion of the butter.
Mix in blender at high speed all ingredients except pineapple and bread. Fold in pineapple and bread by hand.
Pour into baking dish. Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour (or until inserted knife comes out clean).
May be served hot or cooled as a side dish or as a dessert similar to bread pudding.
Serves approximately 6.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Combine caramels and 1/2 cup milk in double boiler.
Stir over medium heat until melted.
Keep warm.
Combine cake mix, butter and 1/3 cup canned milk.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Spread half of batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes and spread caramel mix carefully over baked layer.
Sprinkle caramel layer with chips.
Stir nuts into remaining batter.
Drop by spoonfuls over caramel mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: london broil with red wine and shallots
directions: Brush flank steak with soy sauce, salt, pepper and thyme. Marinate 1 hour.
Brush again.
Grill over fire for 4 to 5 minutes each side for rare.
(May use oven instead of grill.) Combine shallots and wine and bring to a boil.
Add butter and salt it to taste.
Stir until butter is melted.
Add parsley and spoon over steak.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Layer first 4 ingredients beginning with chicken and ending with cheese.
Mix the remaining ingredients well and pour over the top layer.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine cocoa, milk, butter and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Take off stove when the first bubble appears.
Add oatmeal, vanilla and peanut butter.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in a closed container. To make tea, use 2 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion; drain.
Add seasoning and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Chop up lettuce and toss all ingredients together in large salad bowl.
Mix in dressing.
Put crushed taco chips on top.

title: scotch broth
directions: Remove most of the fat from meat and cut into small pieces. Put into a large pot with cold water.
Bring to a boil and stir in barley.
Simmer, partially covered, for 1 1/2 hours or until the meat and barley are tender, adding more water as it evaporates. Remove the meat from bones.
Cool the soup and skim off fat.
Melt butter in a skillet and add the carrots, celery, turnip and onion. Cook over low heat, stirring often, for 10 minutes.
Add to the soup.
Season with salt and pepper; cook for another 10 minutes or until veggies are tender.
Serve hot.

title: bellevue blueberry crunch
directions: Spread pineapple (and juice) in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Scatter blueberries over pineapple. Sprinkle with 3/4 cup sugar. Sprinkle cake mix all on top. Drizzle butter over cake mix, then sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup sugar. Top with pecans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. If desired, broil for 1 minute after baking to brown the top.

title: enchiritos
directions: In medium bowl, combine ground beef with flour, chili powder, salt, minced onion, paprika, onion power and garlic powder. Use your hands to thoroughly mix ingredients into ground beef. Add seasoned beef mixture to the water in a skillet over medium heat. Mix well with wooden spoon or spatula, and break up meat as it cooks. Heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until thoroughly browned. The finished product should be very smooth, with no large chunks of beef remaining. Heat refried beans in medium saucepan over medium heat, or in microwave for a couple of minutes on High. Wrap tortillas in a moist towel and microwave for 1 minute on High. Spoon about 3 Tbsp. refried beans down the center of each tortilla. Spoon 3 Tbsp. beef on top of beans, followed by a couple of tsp. minced onions. Fold the two sides of tortilla over meat and beans and flip the tortilla over in a plate. Spoon a couple of Tbsp. of red chile sauce over top of tortillas, the sprinkle a couple Tbsp. of shredded Cheddar cheese. Heat dish for 30 to 40 seconds in microwave, or until cheese on top begins to melt. Repeat with remaining ingredients.

title: country style apples
directions: Slice off tops of 8 apples and scoop out inside with melon-baller.
Reserve apple tops and discard apple insides.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Stir until thick.
Add vanilla when done. Pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Add cornbread mix, stirring until just moistened.
Pour batter into 10-inch cast iron skillet coated with vegetable cooking spray. Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: mustard or turnip greens
directions: Stem and pick the greens; wash several times.
Put greens in large pot; the water on the leaves from washing is sufficient, do not add any.
Add salt pork, onion and seasonings; cook slowly, until meat and greens are tender.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Lightly beat eggs; add milk and vanilla.
Mix flour and sugar and add to egg mixture.
Add butter and mix.
Pour in shell.
Bake at 350° until set, about 45 minutes.

title: really good chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light.
Beat in vanilla and eggs until smooth.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Beat into batter.
Add chips and nuts.
Drop onto baking sheets 1 heaping tablespoonful at a time.
Bake for 12 minutes, turning sheets end for end at half way point.
Bake at 325°.
After removing from oven, let sit until cookies are firm before putting on racks to cool.

title: sweet potato fluff
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour in shallow baking dish.

title: salad-in-a-pocket sandwiches
directions: Cut pita rounds in half.
Carefully open so you can see the pocket.
Spread dressing inside pockets.
Tear ham, turkey and cheese in small pieces and place inside pockets.
Stuff 1 lettuce leaf inside pocket and add meat mixture to each pocket.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute butter, onion, and green pepper.
In a separate bowl, combine eggs, cream corn, whole corn, and corn mix.
Add the sauteed ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole or 9 x 13 pan. Spread sour cream on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
12 to 15 servings.

title: garlic mashed potatoes
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, combine potatoes and enough water to cover potatoes by 1-inch.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and cook until fork-tender.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt in a heavy saucepan. Mix well.
Combine milk and egg yolks; beat with a wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes or until frothy.
Gradually stir into sugar mixture, mixing well.
Place over medium heat and stir constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate, butter and vanilla extract, stirring until chocolate and butter melts. Spoon into pastry shell; set aside.

title: singleton's cha cha
directions: Wash all vegetables; cut cabbage, tomatoes, peppers and onions into small pieces.
Cover with salt.
Use cloth and soak overnight, covered.
Drain the excess water next morning.
In pan, place pickling spice, sugar and 3 cups water to make syrup boil, then add all vegetables and cook until tender.
Pack in clean jars and seal.

title: wassail
directions: In large boiler, mix cranberry juice, apple cider and pineapple juice.
Heat and dissolve sugar in juices.
Using cheesecloth or something similar, bag up the cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Put bag in juice mixture and simmer at least 1 hour.
Refrigerate when done.
Heat before serving.

title: tina's rice
directions: Dice water chestnuts.
Then, combine rice, cheese, chestnuts and broccoli in a large oven-proof casserole dish.
Top with potato chips (optional).
Bake at 425° in a conventional oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding with milk and fold in Cool Whip.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Spread pudding mixture over crackers.
Top with another layer of graham crackers.
Mix together cocoa, melted oleo, hot coffee and powdered sugar. Spread icing over crackers and refrigerate, covered, for at least 12 hours before serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Overnight, if possible, or at least 4 hours before grilling, mix in largest bowl you have the salad dressing, cubed meat and cut up vegetables.
(Dad even threw in a drained can of whole potatoes.)
Stir occasionally to get all pieces covered with the dressing.

title: corn and green bean delight
directions: Mix green beans, green pepper,	sour
cream,
crackers, corn, celery and onions; pour into a greased 2-quart casserole dish. Combine
crackers,	butter	and
almonds;
spoon
over casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: citrus-marinated flank steak
directions: Score meat on both sides by making diagonal cuts at 1-inch intervals on surface.
Place in a plastic bag set in a shallow dish.
Add marinade and orange slices.
Seal bag; turn to coat. Marinate in the refrigerator for 6 to 24 hours, turning bag occasionally.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in water. Pick over beans. Combine beans, salt pork and onion in crock-pot.
Combine dry ingredients.
From tap draw enough water to mix dry ingredients.
Pour mixture over beans. Mix molasses with 1-quart hot water to thin molasses.
Add to beans. Add enough hot water to cover beans.
Cover crock.
Cook on high for 8 hours.

title: high calorie milkshake
directions: Blend on high in blender.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Serve with fresh slices of apples, bananas, etc.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper and sage.
Turn chicken pieces in the mixture until well coated.
Dip chicken pieces in buttermilk and roll in cornflakes.
Place in roasting pan.
Put in fridge for about 10 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Drizzle butter over chicken.
Bake 1 hour.
Turn occasionally.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter or oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla wafers.
Mix in coconut and pecans.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a well-greased and floured Bundt pan for 90 minutes or until done.

title: flaky herb chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine cracker crumbs, cheese, basil and oregano.
Dip 1 chicken cutlet into yogurt, then into crumb mixture, coating both sides evenly.
Repeat with remaining cutlets.
Arrange chicken on nonstick baking sheet; drizzle each cutlet with 1/2 teaspoon oil.
Bake chicken until lightly browned, 7 to 8 minutes.
Turn cutlets over; drizzle each with 1/2 teaspoon oil.
Bake until cooked through and lightly browned, 7 to 8 minutes longer.

title: creamy fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese by leaving it at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Put the cream cheese and marshmallow cream in the mixing bowl and stir until they are blended together.
Wash fruit, cut into wedges or chunks.
Put a toothpick in each piece of fruit or put several fruits on skewers.
Arrange the fruit on a platter and serve with the dip.

title: noel nibbles
directions: Slice frankfurters.
Add preserves, barbecue sauce and frankfurters.
Simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add pineapple.
Heat thoroughly.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine corn syrup and chocolate in a double boiler.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted. Remove from heat.
Beat with a rotary beater until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Serve hot.
Can be stored in refrigerator; reheat over hot water.

title: jello-cream berry cake
directions: Make cake and cool.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in thawed strawberries, sugar and salt.
Cool until thickened. Fold in Cool Whip. Cover a 9 x 13-inch pan with broken pieces of 1/2 the cake.
Pour half of jello mixture over it.
Then the other half of cake pieces on top of that.
Then the rest of jello mixture.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours.

title: white chicken chili
directions: Simmer beans, half the onions, and half the garlic 2 hrs in the chicken stock or until the beans soften, stirring frequently. Add chicken and salsa. Saute pepper, spices, and the remaining onions and garlic in the oil and add to the chili. Simmer for one more hour. Garnish with Sour cream or Monterey Jack Cheese.

title: marinade for pork chops
directions: Mix in 1-quart bowl.
Pour over 4 to 6 pork chops.
Marinate 1 to 3 hours, then grill.
Pork chops can also be baked in oven until done.

title: crab salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water in a 2-quart glass dish.
Add pie filling and pineapple and chill until firm.
Combine cheese, sour cream, nuts and sugar.
Spread over jello mixture.
Chill and serve.
Great with turkey and dressing for holidays.

title: 2-tone icing
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar, salt, cream of tartar and water in double boiler over boiling water.
Beat with mixer 7 minutes or until icing peaks.
Remove from heat.
Continue beating until it cools.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla.

title: chocolate kahlua trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package and bake as directed. Let brownies cool and then cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Prepare pudding mix but do not chill.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except carrots and nuts until well blended.
Add carrots and mix well.
Remove from mixer.
Add nuts. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: noodles romanoff(side dish)
directions: Boil water in large pan; add noodles.
In small saucepan, melt 2 to 3 tablespoons butter, adding Velveeta, cubed.
Stir constantly.
After the cheese and butter are melted, add sour cream, salt and pepper.
Drain noodles.
Stir cheese mixture into noodles.
Serve hot.
Great with barbecue ribs and pork chops.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Butter a 6-cup loaf pan and line with parchment paper.

title: pineapple zucchini loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5-inch pans. Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Blend well. Add zucchini.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; add to butter.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Mix well. Bake about 1 hour.

title: butter balls
directions: Roll into balls and bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: spidery chocolate treats
directions: Melt the chocolate in double boiler, or use a microwave oven for 1 to 2 minutes at 50% power.
Stir in the rice cereal and coconut.
Drop mixture onto wax paper, a teaspoon at a time. Chill in refrigerator until set.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix all ingredients; spoon into casserole dish.
Spread cheese on top and cook until cheese melts at 350°.

title: white chocolate bread pudding with sauce
directions: Melt 10 ounces white chocolate over a double boiler; stir until chocolate melts and is smooth. In separate pan, combine egg yolks, eggs, sugar, vanilla, 2 cups whipping cream, milk and salt. Stir mixture very well. Then heat until just lukewarm. Do not let it get too hot. Add chocolate to mixture and blend until smooth. Place lightly toasted bread crumbs in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan or baking dish. Pour mixture over bread. Let mixture soak until bread is moist. When bread is moist, cover tightly with foil. Set pan into a larger pan. Add water to larger pan. Bake at 275° for 1 hour. Remove foil and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: oriental fried rice
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons peanut oil in wok on high.
Lightly beat eggs and slowly pour into hot oil.
Swirl the wok until egg sets. Remove from wok and put on cutting board.
Put 1/4 cup peanut oil in wok and heat to high.
Add cooked rice and stir-fry until heated through.
Add onions, ham, ginger and pea pods.
Slice the cooked eggs after slicing them into 3-inch long strips and add to rice mixture.
Add soy sauce a small amount at a time to desired taste.

title: arizona clam chowder
directions: In 3 to 4-quart pan, cook bacon over medium heat until lightly browned, about 5 minutes; stir often.
Add onion, chili and celery and cook, stirring often, until veggies are slightly browned, 10 to 14 minutes.
Stir in potato, thyme, clams with their liquid, clam juice, tomatoes and then liquid (break up tomatoes with a spoon).
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are tender to bite, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and pepper on waxed paper.
Coat slices with flour mixture.
Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in large skillet over medium heat.
Add tomatoes in a single layer.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes per side until lightly browned and just barely tender. Remove to serving platter.
Repeat with remaining margarine and tomatoes.
Serves 4.

title: hurry-up hamantaschen
directions: Cut cookie dough into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Roll each slice into 2 1/2-inch circle.
Place a teaspoon of filling in center. Pinch edges together to form triangle.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 14 minutes until golden brown.
Cool at least 10 minutes before serving.

title: monterey weekend supper
directions: Parboil zucchini with garlic salt.
Cook rice with 1/2 salt and pepper.
Slit chilies; remove seeds.
Cut cheese into thin slices (reserving 1/2 of cheese grated for topping).

title: chicken paprika
directions: Wash and dry the chicken.
Rub with salt and pepper.
Heat the oil in a deep skillet.
Brown the chicken in it and remove.

title: mexi-corn salsa
directions: Remove husks and silks from corn.
Place ears in boiling water to cover.
Return water to a boil and cook 4 minutes.
Drain and immediately cover ears with ice water.
Drain corn and cut from cob.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, egg and vanilla until smooth in a large mixing bowl. Add flour, baking soda and salt, mix well.
Add fresh apples and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350 F in 9 x 13 pan for approximately 1 hr.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat Blue Bonnet 70% quarters and powdered sugar with electric mixer, until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream.
Beat at low speed until just blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, until toothpick comes out clean.

title: penny carrots
directions: Slice carrots and cook until crisp-tender.
Combine diced pepper and onions.
Mix tomato soup, oil, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, mustard and salt. Pour over carrots, pepper and onions.
Let marinate overnight.
Serve cold.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Melt butter and blend in cheese, soup and onion.
Mix well. Remove from heat and add sour cream.
Mix cheese mixture with the frozen hash browns.
Pour into baking dish that has been greased and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli ham ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coarsely chop ham, broccoli and onion with food chopper.
Finely snip parsley.
Grate cheese.
Mix all except rolls.
Arrange crescent triangles in circle on a 13-inch baking pizza pan slightly greased.
Spoon filling over base all around circle.
Fold points of triangle rolls over filling and tuck under base at center.
Filling will not be completely covered.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Add finely chopped onion, green pepper, celery, grated carrot and bite-size tomatoes into cold, cooked spaghetti.
Add bottle salad dressing and sliced olives.
Mix well, then sprinkle Salad Supreme.
Chill and enjoy.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add nuts.
Fold in eggs.
Bake in bread pan in slow oven for about 1 hour at 325°.

title: meat loaves and zucchini
directions: In large skillet over medium heat, fry bacon until light brown.
Meanwhile in medium size bowl mix well, ground beef, eggs and next 4 ingredients.
Shape into 3 small meat loaves.
Push bacon to one side of skillet.
Over medium heat, in the hot bacon fat brown meat loaves well on all sides.
Add sliced zucchini and tomato sauce.
Cover and cook 15 minutes or until zucchini is tender-crisp.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Pop the corn in oil.
Melt marshmallows with 1/2 stick margarine.
Pour in M&M's and peanuts.
Mix in popcorn.
Pour into well greased Bundt pan.
Let cool, then turn out onto plate. (Could also make in 13 x 9-inch pan.)
Kids love this.

title: swiss mocha
directions: Mix together.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, dissolve 2 teaspoons more or less, in a cup of hot water.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix condensed milk, lemonade and Cool Whip together.
Then pour into pie crust.
Put in icebox until time of serving.
Serves 8.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out pizza crust thin, but don't make any holes.
Cut into 4 squares.
Lay ham on each piece, then put cheese on top.
Roll the dough from corner to opposite corner (diagonally).
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Put in oven for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Heat pizza sauce.
You can dip the roll-ups in the pizza sauce.
Be sure to pinch the ends of the roll-ups before putting in the oven.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix oleo, flour and nuts and pat on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: bacon-wrapped meat loaves
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except bacon.
Shape mixture into 6 loaves.
Crisscross 2 half slices bacon on each loaf, tucking ends under loaf.
Secure on top of loaf with toothpick.
Place loaves in shallow baking pan, lined with foil. Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until loaves are done in middle when toothpick is removed.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls in pan and bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cream the cream cheese; add dressing.
Add the mayonnaise; spread this on the crust.
Top with the chopped vegetables, then top vegetables with lots of grated Cheddar cheese.

title: yummy apple cake
directions: Combine
cream	cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 egg, mixing well. Set
aside.
Combine flour, remaining 1 1/2 cups sugar, baking soda,
cinnamon
and salt.	Add combined oil and eggs, mixing just
until
moistened.
Fold
in
apples
and
nuts. Reserve
2 cups of batter.
Pour remaining batter into greased and
floured 10-inch tube pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture over batter; carefully
spoon
reserved	batter	over cream cheese mixture. Spread
lightly
to cover.	Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool;
remove from pan.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Combine all vegetables in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt; cover with cold water and let set 4 hours.
Drain thoroughly in colander; press out excess liquid.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water and stir until slightly jelled. Add juice, cranberries, nuts and celery. Chill until jelled firmly.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef.
Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Drain.
Stir in tomatoes, paste, water, garlic and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.

title: blessed stew
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Serves 15.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand for 30 minutes, then bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: dijon chicken
directions: Mix together mayonnaise and mustard.
Coat chicken in mixture. Roll in cornflakes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: m-m-m cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large bowl, beat the eggs.
Add the buttermilk, milk, vegetable oil and margarine.
Add the sugar, flour and cornmeal, mixing just until combined.
This may be baked in muffin tins (8 to 10 minutes) or in iron skillets which have been heated in the oven (15 to 20 minutes for a 12-inch skillet). It may also be cooked on a griddle.
May be made 30 minutes or more before cooking.

title: blueberry or cherry delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine (softened) and nuts well.
Spread in 8 x 12 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Cool completely before filling.

title: fannie mae fudge
directions: Use a 3-quart saucepan to melt ingredients.
Mix sugar, butter, milk and vanilla.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Add all the chocolate pieces; stir until melted.
Add nuts.
Pour into buttered pan.
Makes about 5 pounds.

title: three-in-one dip
directions: Beat all ingredients at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Refrigerate. Serve hot or cold with tortilla chips and vegetable dippers.
Makes approximately 2 cups.

title: glorified chicken
directions: Lay chicken breasts in casserole dish.
Lay 1 slice of cheese on each breast. Pour croutons (slightly crushed) on top.
Combine soup, sherry and melted butter.
Pour over chicken with croutons. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broiled chicken breasts sesame
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Marinate chicken in sauce mixture for at least 3 hours.
Broil breasts over a medium charcoal fire for 4 or 5 minutes on each side, starting with the skin side up and basting with the marinade 2 or 3 times.
Remove the chicken from fire when done; brush with marinade.
Roll in sesame seed until well coated.
Return to fire for a minute to brown seed.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and shape into patties.
Coat in bread crumbs and oleo.
Fry in oleo until brown.
Substitute tuna, if desired.

title: mexican dip
directions: Heat chili and cream cheese.
Serve with taco chips for dipping.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows, then add dry jello.
Pour over popped corn and mix quickly.
Form into balls.

title: seasoned country fried chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a plastic bag and shake to mix. Beat egg with milk.
Dip fryer pieces into egg mixture, then into dry mixture in bag.
Heat oil in frypan to 350°; add chicken pieces and fry on each side until golden brown and cooked through.

title: cookies
directions: Put in blender and mix well.
Make balls with mixture smaller than a golf ball because they spread out when they cook.
Mash flat with fork on cookie sheet.
Do not grease cookie sheet.
Cook about 15 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: blueberry squares
directions: Mix all ingredients except preserves.
Spread in buttered 9 x 12-inch pan and score in 12 blocks or 16 blocks.
Put 1/2 teaspoon Smucker's blueberry preserves in each block.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Eat!

title: a taste of thanksgiving
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water for 20 minutes.
Drain.
Combine noodles, turkey, pimento and peas and carrots in large mixing bowl.
In saucepan, combine soup, milk, water and cheese.
Heat to boiling point, stirring frequently to prevent scorching.
Pour cheese sauce over other ingredients and mix.
Place entire noodle mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: patrick and daniel's green stuff
directions: Chill milk for one hour.
Prepare Jell-O as directed on package.
Mix in cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
(May heat if necessary to dissolve.)
Whip milk until stiff.
Add lemon juice and Jell-O mixture.
Beat or stir at low speed to mix well. Pour into crusts.
Put into freezer.
(Other flavors of Jell-O may be used.)

title: rock cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Cream eggs, sugar and margarine.
Sift flour, cinnamon and salt. Combine the 2 mixtures.
Fold in fruit, dates and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake until lightly browned. These keep well.

title: squash supreme
directions: Boil together squash and onion for 5 minutes.
Drain well in colander.
Drain water chestnuts and add to squash with pimentos, sour cream and salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Melt margarine in glass 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cover bottom of dish with stuffing mix reserving half to sprinkle on top.
Spoon squash mixture over stuffing and sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Cover and bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: dutch apple cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and salt.
Beat the eggs, one by one, into the mixture.
Add the sifted flour gradually.
Pour half of the batter in a loaf pan.
Put 1/2 sliced apples on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Add the rest of the batter and remaining sliced apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top of the apples.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: strawberry icebox pie
directions: Mix strawberries with Cool Whip, powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Dissolve gelatin in water in saucepan on stove on low heat.
Stir consistently.
Put layer of strawberries mixture alternately with vanilla wafers in large dish.
Place in refrigerator or freezer.
(Be sure to mix gelatin mixture with strawberries and Cool Whip mixture.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Save out 1 1/2 cups of cornbread crumbs and enough butter to mix for topping.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a well-greased casserole dish.
Crumble cornbread mixture on top. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer all items in order.
Then sprinkle 1 teaspoon sugar over peas.
Cover with mayonnaise, 1 to 2 cups.
Then sprinkle 1 teaspoon sugar over mayonnaise.
Cover with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: african chicken stew
directions: Before cooking, divide breasts and thighs in half again.
Mix flour with curry powder, salt and pepper.
Place flour mixture in paper bag and shake chicken pieces in it a few at a time.
Heat oil in large skillet or Dutch oven until hot but not smoking.
Saute chicken pieces in skillet until brown on each side.
Set aside. Remove any excess fat from skillet and saute onions briefly in pan. Stir in curry paste, then add all remaining ingredients, except potatoes and peas.
Stir together and return chicken to pot. Simmer stew on top of stove for 1 hour on medium-high.
Add potatoes and simmer another 30 minutes.
Add peas and simmer an additional 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix first
ingredients.
Pour into 8 x 10-inch glass dish. Pat down to cover bottom.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. With mixer, mix cheese and sugar.
Fold in 1/2 of large carton of Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Layer graham cracker crumbs, chips, nuts, coconut and then pour milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage; drain. Put sausage back into pan; add cream cheese and Ro-Tel. Simmer on top of stove on low heat until boiling, stirring often. Great served on biscuits, toast or Melba toast.

title: company chicken cordon bleu
directions: Place each piece of chicken between 2 sheets of waxed paper; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: potato leek soup
directions: Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Cover with Saran Wrap and let rest overnight.
Prior to serving, add layer of 6 hard-boiled eggs, finely chopped, and sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: old-fashioned pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt 1/3 cup butter in 10-inch cast-iron skillet.
Remove from heat.
Add brown sugar and stir until blended.
Drain pineapple well.
Reserve 2 tablespoons syrup.
Arrange pineapple in butter/sugar mixture.
Place cherry in center.
Beat remaining 1/3 cup butter with 1/2 cup granulated sugar until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks, lemon peel and juice and vanilla.

title: custard
directions: Beat egg
yolks and stir into milk.
Add vanilla.
Stir flour into sugar and add to milk mixture.
Cook until scalding hot in heavy
pan, stirring constantly.
Do not let boil.	Add allspice slowly and stir in.
This is really creamy.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Combine hamburger and remaining ingredients in casserole.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover with sliced cheese (American, Monterey, etc.)
Bake on low until cheese melts.

title: cheese & vegetable chowder
directions: Saute onion in margarine until soft.
Add vegetables and cook until heated through.
Remove from heat and add flour, stirring well to coat.
Add chicken broth and heat through.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add milk and heat until just boiling.
Serve with crusty Italian bread or your favorite crackers.

title: jalapeno clam dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well adding tabasco sauce to degree of hotness to suit your taste!
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and can of water.
Pour into a baking dish.
Place chicken on top. Sprinkle dry Lipton onion soup on top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cook asparagus spears.
Place cooked asparagus in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle almonds on top of asparagus.
Pour mushroom soup over asparagus.
Top with cheese. Heat at 400° until cheese is melted.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: Boil raisins and water for 20 minutes; add shortening.
When it cools, add egg and dry ingredients.
Spread on jelly roll pan and bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
When cool, spread with thin powdered sugar icing with a little lemon juice in it.

title: chicken baton rouge
directions: Pound chicken until thin.
Coat with bread crumbs.
Saute in just enough margarine to cover bottom of pan (about 3 to 4 tablespoons) until brown.
Make sauce by adding brandy, heavy cream and mustard to pan after pouring off most of margarine. Cook slowly, stirring often.
Add chopped pecans and pour over chicken.
Serve immediately.

title: mel's fabulous grilled cheese
directions: Warm nonstick frying pan on medium.
Butter one side of both pieces of bread.
Slice enough cheese to cover bread.
Place the cheese on the unbuttered side of the bread.
Place ham on top of the cheese.
Place other slice of bread on top with buttered side up.
Place the sandwich in the warmed pan and cover so the cheese will melt.
Fry for about 1 1/2 minutes or until golden brown, flip and fry again for 1 minute, until golden brown.
Remove from the pan and enjoy.
Peanut butter and jelly may be substituted for the ham and cheese.
Serves 1 person.

title: haystack cookies
directions: Melt together chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Add peanuts and chow mein noodles.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet and place in refrigerator to harden.

title: double "d" dip
directions: Cube and melt cheese in microwave.
Add remaining ingredients. Serve with your choice of chips, veggies, crackers.

title: lime grilled chicken
directions: In a small bowl, mix together soy sauce, lime juice, olive oil, and garlic.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and marinate for 1 hour.
Heat grill to medium.
Cook chicken 5 minutes, turn and cook 5 move minutes, turn again 2 more times.
You may need to turn heat to low depending on your grill temperature.

title: tomato aspic salad
directions: Cook
all
together for about half hour and run through sieve. Dissolve
packages of Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water; add to other mixture and pour into molds or flat glass dish.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Cook yellow rice according to directions on package.
Combine hamburger, salsa and cooked yellow rice in casserole dish.
Sprinkle taco seasoning and 1/2 cup water over the mixture and half of the cheese.
Mix well.

title: baked rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all in large bowl.
Spray baking dish with vegetable spray.
Pour mixture in baking dish and bake for 25 to 35 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: party cheese balls
directions: Make in ball.
Shape and roll in chopped pecans.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Cook vegetables.
Drain.
Add soup and sour cream.
Mix.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Top with onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In deep bowl, stir flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Combine eggs and milk; pour into dry ingredients.
Stir with whisk or mixer until smooth.
Heat 1 1/2 to 2-inches of oil in heavy skillet or deep fryer to 375°.
Hold finger over end of funnel. Place 1/2 cup batter in funnel.
Remove finger from end of funnel and, with slow motion, dribble batter into hot oil in shape of a coil.
Fry cakes 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Turn over.
Remove cake; drain on paper towels.
Sift confectioners sugar over warm cake or serve with syrup and cinnamon.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil and
bone
chicken.
Lay
aside on plate.
Put the other ingredients in a deep saucepan, except Doritos.
Put 1/2 chips in bottom
of a 10-inch baking dish; add chicken mixture and top with chips.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: better than sex cake?
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Blend together; add wings and marinate at least 6 hours.
Cook 20 minutes at 400°; then 40 minutes at 350°.
They're the best!!

title: sweet and sour porklubbock, texas
directions: Cut pork into pieces 1 X 1 X 1/2-inch.
Mix flour and seasonings.
Mix egg and milk; beat well.
Roll pork in flour mixture and shake off excess.
Dip in milk mixture and mix thoroughly.
Drain well, then dip in flour mixture again, mixing until well coatd.
Shake off excess flour and fry in deep fat at 350° until the crust is brown and crisp, then drain and place on plate.
Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: diana's coleslaw
directions: Grate cabbage and carrots in blender.
In small bowl, mix other ingredients.
Toss into cabbage mixture until completely covered.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350°
for 12 - 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Pound
enough
chicken
breasts
for
your family until flat. Coat
with
bread
crumbs and pan-fry until done.
Pour enough spaghetti
sauce
into
a 9 x 13-inch pan to just cover the bottom.
Arrange cooked chicken on top of the sauce.
Pour additional sauce over the top to completely cover the chicken. Sprinkle a
generous
amount
of Parmesan cheese over the top. Garnish with parsley flakes.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake four hours, uncovered, in oven at 250°.
Serve over rice or noodles.
May be prepared ahead and frozen.

title: danish frecedella(meatballs)
directions: Mix ground beef or turkey, milk, onion and salt.
Add flour. Make balls by throwing spoonfuls several times against the side of the bowl.
Brown on 3 sides in hot fat.
Serves 4.

title: ranch roasted potatoes
directions: Slice new potatoes and place in plastic bag. Pour oil in on potatoes and toss. Add your Ranch dressing mix and toss again. Put potatoes in a Pyrex dish and bake in an oven at 450° for about 45 minutes.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 10 x 15 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Preheat oven to 400°.
In large mixing bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Measure into large, heavy saucepan 2 sticks margarine, 5 tablespoons cocoa and water.
Heat saucepan mixture to boiling, stirring well.
Add to flour-sugar combination, blending well.
In medium bowl, beat eggs; stir soda into buttermilk.
Add to eggs along with vanilla.
Add this buttermilk mixture to the flour-cocoa combination.
Mix well.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake about 25 minutes or until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Place sweet potatoes in 2 to 3 1/2-quart slow cooker. Mix remaining ingredients except nuts; spoon over potatoes. Cover and cook on low heat setting 6 to 8 hours or until potatoes are very tender.

title: pineapple-zucchini bread or muffins
directions: Spray 2 small loaf pans (7 1/2 x 3 1/2-inches) or one large loaf pan with Pam.
In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients. Add dry ingredients.
Fold in zucchini.
Pour in pans or muffin cups.
Makes 16 servings.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut corn off the cob and mix with tomatoes and green pepper in a bowl.
In frying pan cook bacon strips; remove bacon and cut or chop into pieces.
Add 1 cup water to pan.
In pan, stir in corn mixture together with bacon.
Cook over medium heat and stir to keep from sticking.
If ingredients are sticking add 1/2 cup water. Cook for approximately 30 minutes.

title: candy buckeyes
directions: Mix together the sugar, peanut butter and margarine; roll into balls.
Dip balls into chocolate and paraffin (melted in double boiler), leaving small circle of peanut butter showing to look like a buckeye.

title: spaghetti and smoked sausage(kids love this)
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Set aside.
Cut sausage in small circles.
Saute sausage for 5 minutes.
Remove sausage from skillet with slotted spoon and drain.
Add onion and garlic to skillet with drippings left from sausage.
Saute for 4 to 5 minutes.
Do not brown.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste and tomatoes (that have been crushed with juice).
Rinse tomato sauce and tomato paste cans out with water and add to mixture.
Depending on how thick you want sauce, you can add 1/2 can of water from the tomato can, if you want.
Add smoked sausage and drippings. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add cooked and drained spaghetti to mixture.
Add a little at a time to make sure you don't add too much spaghetti and take up all the sauce.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, milk and cocoa; bring to boil.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat, add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Spoon onto foil and cool.
Makes 15 cookies.

title: frozen delight
directions: Use a container about 4 inches high, 8 inches long and 4 inches wide.
I used a Rubbermaid container.

title: bean burritos(makes 4 servings)
directions: Place the cooked kidney beans in a medium-sized bowl, and mash these to the desired consistency.
Coat a small nonstick skillet with canola oil, and place it over medium heat until hot.
Add the onion, red bell pepper and garlic; saute for 5 minutes or until the onion is tender.
Stir in the cumin, coriander and white pepper.
Cook for 1 minute, and remove from heat.
Add the onion mixture and corn to the beans; stir well.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream the Crisco, oleo, sugar, vanilla and egg until fluffy.
Stir in dry ingredients. Blend in milk.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet; flatten with bottom of glass which has been greased and dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
Carefully remove yolks.
Mash yolks and stir in mustard, add mayonnaise; blend well.
Spoon yolk mixture evenly into egg whites.
Place an olive half in the center of each.
Sprinkle with cajun seasoning.

title: mandarin vinegar
directions: Place vinegar, sugar and mandarin peel in a large saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Cool and store in covered container.
Use as you would for any recipe calling for vinegar.
This mandarin vinegar adds zest to your recipes and also makes a delightful and unusual hostess gift.
Yields 1 quart.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Add zucchini.
Beat all ingredients.
Add oil and beat until smooth.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: michael's chocolate cookies
directions: My mom does what I ask her to do.
You put this much chocolate in and stir it.
Put it in the oven and that's it.

title: baked meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make about 70 meatballs. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan or crock-pot.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown steak and onion; drain grease.
Add mushrooms and soup. Fill can 1/2 full of water and add.
Stir in sour cream, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and cook over low or medium heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Prepare noodles, drain and add to mixture.
Keep covered until ready to serve.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly the butter, shortening, sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Work in flour and salt until dough holds together. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Beat egg white; dip balls in egg white and roll in nuts.
Press center down with thumb.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
When cool, put Butter Cream Frosting in center.

title: baked cranberry relish
directions: Toss cranberries and sugar.
Place in a lightly greased baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir in walnuts, marmalade, and lemon juice and refrigerate.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground beef in large saucepan draining excess fat.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomato paste, water, bouillon cube, green pepper and onion.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook rigatoni and small shells for 15 minutes in boiling water.
Drain.
Layer 1/2 cooked macaroni in 2 qt. casserole dish.
Add layer of 1/2 of the mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle with romano.
Layer rest of cooked macaroni.
Pour sauce over all.
Top with remaining mozzarella cheese and romano cheese. Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: squash croquettes
directions: Combine squash, onion, egg, salt and pepper; mix well. Stir in flour. Drop by tablespoons into hot oil. Cook until brown, turning only once.

title: chili-cheese dip
directions: Brown beef well; drain off excess grease.
Add all other ingredients to beef.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Stir often.
Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: almost snickers
directions: Mix together and place in 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Freeze; cut into 9 squares.
One piece equals 1 fat.

title: joy's buttermilk pie
directions: Mix ingredients. Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 325° about 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix it up!
Grease and flour loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine butter, milk, sugar and salt; boil for 12 minutes or desired soft ball stage, stirring at all times.
Remove from heat. Quickly add marshmallow cream to melt, then chocolate chips to melt.
Thoroughly mix in vanilla.
Pour into one large buttered cookie sheet 1 inch deep or one 9 x 12-inch pan and one 8 x 8-inch pan.
Makes 50 pieces.

title: apple pie filling
directions: In large saucepan blend sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg. Stir in water.
Bring to a boil and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice.
Pack prepared apples into jars.
Fill with hot syrup.
Process in boiling water bath 20 minutes for quarts, 15 minutes for pints. Makes about 3 1/2 quarts.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: short method dill pickles
directions: Combine sugar, salt, vinegar and water.
Tie spices in a cheesecloth bag.
Add to vinegar mixture.
Simmer 15 minutes. Pack cucumbers into hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch space at top.
Put a head of dill in each jar.
Heat brine to boiling.
Pour boiling hot vinegar mixture over cucumbers, leaving 1/4-inch space at top. Adjust caps.
Process pints and quarts 15 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes about 7 pints.

title: beef gravy
directions: Scramble and cook ground beef until light brown (done). Sprinkle flour on top and stir around, cooking on medium heat. Salt and add milk.
Cook until it thickens.
It can be served on toast.
Cooked thicker, it can be served on buns as a sandwich.

title: stir-fry pepper steak
directions: Slice steak diagonally into thin slices, then cut into 1-inch squares.
Heat half the oil in wok.
Add pepper and salt.
Saute steak until browned.
Transfer to plate.
Add rest of oil and heat.
Add green pepper, celery, garlic and bouillon.
Turn heat down.
Return meat to wok.
Cover and cook until vegetables are crispy tender, about 5 minutes.
Blend water, soy sauce and cornstarch together.
Add to meat mixture.
Cook until thickened, stirring, about 5 minutes.
Serve with hot rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand in ice cubes for 3 hours.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Add cucumbers, onions and bell peppers.
Bring to boiling point.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Seal in sterilized jars. Process for 10 minutes at simmering temperature, about 180°.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer until onion is tender. (Do not drain vegetables.) If soup seems too thick, add 1/2 to 1 cup water.

title: pizza dippers
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Crumble.
Drain.
Set aside. Combine flour, cheese and salt in mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture is the size of small peas.
Stir in sausage.
Add water, a little at a time, tossing and stirring with fork until dough is just moist enough to hold together.
Shape into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.
Serve hot dipped in sauce.
Makes about 40.

title: lettuce dressing(why use store bought dressing?  make your own.)
directions: Cut up bacon into small pieces and fry in skillet with onions. Add flour and stir.
Place in bowl and add water, sugar and vinegar.
Mix well.
Pour over vegetables and bake.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix with cocoa.
Add vanilla, buttermilk, food coloring, butter and eggs.
Blend until moist.
Add soda and vinegar. Mix into cake mix.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes in layer pans.
Cool and frost.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Beat eggs.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch cake pan for 45 minutes at 350° (with English muffins and fruit, makes a great breakfast for company).

title: blueberry bars
directions: Place flour and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Cut in margarine until size of small peas.
Measure 3/4 cup of mixture and reserve for crumb topping.
Add unbeaten egg yolks and 1 cup milk to remaining crumb mixture in bowl.
Beat for 3 minutes until well blended (electric mixer at low).
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold gently, but thoroughly, into batter.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add other ingredients and heat until warm.
Do not boil.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mamaw's salad
directions: Make a layer of marshmallows, a layer of pineapple, a layer of cheese, a layer of nuts and a layer of whipped cream.
Sprinkle top with nuts.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: vegetable-lentil soup
directions: Put lentils, water, salt and lard in big soup pot and bring to boil.
Cook on medium 30 minutes.
In frypan, melt 2 tablespoons butter and saute onion, green pepper and celery until tender.
Add to lentils.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are tender.

title: chicken mornay
directions: Melt butter; add flour with a whisk.
Should be thick.
Add more flour, if necessary.
Set aside.

title: mommie's pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Should be able to stick your finger in without burning yourself.
Stir in remaining ingredients, mixing vigorously.
Heat oven to 425°.
Shouldn't be sticky.
Should be semi-firm, but workable.
If sticky, add a little flour.
Let set for 5 to 10 minutes (cover bowl).
Cook 15 minutes.
Cover pizza pan with oil.
Sprinkle cornmeal.
Press in dough.

title: hello dollies
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press into pan. Layer coconut, chocolate chips and pecans.
Drizzle milk over top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add cooking oil and stir well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir well after each.
Add carrots and nuts. Bake in 3 (8-inch) pans at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.
The baby food makes this cake very moist.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Icing.
Spread between each layer.
Spread the rest on top and sides.

title: chocolate chip-date nut cake
directions: Pour hot water over dates.
Add soda.
Let stand.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg, milk and date mixture.
Add flour, 1/2 cup nuts and 1/2 cup chips.
Pour batter in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle remaining nuts and chips over top.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Does not need frosting.

title: venison jerky
directions: Cut venison crossgrain into narrow strips.
Combine all ingredients.
Marinate 24 hours.
Dry meat in a shallow pan in single layers for 16 hours over low heat, turning often.
Or hang meat in a warm, clean area for 3 days.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs, then chop and mix in large bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Chill for 20 minutes.

title: super tuna loaf
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup tomato soup with tuna, bread cubes, eggs, parsley and lemon juice.
Spread into a well-greased loaf pan. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Heat water, remaining soup, horseradish and basil.
Use for dipping tuna loaf in or for pouring over tuna loaf.

title: amish dandelion gravy
directions: Combine flour and butter.
Add enough milk to make a thin gravy and bring to a boil.
Add eggs, vinegar, salt, onion and sugar.
Just before serving, add dandelion leaves.

title: chicken pot pies
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cook peas and carrots according to package directions; drain.

title: mushroom cheese mold
directions: Combine cheeses, garlic, mustard and salt in a bowl.
Add chopped mushrooms, onion, pimento and parsley.
Turn mixture into lightly buttered 3-cup mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Unmold onto serving platter.
Garnish with sliced mushrooms and parsley. Serve with crackers.
Makes 3 1/2 cups spread.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare rice according to package directions.
Set aside.
Saute celery, peppers, onions and mushrooms in oil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Fold in rice.
Pour into an oiled 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Fry the bacon.
Crumble and add to soup.
Use drippings, flour and milk to make a gravy and add to potatoes.
Add soup to potato mixture.
Cook for 10 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter in a large Pyrex dish; melt in oven.
Mix flour, sugar and milk, like pancake mix.
Pour batter over butter.
Spoon in peaches.
It's okay to let some syrup in too.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sausage wraps
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Cut each triangle lengthwise into thirds.
Place sausage on shortest side of each triangle and roll up. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Crust:
Melt margarine in milk; pour into mixed flour and salt.
Combine well.
Roll out and line a 9 x 13-inch casserole with half.
Save remaining.

title: banana split pie
directions: Layer, chill and divide in fourths.
Only 50 calories per serving.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together; drop by spoonfuls into hot fat.
Dip spoon into water after every use.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Place macaroni, eggs, celery and onion in a large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard, salt, pepper, sugar and vinegar; pour over rest of ingredients.
Mix well.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil at low heat for 5 minutes.
Then add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda and 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Mix.
Pour over 8 quarts popped popcorn.
Put on cookie sheet and bake at 250° for 1 hour.
It is good to stir this while it cools, then it won't stick together.

title: fruit salad(low-fat)
directions: Pour pineapple juice in measuring cup and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups. Cook pudding and juice-water on stove until it boils and thickens. Cool. Mix with fruit and chill.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients and
mix well.	Bake in greased and floured muffin pans at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: better than grandma's meat loaf
directions: Mix well; shape into loaf or bake it in a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until brown and firm.

title: pork and bean salad
directions: Place all ingredients together for a quick last minute salad. Mix thoroughly.
Chill and serve.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs with sugar until thick.
Pour into chilled 1 gallon ice cream cannister.
Mix in milk, cream, vanilla and salt. Insert dasher and assemble ice cream freezer.
Be sure to read and follow manufacturer's special instructions.

title: heavenly healthful ambrosia
directions: Combine yogurt, whipped topping and coconut; set aside.
In large bowl, combine pineapple, oranges and grapes.
Remove 1/2 of mixture from bowl and set aside.
Sprinkle 1/4 c. wheat germ on top of fruit in bowl.
Top with 1/2 of yogurt mixture.
Layer with remaining fruit, wheat germ and yogurt.
If desired, garnish with additional fruit and wheat germ.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill 2 hours to blend flavors.
Stir before serving.
(May substitute 16 oz carton plain low fat yogurt for sour cream.)

title: oven pork chops
directions: In a heavy skillet, brown the pork chops on both sides in the vegetable oil, a minute or 2 per side.
Place the chops in a large casserole dish.
Layer on the potatoes, add the chopped onion.
Add the soup, undiluted.
Cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Raise the oven temperature to 375° and bake for 30 minutes more.
Remove the cover for the last 10 minutes for crispier chops.

title: german chocolate snack cake
directions: Line bottom
of
a
9-inch round baking dish with waxed paper. Place
butter
in
dish.
Microwave
on
High 45 to 60 seconds, until
butter
melts.
Blend brown sugar and half and half into the
butter.
Microwave on High for 1 minute, stirring once. Sprinkle with pecans and coconut.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Place in large pan. Bake at 350° until done. May place around turkey or chicken and bake until done.

title: cheese omelet
directions: Put into a mixing bowl the eggs and milk.
Whip the tar out of the mixture until light and fluffy.

While beating the egg/milk mixture, preheat an omelet pan (folding, hinged pan is best; they are available at Bealls for around $9.99+) until it just sizzles when you sprinkle drops of cold water into pan.
Pour half of the egg mixture into each side of the pan.
Tilt both sides of pan so mixture starts to cook.
When firm, place six pieces of cheese on each side of the pan.
Fold over and cook for a short time, rotating pan until done.

title: wendy's frosty
