directions: Mix all ingredients and churn.

title: old fashioned potato filling
directions: Melt
butter
in
skillet.
Add onion and celery.
Cook until soft; do not burn.	Beat eggs in milk.
Mix all ingredients; put in casserole.
Dot with butter and bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until brown.

title: turkey centerpiece
directions: Place 5 or 6 pretzel sticks in the back of the roll to create a tail.
Use another pretzel stick as a neck at the front of the roll.
Position the marshmallow at the end of the pretzel stick. The marshmallow is the head of the turkey.
Happy Thanksgiving.

title: venison roast baked in foil
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place roast on a large piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Sprinkle the dry onion soup over the meat.
Bring edges of foil together and seal tightly.
Place in shallow roasting pan and bake for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Thicken pan juices for gravy.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Put in casserole.
Moisten Ritz crackers with melted margarine.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecued walnuts
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in a baking dish in oven as it heats.
Stir in sauce and walnuts; toss until walnuts are evenly coated.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes or until toasted.
Spread on paper towel to cool.
Sprinkle with salt. Store in covered container.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix jello, pineapple and sugar in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Let cool completely. Fold in buttermilk, then fold in Cool Whip. Makes 2 quarts.

title: broccoli raisin salad
directions: Mix all 4 ingredients.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir until thickened, reduce heat.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
(Use egg whites for meringue.)
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Gradually stir 1 cup of the hot mixture into yolks; return mixture to sauce pan and stir 2 minutes more. Remove saucepan from heat.
Stir in peanut butter until smooth. Stir in peanuts.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Make meringue and cover pie.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 more minutes.

title: good 'n quick rolls
directions: Put sugar in lukewarm water and dissolve.
Add the other ingredients, mixing well.
Knead flour mixture slightly in bowl. Cut off the portion of dough you will need for the meal's rolls; store the remainder in the refrigerator in a closed container.
Cut individual portions of rolls.
Flatten and fold each piece once, and place in a greased pan.
Cover; let rise for about 4 hours in a warm place.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mom's crumb cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter together until it is fine crumbs. Take out 1/2 cup crumbs and reserve for top of cake.
Add the 2 teaspoons baking powder; mix well.
Add eggs and milk.
Flavor with vanilla; beat well.
Bake in 7 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs on top before baking.
Bake at 350° until tests done.

title: golden glow pie
directions: Put everything except coconut, nuts and chocolate chips in blender.
Mix.
Stir in coconut, nuts and chocolate chips.
Put into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until pie is golden brown.

title: princess bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and 1/4 cup sugar.
Heat mixture on stove and bring to a boil.
Simmer until thick.
Cool and then place in blender and blend until smooth.
In separate bowl, mix remaining sugar (1/2 cup), oats, coconut, flour and baking soda. Cut in butter, using a pastry blender or 2 dinner knives.
Press 2/3 of this mixture on bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread the date mixture on top and then crumble remaining coconut mixture on top.
Bake 30 minutes in preheated 375° oven.

title: reese's chewy chocolate cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well.

title: baked chocolate pudding
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt, cocoa, baking powder.
Add milk, melted butter, nuts and vanilla.
Pour mixture into greased baking dish.
cover with the mixture of white sugar, brown sugar, cocoa.
Over all pour the water.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: ham macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients with macaroni in large mixing bowl.
Chill or serve immediately.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lime buttered fish
directions: Combine in microwave the margarine and lime juice.
Mix grated cheese and bread crumbs.
Coat fish with cheese/crumbs.
In a pan, layer lime butter, fish and lime butter.
Microwave until fish flakes.

title: zucchini skillet
directions: Brown in skillet ground beef; drain fat.
Add flour, salt, pepper and basil to taste.
Add onion, chopped fine.
Add layer of zucchini, thinly sliced and layer of tomatoes, chopped.
Put lid on skillet; steam for 20 minutes over low heat.
(Best when vegetables are fresh.)

title: cheese spinach pie
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender; cool.
Lay slices of cheese over pie dough.
Follow with spinach, then onions.
Beat eggs, adding enough milk to make 1 cup.
Add seasoning and pour over ingredients in the pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven about 35 minutes or until a knife comes out clean.
Serve piping hot.
(Can be frozen after baking.)
Serves 4.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain off excess fat.
Add taco mix and water. Simmer, uncovered, until mixture is thickened (about 15 minutes). Lightly grease bottom of 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Spread refried beans evenly on the bottom.
Sprinkle onion on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pork chop fried rice casserole
directions: In saucepan, bring the 1 3/4 cups water to boil.
Remove from heat; stir in rice.
Cover and set aside.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes until tender and peel.
Mash potatoes and mix all ingredients together until creamy.
Pour into 2 deep dish pie crusts.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or more.

title: ed's delicious frozen strawberry dessert drink
directions: Place strawberries (frozen) into blender (make sure that you break them up first).
Pour water and vanilla (if used) into blender.
Blend at high speed, stopping occasionally to stir. While blending, add banana.
Add ice cubes until desired consistency is reached.
Serve in bowls or glasses, depending on how thick you make it.

title: root beer cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Beat in egg. Add vanilla and root beer oil. Add dry ingredients which have been sifted together. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill dough 3 hours. Roll out 1/8-inch thick in shape of root beer float mugs. Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Cream sugar and cheese together.
Add all other ingredients and stir well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground chuck and add taco seasoning; mix corn, tomatoes, tomato sauce and ground chuck together with beans. Place in a casserole dish. Mix Jiffy mix and pour on top of mixture. Bake until near brown; sprinkle cheese on top then put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: jersey potatoes(no need for baked potatoes)
directions: Scrub potatoes and cut into cubes. Place potatoes in a round microwavable dish and cover with water. Cook on High for 10 minutes. Stir well and microwave in 5 minute intervals until done. Drain water. Salt and pepper to taste. Add melted butter and either sour cream or Ranch dressing.

title: beef wellington
directions: Early in the day or the day before, prepare Quick Puff Pastry and reserve.
Trim any fat from fillet; season with salt and pepper.
Brush with oil.
Place on rack in roasting pan; roast in preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes (for a rare roast).
Remove from oven, cool to room temperature.

title: chocolate caramel nut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup evaporated milk over low heat, stirring frequently until smooth. Set aside.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown, drain and combine with kidney beans, butter beans, pork and beans (juice included), sugar, brown sugar and catsup. Bake at 350° for 3 hours, covered.
I sometimes cook mine in the crock-pot.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt, butter, nutmeg and potatoes.
Beat with mixer until fluffy.
In small bowl, beat egg yolks until light and lemon colored.
Add to potato mixture.
Add raisins and pecans. In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into potatoes and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° 50 - 60 minutes, or until firm.
Top with marshmallows and brown.

title: spicy popcorn
directions: Stir together in a saucepan the peanut butter, sesame or corn oil, soy sauce, ground ginger, garlic powder and cayenne pepper. Pour melted mixture over popcorn and banana chips; put popcorn and banana chips in a roasting pan in the oven.
Heat at 300° for about 10 minutes, stirring several times.
Makes about 5 quarts.

title: ranch biscuits
directions: Dissolve sugar in warm water in a large mixing bowl. Add dry yeast. Add other ingredients.
Mix and let stand to rise. Work down 3 times, then put in refrigerator.
Will keep in refrigerator up to 3 weeks.
(Work down often.) Bake in a 350° oven.

title: cantaloupe cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; beat until smooth.
Add flour, cinnamon and baking soda; mix until smooth.
Fold in fruits. Spread mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Lower the temperature to 325° and bake for 10 minutes more.
Cool and frost.

title: krauter klosschen(meat broth with herb dumplings)
directions: In a small bowl, beat butter until light and creamy.
Beat in egg, breadcrumbs, herbs, salt and nutmeg to make a light, smooth mixture.
Let stand 15 minutes.
In medium saucepan, heat stock and sherry over medium heat.
Using a teaspoon or your hands, shape dough into small dumplings.
Rinse your hands in cold water to prevent sticking.
Gently poach dumplings in heated stock over low heat, about 3 minutes.
Makes 3 servings.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift together dry ingredients. Cut in shortening. Mash sweet potatoes and add to flour mixture with milk. Mix well. Turn onto floured surface and knead lightly. Pinch off and place on lightly greased baking sheet. Place in preheated 425° oven and bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: good and easy swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together soup and water.
Measure out 1/2 cup soup mixture and combine with meat and next 4 ingredients.
Make meatballs in size desired.
Brown in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add rest of soup mixture and simmer 1/2 hour.

title: onion casserole
directions: Slice and quarter onions; boil until tender.
Drain.
While onions are cooking, make white sauce.
Melt margarine in saucepan. Add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute.
Slowly add the milk and stir until boils; boil 1 minute.
In a
1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish, layer onions, white sauce, cracker crumbs, onion, white sauce and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: aunt nancy's peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Shape into marble size balls. Place onto wax paper. Melt candy coating in microwave. Roll in melted chocolate. Replace onto wax paper. Air dry or refrigerate.

title: quick beef stew
directions: Pressure cook beef in 1 1/2 cups water.
While beef is cooking, put potatoes, celery and onion in a large pan to cook.
Salt to taste.
Cover with water.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Pour water off of beef and vegetables.
Combine in one pan.
Add sliced carrots.
Mix seasoning as directed.
Pour over beef and vegetables.
Let simmer for about 1/2 hour.
Will feed 4 to 6 people.

title: down home crab cakes
directions: Combine mayonnaise and egg in a large bowl; mix in next 5 ingredients.
Stir in crabmeat and 1 to 1 1/4 cups breadcrumbs or enough to hold mixture together.
Shape into 8 patties.
Coat patties with remaining breadcrumbs.

title: danish puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Measure first cup flour into bowl.
Cut in butter.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons water and mix with fork. Round into ball and divide in half.
Pat dough with hands into 2 long strips (3 x 12-inches).
Strips should be 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: crock pot beef with gravy
directions: Add all ingredients in a slow cooker or crock pot.
Stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low for about 8 hours.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: sukiyaki
directions: Heat oil in skillet, add meat and brown lightly.
Mix sugar, soy sauce and water.
Cook half of this with meat.
Push meat to one side of pan and add sliced onions, celery and green pepper. Cook a few minutes; add remaining soy sauce mixture, bamboo shoots and mushrooms.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Add green onions; cook 1 minute more.
Serve over rice.
Serves 8.

title: venus de milo soup
directions: Brown hamburg and drain.
Add chopped celery and other ingredients.
Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Place in a buttered pie plate.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: hot crabmeat appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds, mixing until well blended.
Spoon mixture into 9 in. pie plate.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15 min.
Serve with crackers. Makes approx. 1 1/2 cups.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except walnuts.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape chilled mixture into ball.
Roll in nuts. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Crust:
Combine butter, flour and sugar.
Mix until firm. Press onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for ten minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend together the cheese and cream cheese, mixing well.
Mix in onion, garlic and Worcestershire.
Form into a ball.
Sprinkle with paprika, roll in finely chopped pecans to cover.
Serve with crackers.

title: pork st. tammany
directions: Cook rice according to package directions and set aside.
Pour boiling water over apricots.
Let stand 20 minutes to soften. Drain.
Saute green onions, mushrooms and green pepper in butter until tender. Stir in rice, apricots, pecans, parsley and seasonings.
Remove strings and slice roast in half lengthwise, if not purchased sliced.
Slice pork pieces lengthwise in half again, slicing to but not through one side.
Lay pieces side by side and spoon stuffing mixture evenly over pork.
Beginning with long side, roll pork in jelly roll fashion and tie securely with heavy string at 2-inch intervals.
Place roast on a lightly greased rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Place bacon lengthwise over roast. Insert meat thermometer into thickest part of roast, making sure it does not touch fat or stuffing.
Place an aluminum foil tent over roast. Bake at 325° for 3 hours or until meat thermometer registers 160° (30 to 35 minutes per pound).
Remove foil for the last 30 to 40 minutes of baking. Remove roast from oven.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Remove string, slice and garnish with apricot halves and parsley, if desired.
Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: jello molded salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and juice.
Stir in sherbet.
Add oranges.
Pour into mold.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine listed ingredients in a large mixing bowl and mix together with a wooden spoon.
Pour into well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes. Top with cream cheese frosting.
(I use Betty Crocker or Duncan Hines.)

title: peach-almond pound cake
directions: Cream butter, gradually adding sugar and beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Combine sour cream and peaches.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with peach mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.

title: pasta raphael
directions: Lightly drain tomatoes, reserve liquid.
Combine tomatoes and undrained artichokes in a large bowl.
Heat olive oil in a large saucepan.
Saute onions, garlic, basil, oregano, parsley and red pepper flakes over medium heat for 5 minutes or until onions are translucent.
Add tomato and artichoke mixture, season with salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, over medium heat at least 1 hour (longer is better).
Break up tomatoes and artichokes as they cook. If sauce is too thick add reserved tomato liquid.
Before serving add Romano and stir until incorporated.
Serve hot or room temperature over tortellini.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple pyramid
directions: Arrange the pineapple on a serving tray.
Top with sliced cranberry.
Add cottage cheese and cherry.
(It would look like a pyramid.)

title: shrimp creole
directions: Brown flour and butter.
Add all ingredients except tomatoes, shrimp and rice.
Cook 5 minutes; add tomatoes and shrimp and cook 1 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Bring to boil and make thick with Clear Jell.

title: cheese and spinach casserole
directions: Put cottage cheese in mixing bowl.
Add eggs.
Add cheese and butter.
Cut into coarse pieces.
Stir.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken; debone and take skin off.
Boil eggs, dice celery, dice pickles, dice onions and drain pineapple.
Mix all together and add salad dressing to taste.
Salt and pepper.

title: apple dumplings deluxe(1929 recipe from better homes and gardens)
directions: Mix dry ingredients into wet.
Roll 12 x 12-inches.
Cover with apples, spices and 1/4 cup sugar.
Roll up.
Cut 1-inch slices.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, cut side down.

title: cole slaw
directions: (I substitute white vinegar and sprinkle garlic salt and basil over the top of the vinegar to taste.)
Beat all ingredients, except cabbage, with mixer.
Pour over cabbage.
Do not stir. Cover and chill in refrigerator for 30 minutes before mixing salad.
Salad is best when cabbage is shredded into thin strings. Will keep in refrigerator for weeks.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together.
Chill 2 hours or more.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll dough on well floured board.
Cut into shapes.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam. Cut biscuits into fourths. Dip biscuit pieces, one at a time, in butter, then in cinnamon and sugar mixture. Sprinkle pecan pieces over biscuits.

Stand each biscuit piece up around Bundt pan. Mix remaining butter, cinnamon and sugar over low heat until sugar is completely melted. Pour this over biscuits in pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter rice krispies treats
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Using buttered spatula or wax paper, press mixture evenly into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray or butter. Cut into squares when cool.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Mix in other ingredients. Chill.

title: hominy casserole
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients except 1 cup shredded cheese.
Spoon into 2 1/2-quart lightly greased casserole. Sprinkle reserved cheese on top and bake approximately 30 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: eggplant dip
directions: Prick the eggplant several times; place on a plate and microwave, uncovered, on High for 6 minutes or until eggplant is tender and collapses.
Allow to cool in the refrigerator for 30 minutes.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Add sugar to beaten egg whites.
Roll crackers fine and fold into egg/sugar mixture.
Add nuts, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Put in ungreased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream on top.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix the sour cream, cream cheese and taco mix.
Spread into dinner plate.
Top with shredded cheese, onion and tomatoes. Serve with large, warmed tortilla chips.

title: buttercrunch candy("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook, stirring often, to hard crack stage (300° on candy thermometer). Remove from heat and stir in nuts.
Pour quickly into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread chocolate chips over top.
Let set.
Break into pieces.

title: meat casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except the cheese.
Put in a 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: gooey butter cookies
directions: Mix egg, oil, milk. Stir in dry cake mix.
Mix well.
Roll dough into balls.
Then roll in powdered sugar before placing on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: christmas date cookies
directions: Put first three ingredients
(dates, sugar and oleo) in boiler and cook until dates melt,
about
10 minutes on medium heat.
Add next three
ingredients (Rice Krispies, vanilla and pecans).
Mix well.
Let cool in
pan.
Make
small
balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter sandwich
directions: Spread peanut butter on one slice of bread.
Put butter on other slice of bread.
Put them together.

title: bimbom's sweet potatoes
directions: Drain all juice from sweet potatoes.
Mash potatoes well.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Heat at 350° until bubbling hot, 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: seafood bisque
directions: Blend soups, milk, cream, onion and celery in saucepan.
Add asparagus, shrimp and crab; heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Add wine last.
Serve with pat of butter floating on top.
Do not stir it in.

title: tropical fruit whisper
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Serve over ice. Yield:
1 quart.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and chill overnight.

title: scroodle noodles
directions: Cook
corkscrew
noodles as directed on package.
Drain and put
in
crock-pot.
Mix 1/2 stick margarine with noodles. Cook together
in small amount of water cauliflower, broccoli and mixed vegetables.
Drain and add to noodles.
Season with salt and pepper.
Melt
Velveeta cheese in milk and remaining margarine. Pour
over
noodles
and vegetables.
Keep well in the crock-pot on low.

title: white chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler, then beat in butter.
One by one, beat in egg yolks.
Whip the cream until stiff peaks form. Beat the egg whites until they form soft peaks.
While beating, sprinkle in sugar.
Scrape the chocolate down the side of the egg white bowl and delicately fold together.
When almost blended, fold in the whipped cream.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour in pie shell and bake for about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: best ever salad
directions: Peel tomatoes and cut into bite-size pieces.
Core peppers and cut into strips.
Place in a large bowl.
Grate onion on top. Sprinkle salt on top.
Cover and let stand for 15 minutes or longer.
To serve, sprinkle with the oil and toss.

title: nut butterballs
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
Mix in butter, vanilla and nuts, mixing well.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Roll half of the balls in nuts.
Place the plain balls and those rolled in nuts on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Roll plain cookies in powdered sugar.

title: white sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk, all at once.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir 1 to 2 minutes more. Makes 1 cup.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Beat egg yolks. Add 2 tablespoons milk. Stir in other ingredients in order listed. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick. Pour into baked deep-dish pie shell.

title: italian cookies
directions: Cream together butter, shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add flavoring and nuts.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add to first mixture.
Make into small rolls.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake until only slightly tan.
Cut up diagonally.
Toast just a little (approximately 5 minutes).

title: party meat balls
directions: To make meat balls blend
egg, onion soup mix, paprika, bread crumbs and meat.
In
saucepan,
heat
grape
jelly
and barbecue sauce on low heat
until
well
blended.
Cook
meat balls in oil, drain and add to sauce serve as appetizer.	Keep warm.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine crushed pretzels, sugar and margarine and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Set aside to cool.

title: stuffed syrian bread
directions: Early in the day, or night before, scramble sausage in skillet until nearly done.
Saute onion and green pepper in sausage drippings until tender.
Drain off all fat.
Mix onion, pepper and sausage together.

title: avocado layered dip
directions: Layer 1:
Mash avocados.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Flavor with garlic powder or salt (to taste).
Blend with mayonnaise.

title: gingerbread bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine gingerbread mix, butter and 1 egg.
Spread mixture evenly into 2 greased 8-inch square baking pans.
In a medium bowl, combine cream cheese, remaining 2 eggs and confectioners sugar.
Spread evenly over gingerbread layers.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until slightly browned.
Allow to cool completely in pans.
Cut 1 x 2-inch bars. Store in airtight container.
Yields about 2 dozen bars in each pan.

title: favorite brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Melt shortening. Mix with cocoa.
Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes or until brownies pull away from sides of pan.

title: poppy seed coffee cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs, evaporated milk and vanilla in large bowl. Mix dry ingredients (flour, baking powder, salt and poppy seeds) in separate bowl and add to liquid mixture. Pour into greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Allow to cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan. While still warm, brush with melted margarine and dust with powdered sugar. You can also drizzle with a mixture of powdered sugar and lemon juice to serve as a dessert cake.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine ingredients in medium-size mixing bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: boiled peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the margarine, sugar and cocoa.
Boil 2 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until smooth. Add oats.
Stir.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let stand about 30 minutes.

title: pimento cheese
directions: In large bowl, cream 2 cheeses together.
In another bowl, stir mayonnaise and sugar until smooth and creamy.	Add pimentos and cheese.
Blend well.
Yield 3 cups.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into four pieces.
Put sugar and cinnamon in bag.
Toss in biscuit pieces.
Coat them well.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bring to boil the sugar, syrup and butter/margarine.
Pour syrup over biscuits and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Mix white cake mix as directed.
Add creme de menthe to taste. Add green food coloring.
Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: instant cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice until smooth.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate until ready to serve, a minimum of 20 minutes.
When serving, top with pie filling, if desired.

title: herbed breadsticks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl combine parsley, onion, Italian seasoning and crushed red pepper flakes; set aside. Unroll 1 can of dough into 2 long rectangles.
Overlap long sides 1/2-inch, firmly press edges and perforations to seal.
Press seasoning mixture evenly over dough. On large sheet of waxed paper, shape remaining crescent roll dough as before into 14 x 8-inch rectangle.
Place on top of seasoned layer.
Firmly press together.
Cut crosswise into sixteen 8-inch strips.
Twist each strip and place on ungreased baking sheet, pressing ends into baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 18 minutes until light golden brown. Cool on baking sheet 5 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 16 breadsticks.

title: blender hollandaise sauce
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in blender on high speed.
Slowly add melted butter.
Sauce will keep at room temperature for an hour before serving.
Yields about 2 cups sauce.

title: cole slaw
directions: Place apples, cabbage and raisins in bowl.
Combine celery seed, vinegar, honey oil, salt and pepper.
Stir well to dissolve honey.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Toss well.
Makes 2 servings.

title: three-minute fudge
directions: Butter square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix milk, sugar and salt in 2-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts until melted.
Pour into pan.
Refrigerate until firm (at least 1 hour).
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares. Yields 3 dozen candies.

title: millet patties
directions: Blend onion, garlic and milk in blender until chunky.
Pour into mixing bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Place by spoonfuls on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam and flatten with a fork to form patties.
Brown in oven at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well. Add rest of ingredients and blend well.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: white mountain muffins
directions: Stir just until mixed.
Fill muffin tins at least half full. Bake at 400° until raised up and golden brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pecan chicken a la king
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter; cook celery until tender. Add bouillon cube; crush with back of spoon. Stir in flour, salt and poultry seasoning.
Add milk all at once.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles.

title: harvard beets
directions: Combine all ingredients, except beets, in saucepan.
Cook until smooth.
Pour over beets.
Heat.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Process sour cream, Parmesan cheese, scallions and garlic in a blender.
When fully mixed, add artichoke hearts, rinsed and drained.

title: sunday brunch
directions: Brown sausage and onion together; drain and cool.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt, cheese and mustard.
Fold in bread cubes and sausage.
Put generous amount of butter in 9 x 18 inch casserole dish.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 7 - 8 people.

title: quick breakfast casserole
directions: Place half of bread cubes in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put half of sausage on top, followed by half of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Beat eggs with milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over layers in pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Remove cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Place chicken and vegetables in baking dish.
Stir together soup, chicken broth and pepper.
Pour over chicken mixture and mix. Combine flour, milk and butter and stir until smooth.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned and vegetables are done.
Let cool 10 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tomato catsup
directions: Cook tomatoes, peppers and onions without adding water until soft.
Press mixture through a sieve.
Combine pulp, vinegar, sugar, salt and spices tied in a muslin bag and cook rapidly over full gas flame until thick, stirring to prevent burning (about 45 minutes).
Pour into hot sterilized containers and seal.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Boil cut up chicken in large container until done.
Remove chicken and debone.
Place onion, rice, tomatoes, and okra into broth and cook until done.
Add water as needed to keep container full.
Add salt and pepper.
When vegetables are cooked, add deboned chicken.
Serve with crackers or corn bread.
Delicious on a cold day!

title: apple turnovers
directions: Mix together flour, salt, baking powder and lard; add cold water to make a soft dough.
Divide into 6 sections and roll out. Place apples on dough.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle over apples.
Fold dough over and crimp edges.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: marinated salad
directions: Combine and shake together the oil, vinegar, lemon juice, mustard, chopped red onion, paprika, salt and pepper.
Pour over the sausage, broccoli, mushrooms and sliced onion; let marinate for 3 hours.
When ready to eat, pour the mixture over 2 quarts of assorted greens, torn in bite-size pieces.
Add Mozzarella cheese to top.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown ground meat and drain. Add onion, green pepper, and celery. Heat thoroughly. Add tomatoes, soup, spices and beans. Cook on medium heat for 1 hour.

title: hi ho dessert
directions: Mix egg whites, sugar and baking powder together.
Add crackers and walnuts.
Mix together.
Bake in a buttered pan at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat oil and eggs until frothy; add sugar gradually.
Add flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Fold in apples. Spoon into 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cornstarch.
Bring to a boil, then boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, then add vanilla.
Add fluff and peanut butter.
Mix well, then add walnuts.
Mix well. Put in small square pan (greased).
Chill in refrigerator for approximately 1 hour.
Cut into squares.

title: mom's potato pancakes
directions: Rinse potatoes in cold water; drain well.
Place in a large bowl.
Add egg, flour, onion, salt and pepper; mix well.
In a skillet, heat 1/4 of oil over medium heat.
Drop batter by 1/3 cupfuls into hot oil.
Flatten to form a pancake.
Fry until golden brown, turn and brown the other side.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mock beans
directions: Cut bacon in 3 or 4 pieces; mix with all other ingredients. Bake at 350° until they are as baked as you want them. Can fool people into thinking you started from scratch.

title: fudge
directions: Cook on low heat the sugar, cocoa and milk until ball forms in cold water.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Pour in buttered dish until set.
Cut and serve.

title: mexican stuffed shells
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain.
Combine picante sauce, water and tomato sauce.
Stir 1/2 c. sauce into ground beef along with the green chilies, 1/2 c. of cheese and half of the onions.
Mix well. Pour half of remaining sauce into a 8x12 baking dish.
Stuff the shells with ground beef mixture and arrange in dish.
Pour the remaining sauce over shells. Cover and bake at 350 for 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes uncovered.

title: bacon bit slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and cauliflower. Put in bowl. Cover with mayo. Set overnight.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash and dry the squash.
Cut in half lengthwise with a sharp knife.
(Hold onto it firmly.)
Remove the seeds and fibers.
Prick the flesh of the squash several places with a fork.
Place half the sugar, salt, butter and water in each.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cook onion in magarine until soft; stir in flour.
Mix bouillon with water to make 1 cup; add to flour mixture and cook. Stir until thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Combine everything except soup and water and shape into an oval patty about 1-inch thick.
Using a small amount of butter, brown on both sides in a skillet.
Combine soup and water and pour around meat.
Cook slowly in covered skillet for 25 minutes.
If desired, put boiled potatoes around meat.
Soup and meat juices will make the gravy without further thickening.

title: ellen's easy clam chowder
directions: Combine in crock pot and stir thoroughly to avoid lumps. Cook on low until your favorite serving temperature is reached.

title: zucchini cheese muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, bread crumbs, sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir in cheese.
In a medium bowl, combine eggs, evaporated milk and butter.
Stir in zucchini. Add zucchini mixture to flour mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned in a 400° oven.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: lemon berry pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar in a medium bowl with a wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in lemon peel and juice. Stir in 1 1/2 cups of whipped topping.
Spread evenly on bottom of crust.
Press strawberries into cream cheese layer, reserving several for garnish.

title: roy's chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients while milk is heating.
Moisten dry ingredients with 1/2 cup fresh milk and add to hot milk.
Cook until thickened. Beat eggs (separated if you want a meringue). Add a little hot mixture to eggs and mix well.
Pour into the rest of the hot mixture. Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue, if desired. Two recipes will fill 3 shallow pie shells.

title: cranberry-apple delight
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Rinse and pick cranberries.
Mix fruit with sugar and water and place in a 2-quart casserole.

title: strawberry pretzel delight(recipe served at club meetings)
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, 3 tablespoons sugar and melted margarine.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Crust will be very thin.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread 1 cup chopped pecans on bottom of a 9 inch x 13 inch pan.
On top of that, place 1 cup shredded coconut.
Mix German chocolate cake mix as directed on package and pour on top of coconut.
Melt margarine and cream cheese together.
Add 1 box of powdered sugar, and mix.
Pour on top of cake mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage until brown.
Drain and set aside.
Separate crescent rolls in 8 triangles.
Place triangles with elongated points toward center of greased pizza pan.
Press sides and bottom to form a crust.
Seal perforations.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes. Crust will be puffy when removed from the oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Spoon sausage over dough.
Sprinkle with cheeses. Combine eggs with milk and seasonings.
Pour over sausage.
Bake at 350° on lower rack for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
Use pizza pan with high rim around it.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all together, roll in foil and refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in a pan at a tilt, with one end of foil open so it can drain.
Take out of foil and bake 5 to 10 minutes more to dry.
Refrigerate and slice.

title: chocolate glob bars
directions: Mix together.
Place 1/2 of mixture in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Top with Caramel Mixture.
Pour on remaining cake mixture and bake 20 more minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease a 10-inch baking dish.
Cover bottom with layer of potatoes.
Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper.
Dot with butter. Repeat layers until all potatoes, flour and butter are used. Heat milk or cream and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until potatoes are tender when stuck with a fork. Serves 4.

title: tuna almond snack spread
directions: In a large bowl, sprinkle gelatin over cold water; let stand 1 minute. Add boiling water and stir until completely dissolved. With wire whip or rotary beater, blend in cream cheese until smooth. Stir in lemon juice, curry, salt and garlic powder. Fold in onions, pimento, tuna and 1/2 cup almonds. Turn into a 5 1/2-cup fish mold. Chill to firm.

title: sauerkraut dish(kolosvary kapusta)
directions: Stew pork and beef in 1 tablespoon butter and some paprika and 1 large onion, diced.
Stew 1/4 cup rice in 1 tablespoon butter, diced medium sized onion and enough water to cook rice.
Cook 2 cans sauerkraut in 1 tablespoon butter, 1 large sliced onion and enough water to keep kraut thick.
After kraut is cooked, sprinkle with a little flour and mix.
Into deep casserole, beginning with kraut mixture, put a layer of each of the three mixtures:
one layer of kraut, then layer of meat and layer of rice.
Do this until casserole is filled.
Pour one pint of sour cream on top and spread.
Bake in moderate 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: beef or pork tenderloin with herbs
directions: Mix
first
ingredients.
Cut
1/2-inch deep pockets into roast.
Mix
oils; pour over roast.
Cook, basting every 20 minutes.
Cook 1 hour.
Add 1/2 cup wine.
Cook 20 minutes, then add
another
1/2 cup wine.
Tent with foil to keep warm. Add 1/2 cup more wine to pan drippings and brown until thickened.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice up peeled apples in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix ingredients and sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: one dish meal - pot roast
directions: Sprinkle salt, pepper and garlic powder on meat.
Heat oil in Dutch oven.
Brown meat in oil.
Add onions.
Continue to brown. Add water and tomatoes.
Cover and cook on low heat for 2 1/2 hours.
Add carrots, peppers and potatoes.
Cook 30 minutes longer.
Season to taste.
Serves a family of 8.

title: strawberry-applesauce congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello and cinnamon hearts in boiling water; cool. Add applesauce.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture into oblong dish.
Let chill until set.
Beat cream cheese (room temperature) with a little added pineapple juice until smooth.
Add pineapple, pecans and celery.
Spread over cooled jello, then pour remaining jello mixture on top.
Chill until set.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Combine steak sauce, oil, sugar and seasonings in bowl, mixing well.
Add pork chops.
Marinate, covered, overnight, turning pork chops several times.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Grill over hot coals until tender, basting frequently with remaining marinade.
Also can cook these in oven. Yields 12 servings.

title: cranberry molded salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple, etc.
Pour into mold greased with mayonnaise.

title: enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in tomato paste, seasoning and water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peeled tomatoes.
Place 1 tablespoon meat filling and some cheese on each tortilla.
Roll up tightly and place, seam side down, in a greased cake pan.
Top with remaining sauce. Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: daffodil chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Combine egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, lemon juice and rind. Blend well.
Cook over boiling water until thick and foamy, beating constantly, with rotary beater (about 3 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin mixture. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Add remaining 1/4 cup sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating after each addition, until stiff.
Fold carefully into gelatin mixture until well blended.
Pile lightly into shell. Chill several hours or until filling is set.
Spread with whipped cream and garnish with lemon rind, if desired.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour half of batter into prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Melt caramels with butter and milk; pour over cake.
Sprinkle pecans and chocolate chips over caramel layer.
Cover with rest of batter and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer at 350°.
Can serve with whipped cream.

title: coconut pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks and add to flour, sugar and milk.
Cook on stove until real thick, then add coconut and vanilla.
Pour in pie crust.
Beat egg whites and pour on top of pie.
Put a little coconut on top of meringue.
Bake at 325° until meringue is brown.

title: texas sheet cake brownies
directions: Put margarine in a saucepan; bring to boil.
Then add cocoa and milk.
Remove from heat and add sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Beat well and spread on cake while hot.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add last 4 ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: onion burgers
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Shape into 8 large patties.
Grill or broil until done.
Serve on well browned buns, with vegetable garnish, as desired.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons juice.
Mix flour, sugar and reserved juice.
Add pineapple and cheese.
Mix cracker crumbs and margarine; spoon over pineapple.
Bake in greased casserole at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in large baking dish or pan. Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk. Pour into melted margarine and stir lightly. Add fruit on top of batter (no need to stir). Tart and/or fresh fruit will need extra sugar and may need to be precooked a little while. Bake at 350° until done, about 45 minutes.

title: fudgy chocolate cake(yield: 10 servings)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Set aside.
Beat eggs and egg white in a large bowl at medium speed of an electric mixer until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until thick and pale (about 5 minutes).
With mixer running, slowly add melted margarine.
Add 1/2 cup preserves, beating just until mixture is smooth.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift flour mixture over egg mixture; fold in gently.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Rub surface of meat with salt and pepper and place in large bowl.
Heat vinegar, water, onion, bay leaves, peppercorns and sugar together until very hot, but not boiling.
Pour hot mixture over meat.
Cover bowl and let stand in refrigerator for approximately 3 days, turning each day.

title: blackberry jello salad
directions: Stir together and chill until firm.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Arrange chicken in shallow baking dish.
Cover with mushrooms. Combine soup, sherry and sour cream.
Blend well.
Pour over chicken, covering it.
Dust with paprika.
Bake at 350° for
1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix canned fruit and vanilla pudding.
Stir in cut up banana. Chill before serving.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix.
Let stand 30 minutes in refrigerator.

title: cheese ring
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in mold or log roll.
Serve with crackers of your choice.
Put strawberry preserves on top.

title: laban (yogurt)
directions: Rinse kettle out with cold water.
(This will make it easier to clean later.)
Pour in the milk, bring to a boil until bubbles form on top.
Watch so milk doesn't scorch.
Let milk sit until it is cold.
At night time, put back on stove and let the milk get barely lukewarm.
Take container of yogurt; mix it with some of the milk, then mix well with rest.
Put a lid on the kettle, cover with a warm blanket, and set it in the oven.
In the morning, put the kettle in refrigerator with a clean cloth on top of the Laban. This will absorb the whey.
Wring out and put back until it is the consistency you want it.
Put in containers in refrigerator. Makes 4 cups.

title: chicken loaf pate
directions: Mix all together.
Put in loaf pan that has been lined with Saran Wrap.
Chill.
Unmold and decorate with green onions and parsley.
Serve with crackers for hors d'oeuvres.
Serve on lettuce for luncheon or as a sandwich.

title: sweet dip(for fruit)
directions: Cook the ingredients except Cool Whip until thickens (about 5 minutes).
Let cool and add 1 medium carton of Cool Whip. This keeps real good.

title: baked white fish
directions: Place fish in a greased baking dish.
Spread undiluted soup over fish.
Sprinkle pimento over soup and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes (depending on thickness of fish).

title: green sweet chunk pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Soak in salt and water for 3 days.
Drain. Cover with water.
Add alum and scald.
Let stand 1/2 day.
Drain. Cover with water.
Add ginger.
Scald; let stand 1/2 hour. Drain.
Boil vinegar, water and sugar.
In a bag (cheesecloth) put cinnamon, cloves and celery seed.
Add to water mix.
Add food color.
Boil and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand.
Repeat 3 days and then can.

title: cream of chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except for sharp cheese and corn shells.
Take 1/2 cup of mixture, spread on bottom of casserole dish.
Warm up corn shells until soft.
Take one shell at a time in hand, put a scoop of mixture in the middle. Sprinkle on sharp cheese.
Roll up; place face down in dish.
When dish is full, put remaining mixture over the top and sides.
If you find the mixture thick, add more milk.
You need at least 2 1/2 to 3 cups for the top.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix and beat lightly.
Dip onion rings in batter and fry in a deep fryer.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Follow directions on Bisquick box for biscuit dough.
Roll thinner than for biscuits; cut in strips.
Add just enough water to berries to be seen, but not covered in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Mix sugar and flour together, then slowly sprinkle into boiling berries, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Take off heat and add spices, vanilla and butter.

title: caramel popcorn or cracker jacks
directions: Separate large muscles in upper part of hind legs, can use some around scapula if large.
Freeze.
When ready to make jerky, half thaw so it's easy to cut thin strips, cut with grain 1/8 to 1/4 inch thick.

title: el-dorado beef casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain fat.
Add onion, garlic, salt and tomato sauce.
Combine sour cream, cottage cheese and chilies.
Crush tortilla chips in bottom of well-greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Add half of meat mixture, 1/2 sour cream, 1/2 olives and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: jimmy's fried fish
directions: Put fish fillets in a bowl and add mustard.
Stir fish around with your hand until mustard is evenly dispensed.
Add cayenne pepper, Tony's and black pepper to 2 1/2 cups of corn meal mix. Mix ingredients until evenly dispensed.
Put meal in a Ziploc bag and add 5 fillets at a time.
Shake bag until fillets are covered with meal.
Drop fillets into grease that is preheated to 325°. Let cool until they float and are golden brown.

title: pizza crust
directions: Put yeast in a bowl big enough to mix dough.
Add warm water to yeast and let stand a few minutes.
Add Bisquick and mix like bread dough.
When it forms a ball, spread it on an oiled pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Let stand a few minutes.
Add your pizza sauce and toppings as desired (cheese, pepperoni, etc.).
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: praline chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in 1-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Cool slightly.
Beat together egg yolks and praline powder for 3 to 4 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Add chocolate mixture and blend thoroughly.
Add salt to egg whites.
Beat until peaks form.
Stir in whipped cream.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour. Spoon into meringue shells.
Garnish with chocolate leaves or curls, as desired.
Makes 2 servings.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Pour pie filling into pie shells and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar, eggs
and vanilla with electric mixer until fairly smooth.
Pour over blueberries and bake at 350° until brown.

title: festive party punch
directions: Mix juices in a large glass, porcelain or stainless steel container.
Add strawberries.
Pour in ginger ale.

title: taco bake
directions: In skillet brown 1 pound hamburger.
Cook jumbo shells in water until tender, then toss with the melted butter.
Stir in the cream cheese in browned hamburger and 1 teaspoon chili powder. Then add salt.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel brownies
directions: Melt milk and candy together.
Pour half of cake batter in cake pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350°.
Pour caramel on top.
Pour chocolate chips on candy and rest of batter; bake for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, soup, rice and 1/2 cheese.
Place in greased casserole.
Top with remaining cheese and crumbled crackers.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: ice creamdiagonal, iowa
directions: Mix all ingredients together except milk.

title: cinnamon and sugar toast
directions: Toast the bread.
Take a spoon and put the cinnamon and sugar on the toast.

title: chocolate banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat. Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add with banana mixture. Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Can also make muffins.

title: *peanut brittle
directions: Cook peanuts, sugar and corn syrup until peanuts pop, stirring.
Add soda and pour in greased pan.
Cool and break apart to serve.

title: sour cream enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, chopped green onions, chilies, 1 to 1 1/2 cups of Longhorn cheese and hamburger.
Set aside.

title: jambalaya(one skillet supper)
directions: Heat oil in a medium skillet over medium heat.
Add green peppers, onion and ham.
Saute until ham is browned and vegetables are softened.

title: spinach pie
directions: Melt 2 sticks of butter.
Cook spinach and onions; boil eggs. Mix flour and cheese all together and cool.
Put 7 pieces of the dough in bottom of 10 x 13-inch pan and brush each layer with butter.
Put the mixture in and fold the corners over.
Cut in squares and put 7 layers on top.
Brush each with butter.
Work fast with dough.
Bake for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: quick chocolate icing
directions: Bring sugar, cocoa and milk to boil for 1 minute in saucepan. Remove from heat; add stick of oleo and vanilla.
Set to cool. Beat until just beginning to get thick.
Pour over cake.
This old recipe is good to pour over sheet cake.
(Add chopped pecans, if desired.)

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Mix together dates, pecans, cherries, coconut and flour.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.

title: one-dish chicken bake
directions: Mix soup and sour cream.
Mix Stovetop and 1 2/3 C water.
Place chicken in 13 X 9-inch dish.
Pour soup and sour cream mixture over chicken.
Top with stuffing.
Bake 375° for 35 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.

title: date pudding
directions: Cook and boil up (stirring a lot).
Pour in 13 x 9 cake pan.

title: walnut butterscotch cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg together well.
Sift flour with soda, salt and spices.
Blend into creamed mixture alternately with applesauce.
Stir in walnuts.
Turn into greased 9 inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, just until cake tests done.
Remove from oven and spread with butterscotch topping at once.

title: double layer pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Add eggs; mix until blended. In separate bowl, mix pumpkin and spices. Stir 1 cup of the cream cheese batter into pumpkin mixture.

title: fabulous rice salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Set aside and prepare the remaining ingredients in a separate bowl.
Add this mixture to rice mixture and toss lightly with a fork.
Chill thoroughly. Yields 6 servings.

title: cream puffs
directions: Combine butter and water; cook until it comes to a rolling boil.
Add cup of flour; keep stirring until it forms a rolling ball.
Remove from heat; stir in the eggs.
Mix until smooth.
Heat oven to 400°.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet, about 1 inch apart.
Use about 1 tablespoon of mixture for each cream puff.
Yields 12 to 14 cream puffs.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need an 8-inch flower pot and trowel (new).
Crush the Oreos.
Mix cream cheese and butter.
Add powdered sugar.
In another bowl, mix pudding with the milk.
Fold in Cool Whip, then add to cream cheese mixture.
Start layering in the pot beginning with the Oreos and ending up with Oreos.
Put in worms along the way and top with worms and flowers.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Mix melted oleo, sugar, Karo and salt. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes, without stirring. Remove from heat. Add vanilla and soda. Pour over corn. Bake at 250° for 1 hour and stir every 15 minutes.

title: strawberry jello dessert
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups hot water; add strawberries.
Let jell.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Half cake and break into small pieces.
In a punch bowl, layer as listed using half of each ingredient.
Repeat layers. Refrigerate.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: In large skillet, saute onion until limp, drain and put aside. Brown meat, separated with spatula.
Return meat and onion to skillet.
Stir soup and milk.
Add to meat with enchilada sauce and green chilies

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and cube.
Put a layer of chicken, onions, Doritos and cheese in casserole dish.
Mix soups, tomatoes and broth together.
Pour over chicken.
Top with cheese and Doritos. Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Use a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Line bottom of pan with cinnamon crackers.
Add 1/2 pudding mix, layer of crackers and rest of pudding.
Add top layer of crackers.
Chill 2 hours before frosting.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 1 large or 2 small loaves.

title: mexican meat with cornbread topping
directions: Cook meat until brown; drain.
Add rice, spaghetti sauce, salt, chili powder, onions and peppers; mix well.
Cook until heated.
Put mixture into baking dish or pan; top with cornbread mixture.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until cornbread topping is done.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Sift together flour, 1 cup sugar and baking powder.
Add egg and stir.
Heat peaches in
glass dish with the juice and 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour flour mixture over peaches.
Melt butter and pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until top is brown.

title: cream of asparagus soup
directions: Cook asparagus in 1 cup of chicken broth until veggie is tender-crisp.
Drain; reserve liquid.
Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Stir in flour, seasonings and cheese; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly for 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk, 1 cup of water, reserved liquid and bouillon.
Cook, stirring with wire whisk, until mixture thickens.
Stir in asparagus.
Heat through and serve.

title: allison's sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together the sweet potatoes, sugar, milk, vanilla, eggs and melted butter.
Put into Pyrex baking dish.
Top with topping of brown sugar, flour, pecans and butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peaches and cream cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions, using a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Cool cake and split horizontally.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat over low heat until blended.
Do not boil.
Does not have to be refrigerated.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine, water and cocoa to a boil.
Remove from heat and add sugar, flour, sour cream and eggs.
Thoroughly mix ingredients in saucepan and pour into greased cookie sheet (11 x 17 x 3/4-inch) with sides.
Bake at 375° for 22 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix everything together and cook.
You can cook on top of the stove with LOW HEAT and stir often.
Or you can place in oven at 300 degrees and stir about every 1/2 hour.
Cook beans until you have the thickness you desire.
(I cook them about 2 - 2 1/2 hours, we like them thick.)

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt 4 times.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add flour alternately with 1 cup buttermilk.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Stir all ingredients in baking crock, stirring several times as it bakes in a 325° oven for 1 hour or longer.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onion and green peppers in a small amount of margarine until soft, but not brown.
Add green beans, tomatoes, red pepper, salt and pepper to taste.

title: mint surprise cookies
directions: Blend sugar and salad oil. Add eggs and vanilla. Sift and add remaining ingredients; chill.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, beat well; add eggs and beat. Sift dry ingredients and add to cream mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Batter will be real stiff.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
When cool, spread with topping.

title: cream of spinach soup
directions: Wash and steam spinach until soft.
Make a roux of butter and flour.
Cook onion in it until soft.
Add chicken stock and spinach.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.
Blend in blender until smooth.
Season to taste.
Add cream just before serving.
Check seasonings and serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; shape into balls about walnut size.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin together in double boiler.
With toothpick stuck in ball, dip in chocolate to coat. Cool on waxed paper.

title: cheesecake dreams
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square baking pan.
Mix brown sugar, flour, pecans and melted butter well in small bowl. Reserve 1/3 cup of this crumb mixture and pat remaining mixture in bottom of pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
In small bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour over crust and sprinkle on remaining crumbs.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 2-inch squares. Refrigerate.

title: sweet spiced nuts
directions: Beat egg white and water in a large bowl with a fork; add walnuts.
Toss to coat.
In small bowl combine sugar, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and allspice.
Sprinkle sugar mixture over walnuts. Toss to coat.
Spread nuts in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 20 minutes.
Transfer to wax paper to cool.
Break into clumps.
Great at Christmas!

title: sukiyaki
directions: Brown meat in salad oil.
Add vegetables, beef broth and soy sauce.
Cover; cook over low heat for 10 minutes or until vegetables are just tender.
Stir often.
Combine water and cornstarch.
Add to meat mixture.
Stir until thickened.
Serve over hot rice.

title: raisin bread
directions: Heat milk to warm.
Add shortening, sugar and salt.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water and add to mixture when it is cooled to 125°.
Add 2 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Cover and let rise for 1 hour.
Add raisins and nuts and enough flour to make firm dough.
Knead thoroughly and shape into loaf.
Place in greased loaf pan and let rise until doubled.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and oil.
Add squash and remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans and divide evenly into pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done (pan size, 9 x 5 x 3-inch or three 7 7/8 x 3 7/8 x 2 1/2-inches).

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add half of the flour with milk to batter.
Roll nuts, candy and dates in remaining flour; add to batter with coconut.
Bake in tube pan 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Beat eggs and add to mayonnaise, onion, grated cheese and soup.
Add broccoli.
Mix together. Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes (Ritz crackers, 4 sticks to a box, I use 1 stick).

title: butterfly cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until blended, light and fluffy; reduce speed to low. Add flour, milk, cornstarch, oil, baking powder, salt, vanilla and eggs; beat until mixed. Increase speed to high; beat 2 minutes. Spoon batter into 3 (9-inch) pans (greased). Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Frost with Lemon Buttercream Frosting.

title: low country boil(may prepare ahead.  serves 4.)
directions: Place corned beef in Dutch oven; barely cover with hot water. Add onion, garlic, cloves and bay leaves.
Simmer, covered, but do not boil, one hour per pound or until fork tender.
Remove meat from liquid; add potatoes and carrots.
Cover and bring to a boil; cook 10 minutes.
Add cabbage wedges; cook 20 minutes longer or until vegetables are done.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Brown onion and turkey.
Add rice and soups.
Put in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cook, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Sprinkle top with grated cheese, if desired.

title: french toast
directions: Put egg, milk and cinnamon in a bowl and mix well. Dip bread in the mixture, be sure both sides are covered.
Fry on medium, lightly greased pan until golden brown.
Serve with butter and syrup.
Serves 1.

title: salmon stew
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in 2 cups of water until tender.
Add butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Add salmon and bring to a boil. Add milk; heat until warm.
Don't boil.
Serve with saltine crackers.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onion flakes and pepper, spaghetti mix, tomato sauce and water.
Stir and simmer for 10 minutes with lid on.
In large mixing bowl, mix Mozzarella cheese (save a little for the top), the 16 ounces cottage cheese and lots of parsley or parsley flakes.
Boil lasagna noodles in large pan with 2 tablespoons oil.
They are easier to handle broken in half.
Place in pan in this order:
meat sauce, noodles, meat sauce, cheese mixture, noodles, meat sauce, cheese mixture and sprinkle of Parmesan cheese (if desired).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine melted butter, flour, milk and salt.
Mix up.
Arrange alternate layers of potatoes and sauce in greased casserole dish. Cover with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour baked corn
directions: Spray 9 x 9 baking dish with Pam spray.
Mix corn and sour cream in pan.
Spread even.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: italian sponge cake
directions: Whip the eggs with sugar and salt for about 7 to 10 minutes. Start at slow speed then increase to high speed until it forms a ribbon.
(Run your finger across the top, if the line remains its ready.)
Fold in the dry ingredients in 2 to 3 parts.
Slowly folding ingredients in, so that there are no lumps, making sure the flour is incorporated totally.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chicken and pasta
directions: Toss cooked pasta in mixture.
Place cooked chicken breast on top.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese (1 tablespoon per serving).
Serve with a butter lettuce salad.
Serves 2.

title: poppy seed salad dressing(for spinach salad)
directions: Combine in a small bowl. Mix until well blended. Can cover and refrigerate for up to 2 weeks.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Heat soup in a bowl for 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir often.
Cut cream cheese into cubes and stir cheese into the hot soup.
Heat 2 minutes, stirring often.
Mix with electric mixer until smooth. Place in plastic container with a tight fitting lid.
Place in refrigerator to cool.
Serve with potato chips.

title: bean-meat casserole
directions: Saute onions in oil.
Add hamburger and brown.
Drain and add kidney beans and pork and beans.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Bring to rolling boil sugar, butter and milk for 1 minute. Then, stir in the chocolate pieces and vanilla.

title: cookie cutter sugar cookie
directions: Cream powdered sugar, margarine and egg, then add vanilla and almond extract.
Sift flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Mix together and chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until golden.
Cool and frost.
The thicker you roll, the softer the cookie.
I make 1-inch balls and flatten with glass dipped in sugar.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Make dough:
Mix together the shortening, flour and milk. Dough will leave sides of bowl.
Roll dough into rectangles about 1/4-inch thick.
Spread sausage to almost edge of dough.
Roll up like jelly roll, starting at long edge.
Slice about 1/2-inch thick.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes 25 to 30.
Freezes well.

title: golden nugget budget soup
directions: Combine vegetables and margarine in soup kettle; add water to cover.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer until vegetables are tender.
Stir in seasonings, soup and milk; heat through gently. Yield:
4 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix very well.
Serve with sliced apples, pears, bananas, etc. Keep refrigerated.

title: golden gate punch
directions: Combine sugar and water; heat to boiling. Cool. Combine fruit juices. Add cooled sugar syrup and chill. Just before serving, add ginger ale and colored ice cubes. To make ice cubes, blend food coloring with water before freezing. Yield: 5 qt.

title: caramels
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and salt in 3-quart pan. Cook over medium heat until syrup is thick (245°). Add butter and stir until melted. Add milk very gradually so mixture does not stop boiling. Cook, stirring constantly, until thermometer is (242°). Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour at once in a greased pan. Cool, then cut in squares.

title: cheese casserole
directions: Cut cheese and butter into small cubes.
Combine with all other ingredients.
Bake in a greased, 2-quart baking dish at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Let set about 5 minutes and cut into squares.

title: pink salad
directions: Heat pineapple and sugar in saucepan.
Add Jell-O and cream cheese.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool completely.
Put can of evaporated milk in refrigerator several days before.
Beat stiff. Fold in mixture.
Put in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Place in freezer.

title: frozen banana pops
directions: Melt chips.
Stir in peanut butter.
Insert wooden sticks into cut end of each banana.
Dip and roll into peanut butter mixture. Sprinkle with nuts.
Stand upright in fridge until coating is set. Cover and freeze until firm.
Makes 12 pops.

title: lasagna
directions: Layer 1/2 of cooked noodles in a well-greased 9 x 13 pan. Combine cheese, sour cream, onion and green pepper; spread over noodles.
Top mixture with other half of noodles.
Drizzle noodles with melted butter.
Mix tomato sauce with ground beef and spread over noodles.
Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lazy chicken devine
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch cubes- it works easier if chicken is still partially frozen.
Put into 9x13-inch pan.
Add broccoli.
In bowl combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry together. Pour over the chicken and mix together.
Sprinkle top with cheese. Combine breadcrumbs and melted butter (I throw the butter and bread crumbs together in the microwave for about 10-15 seconds) and sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 min.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and roll into small balls.
Chill. In double boiler place chocolate chips and paraffin.
Melt.
With toothpick dip balls into mixture, leaving small area free of chocolate covering.
These look like real buckeyes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Do not
drain the pineapple.
Just mix all together and enjoy.

title: golfer's stew
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Place all ingredients in large casserole and cover.
Bake for 3 hours.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: pauline's egg custard
directions: Start with 4 eggs, beaten well, then continue adding all ingredients one at a time.
Pour into a Pyrex pie plate.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients and mix 1 small jar salad dressing and 2 tablespoons sugar together.
Pour over top, then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and Bac*Os.
Let set for 2 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: oatmeal carmelitas
directions: Melt caramels and milk; cool.
Combine remaining ingredients, except chips and nuts.
Press 1/2 mixture in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle chips and nuts and then spread melted caramels over chips and nuts.
Add rest of mixture. Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Chill 1 to 2 hours before cutting. Very rich so cut pieces small.

title: chocolate salad dressing cake
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Add flour.
Add soda to hot water.
Put salad dressing and vanilla in last.
This is very good.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and whip lightly.
Add cranberry sauce; mix well until smooth.
Add sugar; mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 9 x 11 x 2-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 375° until firm.
Remove and serve either hot or cold.

title: buttermilk waffles
directions: Beat egg whites; set aside.
Beat yolks and buttermilk together.
Add dry ingredients and oil.
Fold in beaten egg whites.

title: cranberry ice
directions: Drop cleaned cranberries into boiling water.
When berries pop, remove from heat and press through sieve.

title: brandy slush
directions: Boil tea bags in 2 cups water until real strong. Add tea to sugar and boiling water.
Cool.
Add juices and brandy.
Mix and freeze.

title: russian tea
directions: In one pot, bring to boil 2 quarts of water.
Add whole cloves and let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
In another pot, bring 1 quart water to boil.
Add tea bags; let stand 5 minutes.
Add sugar or substitute.
In a gallon container, put orange juice, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Add cinnamon sticks.
Strain clove water into gallon container and stir.
Heat to just boiling to serve.

title: molasses baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Combine all ingredients except bacon and mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with bacon.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: sweet and sour greens
directions: Cut cabbage or greens into approximately 1 1/2-inch squares. Combine water, sugar, vinegar, soy sauce and cornstarch and blend well.
Set aside.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine, shortening and sugar. Add eggs. Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Combine to mixture alternately with milk and vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cran-orange punch(diabetic)
directions: Combine cranberry juice, orange concentrate and sugar substitute in a large bowl.
Stir well and chill.
Add soda to fruit juice mixture just before serving.
Serve over crushed ice.

title: weight watchers cranberry salad
directions: Mix and set aside 1 large diet strawberry gelatin and 1/2 cup boiling water.
Chop in blender 2 cups cranberries and 1 small apple.
Add gelatin to fruit and mix 1 can crushed pineapple in own juice, 1 banana (chopped) and 1/2 cup orange juice.
Serves 8. Counts as 1 fruit and 8 optional calories.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, vanilla and sugar together.
Add zucchini and all other ingredients and mix well.
Bake for 1 hour in greased and floured pans (2 to 3 pans depending on size of pan).
Bake at 350°.

title: fun-to-make carrot bread
directions: In a large bowl, mash the margarine with the back of a fork. Beat in the honey and the egg.
Beat in the banana, mashing it with the back of a fork.
Stir in the yogurt and vanilla.
In a medium size bowl, combine the flours, baking soda, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Pour the flour mixture into the large bowl and combine with the egg-banana mixture.
Add the carrots and raisins. Knead the mixture together with your hands.
Pour the batter into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: in season fruit pops
directions: Blend fresh fruit in blender.
Add apple juice, lemon juice and sugar.
Pour into disposable cups and stick popsicle stick in juice.
Leave in freezer for 5 to 8 hours.

title: crab soup
directions: Saute onion and zest in butter.
Add flour; heat and stir until bubbly, adding half and half gradually.
Mix in crabmeat and simmer about 1/2 hour.
Add remaining ingredients, except egg yolks and simmer for another 15 minutes.

title: orange shake
directions: In a blender, combine the milk and orange Jell-O; blend for about 30 seconds or until Jell-O is dissolved.
Spoon in yogurt and ice cream.
Blend for about 1 minute or just until mixed. Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well, except the margarine and Ritz crackers.
Pour into a large baking dish or two small ones.
Top with the Ritz crackers or saltines and 1 stick margarine.
Crush crackers and melt margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butter horn rolls
directions: Put sugar and butter in milk.
Mix water and yeast and add to milk mixture.
Add eggs, add flour and mix well.
Divide into 6 pieces (or more if wanted).
Roll out and cut into wedges.
Spread with nut mixture.
Roll up and twist into semi-circle.
Brush with egg and milk mixture.
Bake on greased tins at
375° for 10-12 minutes.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in layers, then broccoli and sauce.
Top with croutons if desired.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and drain well.
Put spinach between two paper towels and squeeze to remove as much moisture as possible.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients in large bowl.
Make a well.
Add all other ingredients and mix until smooth.
Place in two 9 1/2 x 5-inch bread pans (well greased).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple delight
directions: Roll out single biscuits and fill with apple. Add 1/2 teaspoon sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon on each. (Place in a deep buttered pan.)
In a separate pot, mix margarine, 1 cup sugar, water, 1/8 teaspoon nutmeg and cinnamon. Let boil 1 minute. Pour over biscuits and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: orange beets
directions: Peel and section oranges; set aside.
In small saucepan, bring orange juice to a boil.
Stir the 2 tablespoons water and cornstarch until dissolved.
Stir into boiling orange juice. Reduce heat to medium-low; cook until thickens and boils.
Stir in oranges and nutmeg.
Keep warm until ready to serve.
Pour orange sauce over beets and arrange the oranges.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift and measure flour.
Add baking powder, soda and salt and sift again.
Cream the oleo; add sugar slowly.
Continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and mix until smooth.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with mashed bananas.
Turn into ungreased loaf pan, about 9 x 5-inch.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This will make 3 (1/2 loaf) pans.

title: lasagna mexicana
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet.
Drain fat.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato sauce, beans and chilies.
Layer half of tortillas on bottom of 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Spread half of meat mixture over tortillas and sprinkle with half of cheese. Repeat layers.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients except ground beef in pot and simmer. Cook ground beef and onion in frying pan until done.
Drain and add to simmering mixture.
Simmer about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: cinnamon pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Pour over syrup.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: cake brownies(low-fat)
directions: Spray a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with nonstick coating.
Set aside.
In a medium saucepan melt the margarine.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in the sugar and cocoa until combined.
Add egg white and vanilla to saucepan.
Using a wooden spoon lightly beat just until combined.
Add flour, milk, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat with the spoon until combined.
Stir in walnuts or pecans.
Spread the batter into the prepared baking pan.
