Bake at 350° for 16 to 18 minutes.
After cooled, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Drizzle with chocolate icing.
Cut into bars.

title: turkey roll
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Put in freezer-let set.
Mold into a roll and cover with chopped pecans.

title: layered tex mex dip
directions: Layer listed items in square 8-inch or 9-inch dish.
Serve with Tostitos chips.

title: chocolate mint sugar cookie drops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine 1 cup sugar and vegetable oil; mix well.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Shape into balls; roll in remaining sugar or use colored sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Makes approximately 5 1/2 dozen.

title: calico bean hot dish
directions: Brown together bacon, hamburger and chopped onion.
Add rest of ingredients and heat thoroughly.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix the vinegar, sugar, boiling water and oil. Bring to a boil, but don't boil it.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand, covered, overnight. Drain.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan, crushed pineapple, pie filling on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of cherries. Pour melted butter on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Drain pineapple, but use juice from thawed strawberries. Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Combine all ingredients.
Chill until set.

title: chicken pie
directions: Prepare baking hen.
Cook until tender.
Remove bones, skin and fat.
Cut into pieces.
Add together with good portion of broth. Bring to boil, adding salt and pepper, if desired.
To this, add a paste made with water and flour until possibly half as a boiled custard would be.
Remove from fire.
With about 3 pints of plain flour, add salt to taste, enough Crisco to make short, soft dough. Mix with water.
Grease 9-inch pan.
Roll bottom crust to medium thick.
Line pans and dip 3 regular serving ladles into each crust. Add top crust.
Have prepared a mixture of plain flour, salt and pepper to taste, with enough Crisco that it will crumble but still will stick together in the hand.
Crumble over pies and bake about 425° for 20 minutes or desired brownness.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Pat ground meat on bottom of pan (use a 9 x 13-inch pan for 2 pounds; smaller pan for less meat).
Cover meat with cheese slices.
Mix cream of chicken soup with water and pour over cheese. Arrange Tater Tots on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, depending on pan size.

title: easy potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and slice potatoes thinly.
Slice onion thinly.
In casserole dish, line bottom with potatoes. Sprinkle with a few sliced onions on top.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over.
Add 2 thin slices of butter.
Repeat layer.
In bowl, combine soup and milk.
Mix well and pour on top of potatoes. Cook, uncovered, 30 to 45 minutes or until a slight coating covers potatoes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: green punch
directions: Mix.
Just before serving, add lime to float on top.

title: sauce for green beans
directions: Mix and heat for a few minutes.
Pour over a quart of green beans.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a greased casserole dish and bake at 250° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: tex mex
directions: Mash avocados.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Assemble in layers the refried beans, avocado mix, sour cream mix, onions, tomatoes and olives.
Top with cheese.

title: banana pudding
directions: Line dish with vanilla wafers.
Add pudding mix to milk.
Beat with mixer for 1 minute or until smooth.
Stir in vanilla, then bananas.
Fold in the whipped cream.
Spoon over wafers and chill for at least 4 hours.

title: reduced calorie peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine with sugars; stir in egg, peanut butter and vanilla.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to margarine mixture and beat.
Make dough into 1-inch balls and place on cookie sheet that has been lightly coated with cooking spray. Flatten each ball with a fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Cool cookies for 2 minutes before removing from sheet.
Makes 3 dozen cookies, 72 calories per cookie.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain crushed pineapple and take pineapple juice and mix with instant pudding.
Drain fruit cocktail and add fruit and pineapple to pudding mixture. Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Chill.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: For crust, cook spaghetti noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Combine 1 egg, Parmesan cheese and margarine. Stir in hot noodles.
Press mixture evenly into bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Drain cottage cheese; combine with 1 egg.
Spread over crust.
Set aside.

title: cool whip frosting
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar and milk in a small bowl.
Beat at lowest speed about 1 minute.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread at once.
Refrigerate cake.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix by box directions.
Pour 3/4 of mix into oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake for 15 minutes.
Mix caramels with evaporated milk and melt.
Pour that on top of cake, then place chocolate chips on top.
Place nuts over chocolate.
Pour rest of cake mix on top.
Bake until done (remaining time according to the box directions).
The toothpick test does not work for doneness on this cake.

title: pound cake gingerbread
directions: Bring butter and eggs to room temperature.
Meanwhile, soak light raisins in boiling water 5 minutes; drain and set aside. Combine flour, baking powder and cream of tartar.
Beat butter in a mixer bowl with an electric mixer on medium speed 30 seconds. Gradually add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating on medium to high speed about 6 minutes total.
Add molasses.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each addition, scraping bowl often. Gradually add flour mixture to butter mixture, beating on low speed just until combined.
Fold in ginger and raisins.
Pour batter in a greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Bake in a 325° oven 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly on wire rack.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Combine granulated sugar and cinnamon in a bag.
Add dough quarters; shake until coated. Place pieces in greased tube pan.
Bring brown sugar and butter to boil; boil for 1 minute.
Pour over arranged biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Turn out onto a large plate.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash and soak red beans. Drain. Saute all other ingredients. Cover beans with water in a large pot.
Add other ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer for 1 hour.
Make sure that beans are tender.
Serve over rice.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mini fruitcakes
directions: Coat two mini-fluted cupcake or muffin pans (12 indentations each pan, each indentation 2 1/2-inches in diameter) with cooking spray.
Lightly dust with flour.
Combine cherries and 1/2 cup orange juice in a bowl for 1 hour, toss occasionally.

title: vegetables tossed in olive butter
directions: Place potatoes in a steaming rack in a large Dutch oven.
Add water to depth of 1-inch.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and steam 5 minutes.
Add asparagus and red pepper.
Cover and steam 5 minutes.
Add zucchini and mushrooms. Cover and steam 5 minutes. Add corn.
Cover and steam 1 minute.
Transfer vegetables to a bowl.
Toss with olive butter.
Yields 6 servings.

title: appalachicola spaghetti sauce
directions: Coat meat with flour.
Brown with garlic and onion in olive oil.
Add other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 4 to 5 hours.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add beans and tomatoes.
Cook 40 minutes on medium heat on stove top.
Season to taste.

title: baked apricots
directions: Drain apricots and place in a buttered baking dish in layers. Dot each layer with butter.
Sprinkle brown sugar, mixed with cinnamon on top.
Sprinkle with Ritz cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: chocolate raspberry brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In medium saucepan over medium heat, place chips and butter.
Heat, stirring constantly, until melted. Remove from heat. Stir in flour, sugar, eggs and baking powder. Blend thoroughly. Spread batter in greased and floured 8 or 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from sides of pan. Cool completely in pan on wire rack. Cut into squares.
Yields 20 brownies.

title: peanut butter stars
directions: Cream the margarine, peanut butter and sugars. Add eggs.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.

Mix with creamed mixture. Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla. Shape into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Remove from oven and press 1 chocolate star in the middle of each cookie. Return to oven for 2 minutes or until lightly browned.
Do not overbake.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from cookie sheets.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen cookies. Recipe can be halved for a smaller batch.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar until creamy. In a separate bowl mix instant pudding and milk.
Add to cheese mixture; add Cool Whip.
Alternate crushed cookies and mixture in flower pot or pan.
Save enough cookie crumbs to cover the top. Add gummy worms and/or flowers for decoration.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Bring butter and brown sugar to a boil. Add pecans. Layer graham crackers on cookie sheet. Pour mixture over graham crackers. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: mystery pie
directions: Let water, sugar and cream of tartar boil for 5 minutes.
Add crackers one at a time.
Do not stir; let boil for 2 minutes. Place mixture in an unbaked pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Add top crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 425° or until brown.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light.
Add egg, then sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk, to make a soft batter. Fold in blueberries and fill muffin tins about 2/3 full (use foil liners).
Bake in a 400° oven about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, garlic; then drain.
Add tomato sauce and taco seasoning and let simmer.

title: black-eyed pea supper
directions: Cook sausage in large frying pan or a Dutch oven.
Drain fat. Add green pepper, onion and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and seasonings and stir well.
Add peas with liquid.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice with grated cheese. (Better if prepared ahead of time.
The flavors have a chance to blend.)

title: mulled cider
directions: Heat apple cider in a large saucepan or slow cooker.
Add brown sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add spices and simmer 15 minutes.
Pour into mugs.
Garnish with slices of orange and cinnamon sticks, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg, applesauce, flour, salt and cinnamon and mix well. Mix 2 teaspoons soda with 1/2 cup boiling water and add to the mixture. Add raisins and nuts. Bake in prepared pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add bananas and sift together flour and baking soda.
Add to mixture. If desired add nuts.
Pour mixture into a loaf pan and bake at 325° for about an hour.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; combine all ingredients, then add macaroni. Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: white chili
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain. Saute onion in oil.
Stir in garlic, chilies, cumin, oregano and cayenne.
Saute 3 minutes more.
Add the beans and 8 cups of chicken broth.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer until beans are tender (several hours).
If mixture becomes too dry, add more chicken broth.
Stir in chicken pieces.
Season with salt and pepper.
Ladle into serving bowls, top with shredded cheese. Stir until cheese melts.
Garnish with salsa.

title: yummy peanut butter bars(no bake)
directions: Combine all ingredients except chips and press into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Melt chips in microwave 20 to 30 seconds. Spread over peanut butter mixture and refrigerate for 2 or more hours before serving.

title: no-fat cole slaw
directions: Mix ingredients together in large bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: taco dip (spread)
directions: Mix together and spread on tray.
Then layer: shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, chili peppers and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Serve with nachos.

title: spaghetti pie(makes 2 deep pies)
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Drain.
Add butter and cheeses.
Salt.
Brown ground beef in skillet with next 5 ingredients.
Drain beef into colander.
Pour grease out of skillet.
Return beef to skillet and crispen ground beef.
Add chopped pepper, onion and mushrooms. Stir over medium/high heat until veggies are tender.
Add tomatoes and beef mixture.
Reserve 2 cups meat sauce, using slotted spoon. Mix balance with noodles in buttered pie pans, forming "shells." Top with reserved meat.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with grated or sliced processed cheese.
Return to oven to melt.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil water and sugar together for 5 minutes.
Drop in fresh cranberries and cook until they burst open.
Set off stove and add cherry jell-O and cool to lukewarm.
Add drained, crushed pineapple, chopped celery and chopped nuts.

title: master mix
directions: Measure all dry ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Blend well.
Measure shortening and add to dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Place mixture in a labeled Ziploc bag; store in the refrigerator.

title: fresh orange pie
directions: Cook together the water, sugar, Jell-O, cornstarch and oranges until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with Cool Whip topping.

title: cherry pie filling cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put 3/4 in cake pan; add 1 can cherry pie filling.
Then add the remaining cake.
Swirl together. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: crab puffs
directions: Combine cream cheese, crabmeat, bread crumbs and 2 drops sesame oil.
Heat 1-inch peanut oil in skillet or wok.
Put 1 teaspoon of filling in center of each won ton wrapper.
Fold corner to center, wetting edges to seal.
Deep fry for about 3 minutes or until brown and puffed.
Drain.
Serve hot with Chinese mustard.

title: pork chops baked in sour cream
directions: This "Community Meal" requires all at the table to become involved in the cooking.

Raw meats and vegetables are arranged on platters around a boiling (electric) skillet of chicken broth. All take part in "feeding" the skillet with the raw ingredients which take a minute or so to cook.
Continue feeding the skillet as cooked pieces are removed to individual's sauce bowls for flavoring and enjoying.

title: chicken a la
directions: Melt butter.
Combine rest of ingredients, except chicken, with butter.
Coat chicken wings with mixture.
Bake wings skin side down, for 1/2 hour at 350°.
Turn and continue baking for 15 to 20 minutes or until browned and tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, soup, celery, onion, chestnuts, and mayonnaise. Add 1 cup corn flakes, mix well. Pour into 9 x 13 inch dish, (sprayed with Pam). Mix remaining cornflakes with melted butter and spread on top. Bake at 325° for 35-40 minutes.

title: peanut butter and jelly cake
directions: Cream margarine and peanut butter; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients and add alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.
Spread jelly between layers; spread top and sides with peanut butter frostings.
Garnish with chopped peanuts if desired.

title: tuna balls(low calorie)
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and roll into about 12 to 14 balls.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Serves 3.

title: crispy onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In shallow baking pan, blend everything but potatoes.
Cut potatoes into quarters leaving peelings on if desired.
Add potatoes to pan and stir to coat. Bake (stirring occasionally) for 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Garnish with parsley.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix together then fold in 9 ounces Cool Whip.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer a row of graham crackers, then filling, then graham crackers.
Cover with the following glaze.

title: tomato, macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain.
Saute onion in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Add tomatoes, oregano, salt and pepper. Cook and stir to break up tomatoes for 10 minutes.
Add macaroni, sour cream and Cheddar cheese and mix well.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine, cut in pieces, on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: jo ann's goulash
directions: Brown meat in skillet and drain.
Add other ingredients and simmer until onion and pepper are tender.

title: popcorn
directions: Pour vegetable oil into corn popper.
Pour seeds into popper. Put top on and plus popper in.
Wait about 5 to 10 minutes. Unplug popper and eat!

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cukes, onions and peppers under ice, at least 3 hours under ice.
Combine other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add vegetables; bring to boiling point, don't boil.
Fill sterilized jars to overflowing.
Clean lip of jar and seal.

title: connecticut beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and stir in onion.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix together the soup, sour cream, milk and salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and ground beef.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread mix according to package directions.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a 13 x 9 pan.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Mix together well and drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: simple cornbread dressing(with giblet gravy)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Taste and adjust seasoning, if needed.
Refrigerate for at least an hour or overnight for flavors to blend.
Pour into a 2-quart baking pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.
I usually add cooked chicken to the dressing before baking.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix the three cans of fruit.
Add pudding mix and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Before serving, add bananas if desired.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, cinnamon and salt. Slowly add apple juice and stir well. Add apple slices. Simmer over low heat until thickened. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Cover with second shell, crimping edges. Bake at 350° for approximately 35 to 40 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: spanish cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a loaf pan (8 x 14-inch or average size).
Pour in cherry pie filling and spread over bottom of pan.
Next, add the crushed pineapple (do not drain). Spread this evenly over the cherries.
Empty dry cake mix over pineapple, spreading evenly.
Then sprinkle nuts.
Next, dice two cubes of oleo over the whole mixture.
Put in oven and let bake for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: cowboy supper
directions: Brown hamburger. Drain. Cook shells and cheese. Pour spaghetti sauce on shells. Add hamburger. Mix. Add cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients with wire whisk.
Add next 3 ingredients and blend well with mixer for 2 minutes.
Use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake for about 35 minutes at 325°.
Let cool completely before icing.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with banana, blending well after each addition.
Stir in nuts. Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add taco seasoning and water as directions stated on envelope and simmer as directed.
Add refried beans and 1/2 of salsa.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top as you wish.
I usually put cheese on first, then make stripes of the remaining salsa and sour cream.
On top of that, I sprinkle chopped lettuce, onions and end with black olives.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt oleo over low heat; cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, cloves, ginger and cinnamon.
Add to first mixture.
Chill.
Form in 1-inch balls; roll in granulated sugar.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cappuccino
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fills 1 quart jar.
Add 2 tablespoons in 6 ounce cup of hot water.

title: rancho baked beans
directions: Fry ground beef, onions and shortening in skillet until meat browns.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes.
May be mixed in advance and refrigerated.
Bake just before serving.
Also freezes well.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream the butter.
Add the honey and molasses.
Continue beating until they are combined.
Beat in the egg and vanilla. Mix together the flour, ginger, cinnamon and baking soda.
Add to the butter mixture.
The dough will be slightly sticky. Refrigerate the dough for 1 hour before baking.

title: chipolte chili de pollo
directions: In a stockpot, combine peppers, chicken, bouillon, garlic, onion, carrots, celery, mushrooms, garbanzo beans and approximately 6 to 8 cups of water.
Cover with cumin seed, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 3 hours.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Combine beans and soda in a deep 3-quart casserole.
Cover with water 2-inches above beans; let soak overnight.
Drain beans.
Combine beans, 5 cups water and next 5 ingredients.
Cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap and microwave on High for 15 minutes or until boiling.
Add ham and bay leaf. Reduce to Medium-low (30 percent) power; cover and microwave for 2 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Remove and discard bay leaf.

title: south african grilled chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken, in a glass bowl and let stand for 12 - 24 hours.
Reserving some sauce for basting, marinate chicken pieces in remaining sauce for at least 4 hours in the refrigerator (the longer it marinates, the stronger the flavor).
Grill chicken, basting with reserved marinade until well done.

title: peach supreme
directions: Prepare and bake cake according to package directions, in a 13x9 pan.
Cool cake and spread 1/2 container of Cool Whip on top. Arrange peach slices on top and then spread remaining Cool Whip over peaches.
Chill overnight.

title: sweet 'tater pone
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
In a mixing bowl, combine the sweet 'taters, nutmeg, sugar and 1/2 cup of pecans.
Add the milk and egg.
Pour into the prepared baking dish and sprinkle with the remaining pecans.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cranberry-apple casserole
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Put into a 2-quart baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together; sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Combine egg, sugar and flour.
Add enough of the water to make a smooth paste.
Add remaining water and vinegar; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Put in jars and refrigerate.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: campers special
directions: Crumble and brown beef with onion.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook until well messed up, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve on warmed buns.

title: sunday spice cake
directions: Beat the first 10 ingredients vigorously for two minutes. Stir in baking powder, eggs, soda and milk.
Mix thoroughly and pour into cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Frost.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in oleo.
Add soup, milk, rice and Cheez Whiz.
Cook broccoli and add to mixture.
Pour in casserole and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix in pan over medium heat first 4 ingredients.
Let boil for 1 minute.
Turn off heat.
Adding rest of ingredients, mix well. Spoon on waxed paper to harden.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and gradually add sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and pumpkin. Mix well.

title: skillet scramble
directions: In a large skillet, saute the potatoes, green pepper and onion in oil.
Sprinkle with onion powder, garlic powder and season salt; mix well.
In a bowl, combine the eggs, ham, water, salsa, salt and pepper.
Add to the potato mixture.
Cook until eggs are set. Sprinkle with cheese; cook 2 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.

title: hardtack(molasses cookies)
directions: Blend spices in flour.
Mix lard and molasses.
Add sugars, then egg and flour and spices.
Divide dough; roll in long rolls in wax paper.
Put in freezer and freeze hard.

title: arabian-style pork chops
directions: Say prayer.
Season chops.
Put 1 slice tomato on each chop followed by a layer of rice.
(Use all the rice on this layer.) Next layer, add onion, then green pepper.
Bake at 300° to 325° for approximately 2 hours.

title: cafe mocha mix
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
To serve, measure 1 tablespoon into cup.
Fill with boiling water.
Serves 80.
Makes 5 cups.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix marshmallows, pineapple and drained, pitted cherries.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions for sheet pan.
Mix crushed pineapple and sugar; bring to a boil.
Spoon on cooked cake while hot.
Cool cake completely.
Prepare vanilla instant pudding according to package directions.
Spread on cooled cake.
Spread Cool Whip on pudding layer.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Chill overnight.

title: spanakopita
directions: Cook spinach; drain (squeeze out any moisture).
Break Feta into spinach.
Mix 2 teaspoons olive oil and 2 eggs with mixture. Melt 2 sticks butter with 2 teaspoons olive oil. Spray cookie sheet, brush each phyllo with butter/oil mixture.
Lay 12 sheets of phyllo, spoon mixture on, then continue with 12 remaining sheets of phyllo.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (until golden brown).
Cool before cutting.
Can be served hot as a meal or great cold as an appetizer.

title: st. patrick's punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid in boiling water.
Add cold water, lemonade and pineapple juice.
Blend well; add ginger ale and ice just before serving.
Makes 15 to 20 servings.

title: tuna delight
directions: Drain tuna fish.
Chop up onion, celery and pickles.
Layer bowl with the lettuce.
Mix together tuna fish, fat-free dressing, onion, celery and pickles.
Pour into lined lettuce bowl.
Chop cherry tomatoes into halves and top tuna fish.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Place potatoes, onion and celery in large saucepan.
Cover with water and cook until done.
Drain clam juice into saucepan. Add thyme, salt and pepper and bring to good boil.
Stir in flour paste.
Add milk and clams.

title: potato candy
directions: Mix all ingredients except peanut butter.
Roll out flat and spread with a thin layer of peanut butter.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Chill in refrigerator.
Slice in pieces.
Do not add salt or seasonings to potatoes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine and mix the first 11 ingredients in order.
Add the apples and pecans to the mixture.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Place cake in pan in a brown paper bag until cooled.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, peanut butter, brown sugar and 1 cup granulated sugar in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of mixer until well blended.
Beat in eggs, milk and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed until blended.
(Dough will be stiff.)

title: rice meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make balls slightly larger than walnut.
Place in baking dish.
Pour can of tomato or mushroom or celery soup and 1 can of water over the meat balls and bake slowly 2 1/2 hours in 350° oven.
Makes 18 meat balls.

title: pig cake
directions: Combine cake mix, orange juice and margarine.
Add eggs, 1 at a time; beat 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool before icing.

title: orange bread pudding
directions: Heat orange rind, yolks, milk, sugar, vanilla and salt slightly.
Break bread in small pieces and soak in liquid for 15 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Bake 45 minutes in 375° oven. After cooking and when still hot, pour juice of one orange over the pudding.
Prepare meringue.

title: hershey's syrup chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Wash skins on all apples thoroughly.
Leave the skin of apples on, then cut into slices, making sure all seeds are removed. Place apples in a large bowl.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all together; chill several hours before serving with crackers.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Cut and wash eggplant in slices.
Beat eggs thoroughly.
Put cut eggplant into large bowl of water.
Put vegetable oil in skillet.
Turn heat to medium-high.
Beat eggs in bowl 1. Mix corn meal, flour, seasoning salt and pepper in separate bowl 2. Dip 1 slice of eggplant in eggs then dip into meal mixture, then into hot skillet.
Repeat until skillet is full.
Turn in skillet as needed to avoid sticking.
Repeat until all are cooked, should be golden brown and tender.
Best when served hot.
Always remember to season to your taste.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Bake or boil potatoes and peel.
Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Place a layer of potatoes in bottom of buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and dot with butter.
Continue layers until all ingredients are used, ending with sugar and butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for about 30 minutes or until glazed.
Add marshmallows the last 5 minutes to melt and brown lightly.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Beat the egg yolks for 5 minutes or until thick.
Slowly add condensed milk, lime juice and lime peel; then set aside.
In another bowl, with clean beaters, beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Do not beat whites stiff. Gently fold the condensed milk mixture into the beaten egg whites. Spoon into pie shell.
Bake 20 minutes or until the filling is firm.
Serve at room temperature with a dollop of whipped cream

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and soda.
Add pineapple and eggs; mix.
Pour into cookie sheet pan.
Mix brown sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll very thin.
Cut in small pieces; drop into rich chicken broth (boiling). It is very good to have this frozen.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar.
Add pineapple with juice and strawberries; blend well.
Add nuts and Cool Whip.
Store in sealed container and freeze.

title: teriyaki meat
directions: Cook until it's done.

title: poppy seed coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased loaf pans (makes two 9 x 5-inch loaves).
Bake for 1 hour in a preheated 350° oven.
Freezes well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Mix all ingredients and bake in 2 floured and greased loaf pans or in 1 Bundt pan at 375° for 1 hour.
Check doneness after 45 minutes.

title: no fail divinity
directions: Combine sugar, Karo and water.
Cook, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Continue to cook over low heat, no stirring, until hard ball forms.
Whip egg whites and salt until stiff, but moist. Slowly pour hot syrup while stirring.
When thick, add vanilla and nuts.
Pour on greased plate or pan and let cool before cutting into pieces.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients just until moistened.
Drop by teaspoon, about 2 inches apart, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in heated 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: homemade pretzels
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in a little of the water.
Add rest of water, brown sugar and flour.
Knead 3 to 5 minutes until dough is smooth and elastic.
Cover and rest 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Fill large pot with water and add 1 tablespoon baking soda for each cup of water.
Bring to a boil.
Cut dough into 24 equal pieces; form into pretzels.

title: asparagus and shrimp salad
directions: Cut tomatoes into wedges.
Cook fresh shrimp in large amount of boiling salted water for 1 to 3 minutes.
(Cook frozen shrimp according to directions.)
Drain and set aside.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Place spareribs in roasting pan.
Brown in oven heated to 350°.
When browned, pour off grease.
Arrange ribs into a single layer and cover with thinly sliced onions.
Arrange in layers until all ribs are in pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: bran muffins
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and buttermilk; mix well, then add flour, soda and salt.
Mix together, then add raisins. Pour boiling water over cereal; mix well.
Let cool and then add the remaining ingredients.
Put in muffin tins.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until done at 350°.
Keeps 6 to 8 weeks in refrigerator.
Keep covered in refrigerator.
Never stir.
Always take from the top.

title: potluck casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in salt water; drain and rinse.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Add tomato sauce and cook for 15 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375°
for 20 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken and wine dinner
directions: Place chickens in roaster.
Put clove of garlic in each chicken; save 1 clove for the pot.
Surround chickens with vegetables.
Sprinkle with sauces to taste.
Pour wine over all. Season with salt and pepper.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and baking soda.
Set aside. Combine remaining ingredients.
Add dates to combined ingredients. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven for 35 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add seasoning mix and sauce.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with rolls.
Layer crushed corn chips, beef, sour cream and cheese.
Sprinkle remaining chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for at least 1/2 hour.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Crunch chips with garlic salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in butter and roll in chips.
Place chicken pieces on pan, skin side up, not touching.
Pour rest of butter and chips over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Do not turn chicken.

title: batter for deep fried fish
directions: Beat all ingredients together well.
Dip fish into batter; let excess batter drain, and drop into hot grease.
Fish is almost done when fillet floats to surface.
Wait until golden brown, remove and serve.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place layers of the vegetables in the order given.
Season each layer with salt and pepper.
Put the lightly browned ground beef on top of the celery.
Mix the tomato soup with the water and pour into crock-pot.
Cover and set to low for 6 to 8 hours (high for 2 to 4 hours, stirring occasionally).
Ingredients may be increased by half for the 4 1/2-quart model.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° until brown, about 25 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Cut into squares.
Can be frozen.

title: "mygdalota" - almond cookies
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl and work with hand until well mixed.
Pinch off piece of dough the size of a small walnut and roll between the palms of the hands.
Place on cookie sheet; press one-half blanched almond on top with thumb.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan at once.
Makes about 25 to 32 cookies.

title: dilled ham deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs lengthwise into halves; remove yolks.
Mash yolks in small bowl.
Mix in mayonnaise and dill until smooth.
Stir in ham.
Fill each egg white half with about 1 tablespoon of yolk mixture.
Refrigerate 1 to 4 hours to blend flavors.

title: creamy noodles
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Combine cream cheese and milk.
Heat and stir until smooth.
Stir in broccoli and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook noodles and drain.
Pour sauce over noodles.

title: sweet and sour prawns
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Heat wok or skillet until hot.
Add oil, swirling to coat sides.
Add shrimp.
Stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes until shrimp just turns pink.
Add carrots, green pepper and pineapple.
Cook and toss about 2 minutes.
Add reserved pineapple syrup, vinegar, catsup, soy sauce and ginger.
Cook, stirring for 1 minute.

title: apple betty
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix together apples, sugar, and lemon extract.
Place in a 9 x 13 inch baking pan.
Combine the cheese, butter and graham cracker crumbs, stirring to mix evenly and spread over the apples.
Bake on the lowest rack of the oven for 35 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: arlington salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except boiled eggs and croutons in large salad bowl and toss good.
Put on salad plates and garnish with eggs that have been cut into quarters and put croutons on the top of salad.
Tomatoes can also be used to garnish with just quartering them.
This can be served with crackers or hot whole wheat rolls.

title: pickled fish
directions: Put vinegar and canning salt in a gallon crock.
Put fish in brine for 10 days; stirring daily.
Wash in cold water.
Heat 4 cups white vinegar and 4 cups sugar until sugar dissolves.
Add 12 cloves, 12 allspice, 5 cinnamon sticks and 6 bay leaves.
Slice 2 big onions, place between layers.
Let set 4 weeks.

title: dutch oven limas
directions: Presoak
beans
overnight and boil until almost tender. Add remaining
ingredients and be sure to have enough juice to cover beans (add
water
if needed).
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.
If using ham hock, remove and cut off meat, adding meat back to pot.

title: mint patty cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and mix well. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add peppermint flavor.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add 2/3 cup sugar, beating at medium speed with mixer until light and fluffy.
Add molasses and egg; beat well.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients; gradually add to creamed mixture, stirring until well blended.
Divide dough in half, wrap each portion in plastic wrap and put in freezer for 30 minutes.
This is important otherwise dough will be very sticky to handle.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Cook until mixture is thick and brown the brown sugar, butter and cream.
Then add milk, flour and egg yolk; mix again. Stir constantly until thick. Cool. Add to baked pastry shell-meringue as usual.

title: squash and corn soup(sac and fox foods)
directions: Slice squash into 1/8-inch slices.
Cut corn off cob.
Use a large pot.
Put squash and corn into pot and cover with water 1/2 inch over vegetables.
Boil together 45 minutes.
Add sugar to taste, about 15 minutes after it starts boiling.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Cook cake mix in sheet pan; leave in pan.
Cool.
Punch holes with fork.
Mix milk and cream of coconut and pour over cake.
Mix frozen coconut and Cool Whip and top cake.
Chill.
Keep cool.
tags: cream of coconut pina colada mix

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil and drain spaghetti. Mix with butter, eggs and Parmesan. Press into a casserole dish.
Spread with cottage and Mozzarella cheeses.
Cook beef, onion and green pepper.
Drain.
To meat mixture, add tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Cook until blended.
Pour on top of spaghetti.
Bake 20 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.
Sprinkle with grated Mozzarella and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: soup salad
directions: Stir all vegetables together and chill at least one hour.
Eat cold.

title: rye boat dip
directions: Mix together the ingredients and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Add 2 (3 ounce) packages of dried beef, shredded.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Combine flour, milk and mayonnaise in bowl; mix well.
Fill greased muffin cups.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: molotiv cocktails
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender (must do in at least two batches to fit all ingredients).
Sprinkle top of each portion with a little ground cinnamon or nutmeg.

title: crock-pot potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients into 5-quart crock-pot (except for the milk and chives).
Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.
Stir in milk the last hour.
Top with chives when you serve.
Keeps 1 week in refrigerator.

title: peanut-jelly bars
directions: Lightly grease bottom and sides of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix well with spoon.
Cream margarine and sugar in large mixing bowl until light and fluffy. Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Evenly sprinkle half the crumb mixture onto bottom of greased baking pan. Spread jelly evenly over crumb mixture with back of spoon. Sprinkle remaining crumbs mixture over jelly.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls onto cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix together cream cheese, dressing mix and mayonnaise; spread mixture on cooked crust after it's cooled.
Sprinkle the raw vegetables on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: minestrone
directions: Slice sausage about 1/4 inch thick. Brown in oil in nonstick skillet or pan. Take out the meat and add to the pan, onions, garlic, carrots, celery, basil, parsley and cilantro. Cook and stir for 5 minutes. In soup pot combine vegetables, zucchini, tomatoes with liquid, water, cabbage, bouillon cubes and pepper. Bring to boil, add the meat, cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Add beans with liquid. Cook for 20 minutes longer on medium heat, stirring occasionally. Great served with cornbread.

title: ruby elliott's zucchini casserole - california
directions: Into 2-quart saucepan with water to cover, add zucchini, onion, garlic and bell pepper.
Cook until tender and drain well. May be microwaved.
Into a large bowl, mix eggs, bread, pepper, salt, oil, milk, 1/2 cup cheese and sausage, then add zucchini mixture.
Spray a 6 x 9-inch pan with Pam; pour mixture into pan and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until dry.

title: creamy baked chicken
directions: Wash and skin chicken; season and place in dish.
Cover with cream of chicken soup, mixed with water.
Sprinkle parsley generously.
Bake for about 1 hour, or until chicken is done. Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: caldou-seafood(typical joola dish in the casamance, senegal)
directions: Cook onions in 2 tablespoons hot oil.
Add tomatoes and boneless fish; cook for 3 minutes.
Add water, maggi cube and salt to taste.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Mix in 2 tablespoons of lemon juice and cook another 5 minutes.
Serve over warm rice.

title: date balls
directions: Cook together for 9 minutes the oleo, brown sugar, dates and

title: lone star caviar
directions: Soak peas in enough water to cover for 6 hours or overnight. Drain well. Transfer peas to a saucepan. Add enough water to cover. Bring to
a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and allow to boil until tender, about 45 minutes.
(Do not overcook.)
Drain well and transfer to a large bowl. Blend dressing and let cool. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: eggplant sauce for pasta
directions: Saute eggplant and onion in olive oil about 15 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve over your favorite pasta.
Sprinkle with grated Romano cheese.

title: window pane candy
directions: Combine marshmallows and chopped pecans in large bowl.
Melt chocolate drops and butter.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Pour over marshmallows and pecans.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook carrots and celery in water until tender; do not drain. Cook onions in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, then milk and broth over low heat.
Stir in cheese, vegetables and water.
Do not overcook or boil.
Makes 6 cups.

title: tortilla snack
directions: Put jelly and peanut butter in a tortilla.
Microwave a few seconds and serve.
Delicious!

title: dill pickle snacks
directions: Drain pickles and dry with paper towel.
Soften cream cheese (very soft).
Spread cream cheese on ham slice; wrap around pickle.
Continue to wrap pickle with ham and cream cheese slices until well-covered.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices.
Very tasty!

title: sweetheart pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip and pie filling.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill at least 4 hours before serving.

title: daddy's favorite chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt in separate bowl.
Cream butter and sugar together until well blended.
Add brown sugar, eggs and vanilla to sugar/butter mixture.
Slowly blend in flour mixture. Add chips and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: never fail fudge(microwave)
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together in small plastic mixing bowl. Make hole in mixture and cut butter up in hole.
Pour milk in. Microwave 2 minutes on High power or until bubbly.

title: gazpacho soup
directions: Mix all ingredients
and
refrigerate at least 24 hours before serving.
Serve in bowls and top with a few croutons.

title: rita's picadillo ground beef
directions: Brown ground meat thoroughly and drain.
Add all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer about 1/2 hour. Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar and beat well again.
Add oil, flour and baking powder.
Mix cinnamon with apple slices and fold into mixture. Pour into a greased and floured 8-inch or 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Place dry milk and water in blender and blend well.
Add sugar and butter, blending well until sugar is dissolved.
Store in refrigerator.
One and one-third cups of this recipe is equal to 1 can.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix your dough as you would for making biscuits.
Roll out on floured wax paper until your dough can be cut in strips.
Cut strips into small pieces.
Remove chicken from broth.
Put 1/2 cup sweet milk into chicken broth, bring to boil and add dough strips.
Cook on medium heat for about 15 minutes.
Take chicken from bone and put into large bowl.
When dumplings are done, add pepper and salt.
Pour over chicken and serve hot.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix together water and vinegar.
Set aside.
Mix together sugar and flour.
Slowly mix together; stir until smooth.
Cook in microwave on High until hot and begins to thicken (must be stirred every 45 seconds to 1 minute).
Pour a small amount of thickened mixture over beaten egg.
Stir until well blended, then combine all of the remaining mixture.
Return to microwave until thick (again stirring about every minute).

title: escalloped corn
directions: Beat eggs and add other ingredients together; mix well.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven, covered. Then remove cover and bake until brown (about 10 to 15 minutes).

title: 7-week bran muffins
directions: Mix 1 cup all-bran and boiling water; cool.
Add the oil to the cooled cereal mixture.
Mix the flour, soda and salt together.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, then buttermilk and 2 cups all-bran.
Mix well.
Stir in first cereal mixture, then the flour mixture.
Store in covered container in refrigerator until ready to bake muffins.
(Keeps 7 weeks.)
Bake muffins at 425° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: tetrazzini
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine; add soup and water.
Mix, then add shredded cheese.
Cook over medium low until cheese is melted; add meat and stir.
Add spaghetti (drained) and stir.
Place Tetrazzini mixture into 2 quart or larger casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: grandma charlotte's cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage, onions and carrots.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Mix; re-season if desired.
Can make this the day before.

title: chicken gourmet
directions: Break up dried beef and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Wrap chicken in bacon and lay on dried beef.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate 3 1/2 hours or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
(Or at 275° for 3 hours.)

title: tortellini ala fini
directions: Boil 4 quarts water.
Add tortellini; boil until tender, about 7 to 9 minutes.
While tortellini is boiling, melt butter in a skillet.
Add mushrooms, ham, garlic and oregano.
This mixture is finished when the mushrooms darken.
At this point, add the Parmesan and remove from heat.
When tortellini is tender, add the peas and remove from heat after 30 seconds.
Drain.
Add Alfredo sauce to the tortellini.
Mix in the sauteed mushrooms and ham. Serve.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Layer ingredients as follows:

enchilada or bean dip, avocados, mashed and seasoned to taste with lemon juice, mixture of sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning, browned ground beef, black olives, sliced and drained, green onions and tomatoes, mixed and shredded cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: baked penne with cheese and veggies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Boil water and add pasta, onions and garlic.
Cook 5 minutes and add zucchini and cauliflower.
Cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain and transfer to a large bowl.
Stir in tomato sauce, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper.
Coat an 8 x 12 baking dish with nonstick spray.
Spread 1/2 of pasta mix in dish.
Layer with Ricotta cheese.
Top with remaining pasta.
Sprinkle with Cheddar.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Place rice in the bottom of a roaster.
Dip pieces of chicken in oleo until coated, then place chicken on top of rice.
Add soup and water in a pot with remaining oleo and bring to a boil.
Pour over the chicken and rice.
Bake covered at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: low-fat bran muffins
directions: Line standard muffin tins with paper cups and spray lined tins with vegetable cooking spray.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together first 5 ingredients.
Stir in bran and let stand 5 minutes.
Toss together remaining dry ingredients.
Combine with sugar-egg mixture.
Add boiling water and blend until smooth.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: sausage balls
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
By hand, mix all ingredients.
If it becomes too dry, add more water a drop at a time.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls and bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Parboil zucchini and onion in salt water for 5 minutes. Drain.

title: ham loaf
directions: Put through food chopper, minced ham, onion and parsley.
Add eggs, pepper, bread crumbs, mustard and tomato juice.
Blend well. Pack into greased loaf pan and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Check to see if done.

title: beans
directions: Brown meat, onion, and bell pepper.
Drain; then add other ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
May be simmered on top of stove or crock pot.

title: cherry delight
directions: We have our own cherries.
I use cherries, water, sugar and red food coloring.
Bring to boil.
Mix with water and 3 heaping tablespoons Clear-Jel and put in boiling cherries.
Stir until thick enough.
Put on low heat and let it slowly boil 5 minutes or so.

title: holiday turkey and biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat butter in 2-quart casserole in oven until melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients except spinach and biscuits.
Bake 20 minutes, stirring once, or until sauce is slightly thickened.
Stir in spinach, prepare biscuits, place around edge of casserole, overlapping biscuits slightly to fit. Increase oven heat temperature to 425°.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until biscuits are golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn.
Add dressing; marinate overnight.
Just before serving, add Fritos.

title: wheat germ crust
directions: Melt butter and add other ingredients and mix well.
Press into pie pan and bake for 8 minutes at 350°.
Cool and fill. Perfect for lemon icebox pie.

title: broccoli puff
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Butter a 5 1/2 cup souffle dish or 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Beat baking mix, milk, eggs and salt with hand beater until smooth.
Stir in broccoli and cheese.
Pour into dish and bake until knife inserted in center of dish comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Serve immediately.

title: corn casserole
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onions.
Drain and add spices and tomatoes.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add corn and simmer another 10 minutes.

title: sheila's chicken
directions: Place chicken in a shallow pan. In small saucepan, melt margarine and stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 375°.

title: food for the world
directions: Attend church faithfully.
Come to every Baptist Women's meeting for further instructions.
Read Prayer Partners every day and pray for the needs listed.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on box and put in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Put in oven.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in Dutch oven.
When melted and at full boil, boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter until melted.
Stir in oatmeal and coconut.
Mix until well coated and spoon onto waxed paper by tablespoons.
Allow to set and serve.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture (flour, soda, baking powder and salt), a little first, then some sour cream.
Keep alternating flour and sour cream, ending with flour.

title: rhonda's cherry crunch
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Stir together cake mix, lemon juice, nuts and margarine.
Crumble over pie filling.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool before serving.

title: cheese and broccoli soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion in margarine until tender. Blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Add cheese. Remove from heat when melted.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: *If adding nuts, add 1/4 cup butter.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Set aside baked crust.
Set aside strawberries.
Filling should be made so it will cool.
Recipe is for 1 quart of berries.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: Peel and core apples.
Cut into fourths. Mix and cook sugar, water and red hots in skillet for 8 to 10 minutes.
Drop in apples (core side down). Cover and cook 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove cover and turn each apple quarter over and continue cooking until apples are clear and tender, but not mushy.
Remove apples to dish; continue cooling syrup about 5 minutes. Pour over apples to glaze.
Serve warm or cold.

title: waldorf salad(this is a great salad for any meal.)
directions: Dice apples.
Add celery, nuts, salt and mayonnaise and mix. Peel and slice carrots, then arrange in a nest shape on lettuce leaves.
Fill nest with apple mixture and serve with French dressing over carrots.
Serves 4.

title: margherita's butterhorn rolls
directions: Mix yeast with water.
Allow to ripen.
Add milk and shortening, then add sugar, salt, eggs and 1/2 of the flour.
Mix for 2 minutes, then add balance of flour by hand.
Smooth dough and place in greased bowl.
Cover with cloth; place in warm place until double in size.
Separate dough into 2 parts and roll into circle.
Cut with sharp knife into 16 pie-shaped pieces.
Roll each pie-shaped piece from wide end.
Place on cookie sheet; let stand for 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes (less baking time if they are going into the freezer).
Makes 32 rolls.

title: german red cabbage
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a large saucepan.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: green bean delite
directions: Brown meat, do not drain. Add cut up medium onion when meat is almost done and finish cooking. Add green beans and tomatoes with salt and pepper to taste. Serve with cornbread and green salad.

title: french blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Coat a 6-cup baking dish with the cooking spray. In a medium bowl, toss the blueberries with the orange flavoring and 1 teaspoon of the granulated sugar and let stand, uncovered, at room temperature for 30 minutes.

title: london broil
directions: Peel off any thin tissue on steak.
Score surface of steak lightly (both sides) in a large, diamond pattern, using a very sharp knife.
Mix oil, soy sauce, lemon juice, onion, garlic and pepper in shallow dish.
Marinate steak in sauce, turning occasionally.
Refrigerate for at least 12 hours or overnight.
To broil, remove from marinade and place on grill.
The steak will be more tender if not grilled too long.
Slice in very thin diagonal slices at an angle against the grain of the meat.
Serve immediately.

title: french toast roll-up
directions: Beat cream cheese, egg yolk and 1/4 cup sugar until smooth. Cut crust off bread and roll each slice out with rolling pin. Spread mix on each piece. Put seam side down on parchment paper-lined pan. Mix 3/4 cup sugar and cinnamon. Brush butter over and roll each in cinnamon/sugar mix. Put seam side down. Cover and freeze 2 hours or up to 2 months. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: okra and rice dressing
directions: Saute okra in a small amount of cooking oil until completely cooked.
Remove okra from pan and brown ground beef in the same pan.
When beef is cooked, add all ingredients together and let simmer together for 5 to 10 minutes, or until thoroughly heated. Serves 8.

title: nell's banana nut cake
directions: Toast pecans in 350° oven about 5 minutes.
Beat eggs until light.
Slowly add sugar.
Beat in margarine and vanilla.
Blend together dry ingredients and add alternately with bananas, beating after each addition.
Mix in 3/4 cup pecans that have been chopped.
Retain about 1/4 cup larger pieces for top of cake. Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Pour mixture into pans and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost layers with vanilla, powdered sugar frosting.
Arrange 1/4 cup pecans on top of cake.

title: fruit pizza pie
directions: Press cookie dough into pizza pan.
Bake according to package directions or until golden brown; cool.

title: lemon pepper pork chops
directions: Coat pork chops on both sides with seasoning.
Place on baking sheet.
Cover with foil.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour depending on thickness at 350°.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: In a large bowl, mix ground beef, rice, onions, salt and pepper.
Form into balls.
Arrange in a baking pan and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and blend in tomato sauce, water and garlic powder.
Pour over meat balls.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake approximately 45 minutes at 350°.

title: 30 minute  corn chowder
directions: In a micro- safe bowl, cover onions and celery with water and cook high for 5 minutes.
Combine all the ingredients into a saucepan and cook on med-low until potatoes are tender, 25 minutes.

title: strawberry pie(shoney's style)
directions: Put sugar, water and cornstarch in saucepan.
Heat, stirring until clear.
Remove from heat and add strawberry Jell-O.
Mix until Jell-O is melted.
Place sliced strawberries in pie crusts and spoon Jell-O mixture over them.
Chill in refrigerator, then spread with Cool Whip over top.
Garnish with reserved strawberries.
Cut in half.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: If a
large amount of shrimp is used, other ingredients will need to be increased or doubled.
Keep everything refrigerated while waiting for flavors to mix and marinate shrimp.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Line sides of pan with dough rolled real thin.
Put in a layer of chicken pieces, then cut 3 eggs in slices.
Add a few pieces of real thin dough.
Slice in other eggs.
Dot this with butter and sprinkle with black pepper. Pour in part of broth.
Roll more dough very thin; cut into narrow strips and place lattice-like on top of pie.
Add more butter on top.
Bake pie until nearly done.
Add more broth and milk.
Test for dryness.

title: cole slaw
directions: Core and slice cabbage (1/4-inch thick).
In very large bowl, mix cabbage, grated carrot and vinegar.
Slowly mix in salad dressing, using only enough to suit your palate.
Chill before serving.

title: german erdberbowle
directions: Pour 7-Up and Welch's white grape juice into punch bowl. Slice the strawberries and put in 7-Up-grape juice mixture.
Stir gently.
If desired, chill for 15 to 20 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: chicken hash
directions: Heat butter in saucepan and saute onion about 3 minutes until softened.
Stir in flour.
Add broth and milk gradually, stirring with wire whisk to form smooth sauce.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: To make thickening for gravy, etc., use warm water instead of cold.

title: eggnog bread
directions: In a bowl, combine butter, sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt into the butter mixture, alternating with eggnog.
Mix only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fold in pecans, raisins and cherries.
Spoon into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 70 minutes or until it tests done.

title: hamburger bake
directions: Using 9 x 13-inch pan, put browned, seasoned and drained crumbled hamburger in bottom. Prepare stuffing as directed on box, then spread on top of hamburger. Mix soups with 1 can of water and pour over dressing. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato and egg casserole
directions: Prepare thin white sauce.
In a heavy skillet, melt 6 Tbsp. margarine.
Blend in 3 Tbsp. flour with a wire whisk.
Slowly pour in 3 cups milk, stirring constantly.
Cook for 2 minutes

title: pineapple baklava
directions: Drain pineapple and save syrup.
In mixer, combine cream cheese, Ricotta cheese, 1/2 cup sugar, egg yolks, lemon peel and vanilla.
Blend well together.
Stir in drained pineapple.
Place a leaf of filo in a well buttered 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking pan. Brush with melted butter and repeat with 8 leaves.
Spoon on pineapple cheese mixture and spread evenly.
Top with remaining filo leaves, brushing each with melted butter.

title: corny dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Let stand 15 minutes. Pop hot dogs in batter and fry at 325° or 350°.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Add rest of ingredients; mixing well. Pour in greased 9x13 pan.
Top with crushed flavor chips.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: ricotta cheese pie
directions: Stir Ricotta cheese by hand or mixer until granular.
Mix eggs, sugar and cream with flour.
Combine with Ricotta cheese. Add almonds and vanilla; mix well.

title: strawberry baked ham
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place ham in a large roaster and arrange the strawberries on top.
Mix the wine, water and mustard together and pour over the ham, letting it drip down the sides. Bake for 1 hour, basting every 20 minutes.
After the ham is baked, slice and serve with Strawberry Sauce.

title: pronto pizza burger
directions: Mix first seven ingredients in large bowl.
Toast muffins under broiler until lightly browned.
Divide meat among muffins. Broil 4 inches from heat for 8 to 10 minutes until meat is done. Place cheese slices on top.
Return to broiler until cheese is melted.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Keep 8 crackers aside.
Break the rest in 4 and mix rest of ingredients together, mixing well.
Put in casserole dish. Crush remaining crackers and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon crumb dessert
directions: Dissolve jello, sugar and salt in boiling water.
Add lemon juice; chill until very thick.
Add evaporated milk and whip until fluffy.
Meanwhile, mix butter and vanilla wafers.
Press firmly into 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pan, reserving 1/3 cup crumbs for garnish. Spoon gelatin mixture into pan.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs, chill until firm.
Makes approximately 24 servings.

title: smothered cabbage with sausage
directions: Combine stock or broth, 2 teaspoons salt and 2 teaspoons pepper in a heavy 6-quart saucepan; bring to a boil.

title: summer-zucchini squash casserole
directions: Combine the onion and squash in a pan with a small amount of water and salt.
Cook until tender.
Drain.
Add 2 Tbsp. of butter, dash of salt and pepper.
Meanwhile, in a medium size mixing bowl, beat 2 eggs slightly, add 1/2 cup half and half or milk.
Combine with the squash mixture.
Fold in 1 cup of grated Cheddar cheese. Put in a greased baking dish, sprinkle with cracker or bread crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes, or until bubbly and brown on top.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Blend cake mix, oil and eggs until moistened.
Add mandarin oranges with juice; mix well.
Bake at 350° in 3 layers (greased and floured) for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Bake
for 15 minutes at 400° in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Crumble with fork after baking.
Mix
powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Fold in Dream Whip.
Spread mixture over top of nut mixture.
Spread pie filling over cream mixture. Refrigerate overnight.

title: southern style hot baked fruit
directions: Place prunes, apricots and pineapple in deep 9-inch round casserole.
Combine pie filling, water and sherry.
Pour over fruit mixture, mixing well. Stir in almonds. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mike's chicken and rice soup
directions: Boil chicken gizzards about 30 to 40 minutes.
Cook rice as directed on back of package.
Cook carrots with 1 can of chicken broth, reserved chicken broth, celery, onion flakes, salt and pepper.
Then add to chicken and rice.
Add water if needed.
Cook everything all together for 20 minutes.

title: esther's beef and cabbage
directions: Cook hamburger, drain and set aside.
Simmer cabbage and onion in fry pan with butter or olive oil.
Add enough water to steam fry.
Stir hamburger and cabbage mixture together, add tomato soup.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350°F for 35-40 minutes.

title: raspberry angel food cake
directions: Slice off top 1/3 of cake and set aside.
Hollow out center of remaining cake leaving a 1-inch shell.
Put shell on serving dish. Melt morsels over low heat, stirring occasionally until smooth. Let cool.
Beat 1 cup whipping cream until stiff (until firm peaks form).
Fold in chambord and melted chocolate.
Spoon into cake shell.
Put top back on cake, pressing down gently.
Beat remaining 2 cups whipping cream until foamy.
Add powdered sugar and beat until firm peaks form.
Spread on cake.
Garnish with raspberries or grated chocolate.

title: wedding soup
directions: Cook meatballs as you normally would.
Keep rolled small.
Warm broth.
Add chopped spinach and boil.
Add precooked meatballs. Reduce to slow simmer.
Add acini de pepe until they are fully cooked.
Add 3 tbsp grated cheese and serve.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Saute bell peppers, green onions, medium onions, celery and garlic in small amount of cooking oil.
Add water to vegetables and boil until tender.
Add parsley flakes, bay leaves, tomato paste, tomatoes, crab boil, red pepper and salt.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add 4 beaten eggs.
Sift 3 1/2 cups flour, baking powder, nutmeg, allspice, cinnamon, salt, soda and cloves together.
Add 2/3 cup water, potatoes and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325° to 350°.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Combine until dough sticks together.
Make into balls, 1 1/2 inches.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: freezer cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrot.
Sprinkle the salt; set aside for 1 hour, then rinse and squeeze dry.

title: carrot bread
directions: Stir together dry ingredients in large bowl.
Heat raisins and apple juice concentrate in small saucepan.
Boil 3 minutes or until raisins become soft.
Pour juice and raisins in blender and process until smooth.
Add egg, vegetable oil, vanilla and banana. Blend until smooth.
Add blender mixture to dry ingredients and stir well.
Stir in carrots.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pot roast
directions: Place roast in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Do not brown meat first.
Blend other ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° until tender, about 3 hours.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix the stuffing mix with the mushrooms and bell pepper. Spread half of mixture in bottom of a 3-quart casserole dish.

title: five bean casserole
directions: Combine all and spread with 1 can Contadina tomato paste and bacon strips.
Makes 2 casseroles or one 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Can be made day before baked.	Flavor even better.

title: marinated shrimp with whole spices
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Drain and pat dry.
In electric blender, blend garlic, ginger, jalapenos, lemon juice, salt and black pepper.
Blend on high speed until you have a smooth paste. In bowl, combine shrimp and paste from blender.
Mix well.
Cover and leave unrefrigerated 1 hour.
(If you wish, leave longer, refrigerate.)
Ten minutes before serving, heat oil in skillet over high heat.
Add cinnamon, cardamom, cloves, peppercorns and bay leaf.
Stir 10 seconds or until bay leaf darkens.
Put in shrimp and marinade.
Cook and stir constantly only until shrimp turn opaque and pink all over.
Remove shrimp and any whole spices that cling with slotted spoon and place in bowl.
Add turmeric to contents of skillet.
Stir over hot burner until sauce becomes thick and pastelike.
This will take a few minutes.
Put shrimp back in skillet.
Stir to coat shrimp well.
Serve over rice. Garnish with sliced scallions.
(Warn people not to bite into whole spices.)

title: layered english pea salad
directions: Fix peas according to directions on package.
Drain and put in	bottom of dish.
Layer the onion next, then the water chestnuts.	Next, layer the celery.
On top of the celery, put the bell pepper.
Next put a layer of shredded lettuce.
Cover this with
the mayonnaise.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. This is best when you refrigerate it overnight.

title: fried bows
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs until lemony; add sugar, vanilla and oleo.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix to make soft dough, adding more flour, if needed.
Knead a few times until smooth.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick on floured board.
Cut in squares; make a slit in center, about 1-inch and slip the corner in slit to make a bow.
Fry in deep oil until light brown.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: spinach-cheese rounds
directions: Thaw pastry at room temperature 30 minutes.
Pre-heat oven to 350°F.
Mix egg and water and set aside.
Mix Pepper Jack, Parmesan, onion, parsley, and garlic powder and set aside.
Unfold pastry on lightly floured surface.
Brush with egg mixture.
Top with cheese mixture and spinach.
Starting at one side, roll up like a jelly roll.
Cut into 20 (1/2-inch) slices.
Place 2-inches apart on baking sheet.
Brush with egg mixture.
Bake 15 minutes or until golden.
Makes 20 appetizers.

title: 20 minute chinese rice
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni and set aside.
In a wok or iron skillet, place 1/2 cup water, 1/4 cup oil, diced onion, carrot and celery and fry until golden brown.
Add to Rice-A-Roni in same wok or skillet.
Add other water and oil; fry diced chicken or pork until done.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon soy sauce and add this to Rice-A-Roni mixture.

title: old fashioned turkey soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine turkey carcass, water, salt, bay leaf and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to boiling point.
Reduce heat and simmer covered for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove carcass and strain broth.
Pull off any meat remaining on bones.
Discard bones.
Return meat to pan.
Stir in celery, carrots, onion and potato.
Simmer covered until vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes. Stir in parsley and season to taste with salt.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Prepare noodles as label directs.
Drain.
Stir in 2 tablespoons butter.
Keep warm.
Cut round steak lengthwise in half, then with knife held in slanting position, almost parallel to the cutting surface, slice across width of each half into 1/8-inch thick slices.

title: shrimp and refried rice
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; set aside.
Pour oil around top of preheated wok or skillet, coating sides; heat at medium high (325°) for 1 minute.
Add onion and pepper; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add shrimp, water chestnuts and next 3 ingredients; cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes.
Push shrimp mixture up sides of wok, forming a well at the center; pour egg into well and stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: apricot pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Spray frypan with nonstick cooking spray. Cook pork chops until done.
Reduce heat to low; stir apricot spread, soy sauce and red pepper in small bowl.
Spread over pork chops and cook until apricot spread melts and sauce is heated through.

title: butter pecan cream cheese cookies
directions: Blend flour, brown sugar and butter until crumbly.
Stir in pecans.
Press mixture into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemon angel roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with aluminum foil, extending foil 1-inch over ends of pan.

title: meat loaf
directions: Use amount of ingredients for each pound of ground beef.
Form into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
During last 10 minutes, pour can of tomato soup over loaf.

title: chicken adoba
directions: Cut up chicken.
Salt and pepper and place in Dutch oven.
Put chopped onion and garlic on top.
Put bay leaves, oregano, poultry seasoning and paprika on top of this.
Add oil and vinegar.
Cook 1/2 hour with top.

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Dissolve
jello
in
water.
Add
pinch
of salt, strawberries, pineapple and banana.
Put half of mixture in mold and set in refrigerator to firm.
Keep other half out so it doesn't congeal.
When jello is firm, spread sour cream on top and pour the rest of mixture over all.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine green onions, potatoes, chicken broth and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Puree mixture in a blender or food processor.
Return to pan.
Stir in sour cream, milk and chives.
Heat gently.
Makes 8 1/2 cups.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Shape into loaf.
Pack down lightly.
Cover with catsup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: spaghetti-pizza style
directions: Beat eggs and milk together; add Parmesan cheese.
Toss into cooked spaghetti.
Pat in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake for 10 minutes at 325°.
Pour sauce over spaghetti and layer on your favorite toppings such as green peppers, sausage, onion, mushrooms, pepperoni, ham or olives.
Cover with a generous amount of Mozzarella cheese.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage 1/2 to 1 hour then remove all large cabbage leaves. Mix all other ingredients together. Put stuffing into cabbage leaves, fold sides of cabbage first then roll. Prepare roaster with foil on bottom, then put layer of extra cabbage on bottom. Place stuffed cabbage rolls into roaster. Take 2 cans of tomato soup, two cans of water, cooked together until smooth and pour over cabbage. Cook for 1/2 to 1 hour. Add 2 cans of tomatoes over top and cook 1/2 hour more.

title: cupcake brownies
directions: Make brownie mix according to package directions.
Put cupcake papers in muffin pan.
Fill cupcake papers half full with batter. Place one peanut butter cup in each.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brownie is done.

title: diabetic pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, cool whip and cinnamon together, pour into pie shell and freeze.
Set out 30 minutes before serving.
Keep remaining pie frozen.

title: whipped shortbread
directions: Cream together, then whip with electric beater for 10 minutes. Drop from spoon on cookie sheet.
Trim with piece of cherry, if desired, or nuts.
Bake in 325° or 350° oven until brown around edges.

title: cheese ball
directions: Form in a ball and roll in 1 package of dried beef or ham. Chill.

title: beef turnovers
directions: Mix beef, mustard and enough gravy to moisten.
Roll pastry in small circles about saucer size. Place meat in center. Fold and seal. Bake at 350° until brown.
Serve with more beef gravy.

title: curly chili dogs
directions: In a microwave-safe 1-quart casserole, combine undrained chili, barbecue sauce and mustard.
Make 4 small slits crosswise in each frankfurter, not cutting through opposite side.
Stir into chili mixture and cover the dish.
Microcook on High power for 4 minutes or until mixture is heated through.
Place frankfurters in hot dog buns and spoon chili mix atop.

title: slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, onions, pepper and pimento in large bowl, set aside.
Bring to a boil vinegar, sugar, turmeric, mustard seed, celery and salt.
Let cool and pour over cabbage mixture and place in refrigerator for 12 hor.
Will keep for weeks.

title: green beans
directions: Mix well and heat.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven
Place butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Place in	oven
to
melt butter.	Remove pan;
sprinkle crumbs over butter,
pressing down with fork.
Sprinkle coconut over crumbs; add
layer	of
chips and one of pecans.
Drizzle milk evenly over the
top.
Bake
at
350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool before cutting.
Makes 24 bars.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water in heavy, large skillet, stirring constantly until hard crack stage.
(Drop a few drops in cold water.
You will hear it crack.)
Add 1 bag (approximately 2 cups) raw peanuts to syrup mixture.
Cook until peanuts start turning brown.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Pour into two cookie sheets and spread.
When completely cooled, break into pieces.

title: easy taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onions and saute.
Stir in juice and taco seasoning.
Then add corn and chili.
When hot, serve with chips, cheese, and sour cream.

title: chicken oporto
directions: In a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot butter, cook mushrooms five minutes.
With a spoon with holes, remove the mushrooms to a small bowl and set aside.
In a plastic bag, combine the flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg and shake it to mix. Insert chicken and shake until it is all coated.
In the remaining butter in the skillet over medium-high heat, cook the chicken breasts until browned on all sides.
Stir in cream, wine and mushrooms and heat to boiling.
