Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until the chicken is tender.
This recipe makes 4 servings and takes 45 minutes to prepare.

title: chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, shortening and peanut butter together. Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Cream together until light and fluffy. Add flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Mix until thoroughly blended.
Place by teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° about 6 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet onto wire rack.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: fruit and pudding salad
directions: Thoroughly mix pudding and juice from pineapple.
Add pineapple chunks, drained peaches and mandarin oranges.
Will just take a few minutes to thicken a bit.

title: spinach dip
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Serve in dish or inside loaf of pumpernickel bread that has been scooped out to form hollow middle.

title: russian tea
directions: Store in an airtight container.
Mix 1 heaping tablespoonful mix to 1 cup boiling water.
Simmer a few minutes.
Use one cup mix to 10 cups water for large batch.

title: real tasting butter
directions: Let all 3 ingredients get to room temperature, then blend together with mixer.
Pour into container.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream butter and 1 1/2 cups sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs and flour; beat well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into 15 x 10-inch pan (greased).
Score batter into 24 squares.
Add 3 cherries to each square.
Top with walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: oatmeal coconut cookies
directions: Blend first six ingredients.
Mix in flour, soda and salt.
Add oatmeal and coconut.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 6 to 10 minutes (10 minutes are best).

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix together orange jello, water and orange juice.
Cool until partially set. Add crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges. Mix well & pour into a 9
X 13 dish. Chill until set. For topping, mix lemon pudding, milk and Cool Whip. Frost the jello.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix together with electric mixer. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: dandelion greens
directions: Pick only the leaves from the dandelions. Wash several times in cold water. Cook in the 2 cups of water until the greens are tender. Drain. Cut the greens.
Add bacon grease and fry about 5 to 10 minutes over low heat.

title: spinach noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Squeeze excess moisture from the thawed spinach.
Set spinach aside.
Mix sour cream, soup, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese together in a mixing bowl.

In a deep casserole spread 1 or 2 heaping tablespoons of sour cream mixture (so the noodles will not stick) then alternate in the casserole layers of noodles, spinach, sour cream mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat almost to the top of the casserole.
Top with a thin layer of sour cream.

title: parmesan bread
directions: Thaw bread, but do not let rise.
Roll into 16 balls.
Roll the balls in flour and set aside for 10 minutes.
Melt oleo and mix in cheese and garlic powder.
Coat the balls with the oleo mixture.
Place in greased bread pan.
Let dough double in size. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: sausage stuffed squash
directions: Remove pulp and seeds from squash.
Place, cut side down, in baking pan with about 1/2-inch water.
Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes until tender.

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Cook sugar, flour, salt, cream and milk until thick.
Add raisins and the juice.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Bake until a few small bubbles appear.
Makes two small pies.

title: tuna balls
directions: Drain and flake tuna. Cream the cheese.
Add lemon juice, horseradish, Tabasco sauce and tuna to creamed cheese and shape into small balls.
Roll into snipped parsley.
Chill several hours.
Makes about 40.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Parboil chopped onion in salt water until clear. Drain and debone salmon.
Mix all ingredients well. Season to taste.
Roll in cracker crumbs mixed with salt, pepper and garlic salt. Fry until golden brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour fruit in bottom of cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over it and pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut over top.
I have also put nuts on top.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: instant cappuccino mix
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients. Store in airtight container. Yield: about 2 1/4 cups of mix.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together.
Cook for 1 hour and 5 minutes at 325 degrees.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice, cook broccoli and drain.
Add soup, Cheez Whiz and milk to rice and broccoli.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle Ritz cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: banana chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Stir in banana and lemon juice.
Add flour, salt and spices.
Stir well.
Mix in oatmeal, nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoon on greased sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until edges turn golden brown.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop 6
quarts
of popcorn and set aside.
Bring butter, brown sugar, salt and Karo syrup to a boil, stirring constantly for 5 minutes;
then
add
vanilla
and
soda.
Pour
over popcorn, mixing well;
then place on cookie sheets and bake in oven at 250° for
hour.
Take
out
and
stir at 15 minute intervals.

title: squash casserole
directions: If fresh squash is used, cook until tender.
Mash cooked squash.
Add butter, slightly beaten egg, cheese, crumbs and milk. Mix well.
Put in a greased baking dish and bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 hour.

title: rainy day pan fried steak
directions: In a large black cast-iron skillet heat olive oil very hot. Place steaks in skillet and sear on each side 1 to 3 minutes. Add mushrooms and onions, simmer for 5 minutes. Add wine and vinegar and heat another 3 to 5 minutes, then add butter, melt completely and cook an additional 5 to 10 minutes. Add seasonings and Worcestershire sauce, reduce heat to medium-low, cover and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes until sauce thickens. Serve steaks with sauce on top. This is a perfect recipe for cooking steak indoors on a rainy day.

title: brenda's coconut pie
directions: Mix
ingredients
together.
Pour into pie shells. Bake for 5 minutes at 400°.
Bake for 60 minutes at 300°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Place ham bone, onion and stewed tomatoes in a large pot.
Add enough water to barely cover the bone.
Bring to a boil and simmer 2 to 3 hours.
Discard the ham bone.
Measure 4 cups stock (freeze remainder).
Add all other ingredients to stock.
Bring to boil and simmer for 1 hour.
Make a roux with 3 tablespoons margarine and 3 tablespoons flour.
Add to soup and cook for 3 minutes. Season to taste.
For heartier soup, add 1 or more cups ham bits.

title: krispy chocolate caramel bars
directions: Using pastry blender or fork, combine flour and sugar, then cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.

title: chicken mornay over english muffins
directions: In 10-inch skillet or 3-quart saucepan with wire whisk, mix milk and cornstarch until blended; heat to boiling over high heat, stirring frequently. Reduce heat to medium and cook until sauce thickens slightly, about 1 minute, stirring constantly.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Combine oil and 1 cup sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in molasses.
Combine flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and ginger.
Add to molasses mixture, stirring well.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll each one in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Remove to wire rack to cool.
Yield:
about 4 dozen.

title: chili non carne
directions: In large pot, saute onion and garlic in oil until soft.
Mix in chili powder, basil, oregano and cumin.
Stir in zucchini and carrots until well blended.
Cook about 1 minute over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Stir in chopped tomatoes, undrained and drained kidney beans.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 to 45 minutes or until thick.
Top with chopped onion, tomatoes and lettuce or green peppers.
Makes 8 (1 cup) servings.
Contains 157 calories per serving.

title: corned grouper
directions: Cut
bacon
in	small
pieces and fry (save drippings). Cut boiled
potatoes, leaving skin on and add fish.
Top with plenty of	green onions.
Add small amount of bacon drippings and wine vinegar to taste.
Add salt and pepper.

title: chicken stuffed with garlic
directions: Season chicken inside and out with salt and pepper.
Pull neck skin over back of chicken and secure with a toothpick.
Peel off papery skin from garlic, keeping cloves intact and place garlic in chicken body cavity.
Add in the sherry and tie tall section and legs together with kitchen string.
Fold wings back.
Brush chicken with oil.
Roast in preheated 375° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until brown and tender.

title: three in one dip
directions: Mix all ingredients at medium speed with an electric mixer until well blended.
Serve warm or cold.
Serve with tortilla chips or vegetables.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve 2 packages of yeast in 2 cups of lukewarm water.
Add other ingredients.
When mixed, let rise until doubled.
Shape into rolls and let rise again.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: karen's chicken and hot sauce
directions: Deep fry chicken until lightly brown.
Remove meat and pour hot sauce and butter over chicken.
Eat.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo, peanut butter and chips over medium heat.
When melted, pour over Rice Chex.
Toss gently until well coated.
Mix powdered sugar and cocoa.
Pour over Chex and shake, shake, shake.

title: spicy banana pecan cake
directions: In mixer bowl, cream together sugar, butter (oleo) and oil until light and fluffy.
Add eggs.
Beat well after each egg. Stir in flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Combine banana and milk alternately with flour mixture.
Beat after each addition.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Turn batter into greased and floured 10-inch fluted tube pan or regular pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until cake tests done.
Dust powdered sugar over cake.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli stems, broth, bay leaf and onion in saucepan. Boil for 10 minutes.
Add bouillon cubes until dissolved.
Remove most of the chunks and set aside broth.

title: homemade peppermint hot chocolate
directions: In a large pan combine water, chocolate chips, sugar, salt and candy canes.
Cook and stir over medium-low heat until chocolate chips melt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Heat until almost boiling--do not boil!
Remove from heat and whisk or beat until frothy.
Serve.
Makes approximately 10 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Cube potatoes.
Cook with beef bouillon cubes until done.
Fry bacon.
Saute onion in drippings.
Drain.
Crumble bacon into potatoes when done.
Thicken with half and half and some milk.

title: picante salsa sauce
directions: Drain both cans of tomatoes.
Put Ro-Tel, onion, jalapeno, salt, pepper and garlic powder into blender.
Blend until onion is chopped.
Add whole tomatoes and blend with an on-off, on-off (2 times) for chunky salsa.
Pour into covered jar.
Chill well before using.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: german french toast
directions: Cut rolls in half and place on plate.
Combine egg yolks, sugar, salt and milk.
Pour over buns evenly.
Allow rolls to soak until liquid is absorbed.
They should not become soggy and break! Dip buns in beaten eggs and coat with bread crumbs.
Fry in hot butter on both sides until golden brown.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar and serve hot.

title: congealed dessert
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.

title: stew ala alice(crock-pot)
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook for 8 hours on low heat.

title: chicken in a crock-pot
directions: Arrange chicken in crock-pot.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cook 6 to 7 hours on low.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: In mixer bowl beat together cream cheese, the 2/3 cup sugar and almond extract until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating each at low speed until blended.
Pour into an ungreased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: coleslaw dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Stir until sugar is dissolved. Pour over cabbage.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook together beef, onions and green pepper. Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve on warm buns.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cracker spread
directions: Mix all together and put pecans on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken n' dressing casserole
directions: Melt margarine and pour evenly over stuffing.
Combine soups and broth.
Layer 1/4 stuffing mix.
Layer all chicken.
Pour soup mixture over.
Layer remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: date krispies
directions: Melt
margarine;
add sugar, egg, nuts and dates.
Cook, stirring
constantly for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in Rice Krispies.
Let cool until you can handle and press into fingers.
Roll
in
powdered
sugar and coconut mixed or either one
separately.
Place
on
cookie sheet and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Store whenever you wish!

title: vegi dip
directions: Mix all ingredients (except nuts) together.
Place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for a few minutes until warmed.
Serve.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Pour 1 cup green enchilada sauce in bottom of pan. Mix together onion, cheese, salt, chilies, sour cream and chicken. Add chicken enchilada sauce. Roll mix into tortillas and place in baking dish. Pour remaining sauce over tortillas. Bake at 350° until bubbly - about 30 minutes. Can be frozen. Makes 12 servings.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown onions and season to taste.
Add pork chops and brown with onions (season also).
Mix 1/2 cup white wine or chicken broth with 1 teaspoon of soy sauce.
Pour over pork and onions; cover.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk and margarine.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour peaches and half of juice over top of batter.
Bake at 350° until top is golden brown.

title: easy candy
directions: Melt chocolate drops over hot water.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk and chopped pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: chocolate cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, creaming until fluffy.
Add unbeaten egg, vanilla, cocoa and cinnamon.
Beat well.
Add 1 cup flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Mix well; add remaining flour. Blend well.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes for a chewy cookie.
Cool and cover tightly (very stiff dough).

title: apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Add first 4 ingredients together and beat until blended.
Mix together next 4 ingredients and add to first mixture.
Next add apples, coconut and nuts; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Blend together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Cream together vegetable oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add bananas and crushed pineapple and juice to cream mixture.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture; stir until all is blended (I use a mixer). Fold in chopped pecans and coconut.
Spoon batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 40 minutes, depending on cake pans used.
Check with toothpick if not sure cake is done.
Cool completely before frosting.

title: eggplant casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Add butter to hot eggplant and mix until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 325° until center rises, about 30 minutes.

title: chinese cabbage slaw
directions: Brown slivered almonds in oven at 375°.
Mix cabbage, onions, almonds and sesame seed together.
Take noodles and crumble them in.
Take soup base packet from noodles and add 1/4 cup oil, 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 tablespoons vinegar.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Add to cabbage mixture 30 minutes before serving.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, cocoa, butter and salt in saucepan. Bring to a boil for 1 minute, stirring often. Remove from heat and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla; mix well. Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper or cookie sheet.

title: mut's pound cake and chocolate icing
directions: Cream together butter, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Add sour cream alternately with flour.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: speidies
directions: Mix all above ingredients together.
Marinate meat a minimum of 48 hours; more flavor results in 4 days.
Turn every 24 hours. Cook on skewers on a grill or broil on rack in oven until done. Place speidies side by side (4 to 6) lengthwise in Italian bread; fold and serve.

title: custard pie
directions: Chill pie shell while making filling.

title: ann's ground turkey stroganoff
directions: Prepare
noodles
according
to
package
directions. Meanwhile, in large
skillet, melt butter and fry onions until yellow and transparent.
Cook turkey until almost done;
drain grease.
Add onion	to turkey.
In separate bowl, combine soup and sour cream	for
gravy.
Stir
gravy
into	meat
mixture. Continue cooking on
low
heat
until gravy is heated through. Add seasonings and serve over noodles.	Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese log
directions: Heat cheddar cheese and cream cheese in double boiler until cheese is melted (using fork, stir continually helping cheeses mix together).
Mix in nuts and garlic powder.
Stir well.
Spoon onto 2 layers of foil with 1 layer of saran wrap on top.
*You may wish to divide into 2 rolls; if so, spoon onto 2 separate foil/saran wrap set-ups.
Carefully pull saran wrap edge and roll cheese on top of itself.
Do several times from both sides to help form log shape.
Sprinkle with chili powder.
Close wrap around log and chill overnight.
Slice and cover again before serving with crackers.

title: hopscotch crunchies
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and peanut butter over hot water. Remove from heat.
Stir.
Stir in chow mein noodles and miniature marshmallows.
Drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper lined cooke sheet.
Chill until set.
Makes about 30 pieces.

title: baked cheezy eggs
directions: Make up bread and cheese into sandwiches.
Add the bacon to top of cheese if desired.
Arrange sandwiches into greased shallow baking dish.
Beat together eggs and milk with salt, pepper and onions (if desired) and pour onto the sandwiches.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes or until custard has formed.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate nut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine crumbs and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
In small saucepan, melt 1 cup chocolate chips with Eagle Brand and vanilla.
Spread chocolate mixture over prepared crust.
Top with remaining (1 cup) chocolate chips, then nuts; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: molasses whoopie pies
directions: Mix together and then chill.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Use Ginger Cream Filling or Filling #2.

title: boursin cheese
directions: Blend all and refrigerate overnight. Serve on crackers.

title: green chili corn bread
directions: Mix cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs with buttermilk, shortening and corn.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Pour small amount into bottom of greased casserole.
Add 1/2 chilies and cheese.
Pour in remainder of mixture.
Top with chilies and cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: christmas cutouts
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar and egg substitute; blend well. Sift baking powder and flour together and add to creamed mixture alternately with the milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Chill.
Roll out 1/8 inch thick and cut out.
Place on cookie sheet that has been sprayed with vegetable spray.
Sprinkle with colored sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 77 cookies.

title: cubed steaks(au poivre)
directions: Sprinkle cubed steaks with pepper and salt.
In a 12-inch skillet, over medium-high heat, in hot butter or margarine, cook 2 cubed steaks at a time until browned on both sides, about 4 minutes.
Arrange steaks on platter; keep warm.

title: chocolate sour cream drop cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheets.
Start oven 10 minutes before baking. Set oven at 420°F.

title: corned beef roll
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread out pizza dough on a large rectangular pan.
Spread thin layer of mustard, then alternate thin layers of cheese and meat; roll up from one end to the other. Lay, seam side down, on cookie sheet (ungreased).
Brush mustard on top.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes.
Cool and slice.

title: sugar-free peach pie
directions: Cook pudding as directed, using milk and peach juice.
Layer peaches in baked shell.
Pour pudding over peaches.
Add nutmeg and a little cinnamon.
Cool and serve.

title: quick easy tomato soup
directions: Heat tomato juice and chopped onion.
Add sugar and butter. Salt and pepper to taste.
Reduce heat.
Mix flour with milk; mix well.
Add milk to soup.
Cook until thickened.

title: mixture
directions: Mix all together.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in large pot.
Add chopped onion and cook until tender.
Add broccoli and cook a few minutes.
Stir in soups and milk.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add cheese and melt.

title: mimi's no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cocoa in medium saucepan.
Add milk and butter;
stir
well.
Bring
to a rolling boil over medium heat. Boil for 1 minute and 30 seconds.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients;
mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool.

title: strange fudge
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing it with your hands.
(The cheese is not melted - it just mixes in).
Place in 9x15 inch pan. Refrigerate 2 hours.
Slice and serve.

title: pumpkin soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute onion and garlic until soft, but not brown.
Add curry, salt, coriander and red pepper.
Cook 1 minute.
Add broth.
Simmer gently, uncovered 15 to 20 minutes. Stir in pumpkin and half and half.
Cook 5 minutes until heated through.
Put into blender or processor in batches and blend until creamy.
Return to saucepan and reheat if necessary.
Serve with oyster crackers.

title: "missouri"
directions: Add tomatoes, salt, pepper and Worcestershire to ground beef. In a 2-quart casserole, arrange potatoes, celery, pepper and onion.
Pour meat mixture over vegetables.
Cover and bake 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 4.

title: apple crisp(quick and easy dessert)
directions: Fill 9-inch pie plate 2/3 full with apples.
Sprinkle cinnamon mixture over apples.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, egg and melted butter.
Pour over apples.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: mexican corn chowder
directions: Heat oil and butter in Dutch oven.
Add onion and saute until soft.
Add garlic and saute 1 minute.
Add flour and stir another minute.
Add corn, chiles, tomatoes and broth.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir cream/milk and cheese into soup and cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Do not boil.
This can be made the day before and reheated slowly, stirring constantly.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add cream of chicken soup, milk, chicken and chilies.
Stir together and heat.
Tear tortillas in quarters and layer all ingredients as follows:
tortillas, sauce and cheese.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch dish until hot.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Put pudding in a large bowl.
Add undrained pineapple and mix. Add rest of ingredients, except nuts.
Put some in the salad and sprinkle rest on top.

title: vanilla wafer pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs 2 at a time.
Add remaining ingredients and bake in greased tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: barbecues
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients.
Add catsup; fill bottle with water and add cornstarch and shake.
Pour over mixture.
Add chili powder and brown sugar.
Add mushrooms, if desired.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: creamy vegetable medley
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat soup to boiling. Stir in vegetables.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover; cook 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: hamburg-macaroni casserole(goop)
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add soup mix, oregano, stewed tomatoes and water.
Bring to boil.
Stir in macaroni and simmer, covered. Stir occasionally for 20 minutes.
Stir in Parmesan.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch casserole.
Top with cheese slices.
Place in oven until cheese is melted.
Serve.

title: cream cheese appetizers
directions: Cut ends off white bread.
Spread cream cheese on bread.
Cut bread in half and roll with slice of bacon.
Bake in oven at 375° for 25 minutes or until bacon is done.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over top of crust.
Next, layer with lemon pudding.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and top with chopped nuts.

title: london broil or steak marinade
directions: Score steak and marinate 4 hours or more.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: blizzard
directions: Freeze candy bar.
Break candy into tiny pieces with knife handle before removing from wrapper. Combine all ingredients in blender for 30 seconds on medium speed.
Stop, stir and repeat until well mixed.
Pour into 16 ounce glass.
Makes 1. If not thick enough, freeze until thickened.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, sour cream, oil and eggs in mixer. Beat at high speed 5minutes, then 5 minutes at low speed.
Pour 1/2 batter in buttered and floured Bundt pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 chocolate chips and 1/2 nuts on batter.
Add rest of batter, then chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° about 55 minutes, check at 45 minutes, may be done.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Cook the rice pilaf as directed.
Cook other ingredients halfway in frying pan; mix with rice.
Cook for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: *rice pudding
directions: Cook rice with 1 cup of water until water evaporates.
Add 1/2 stick butter and the milk.
Bring to a slow boil and cook 50 minutes. Beat eggs, vanilla and sugar. Pour slowly over rice mixture, mixing at the same time.
Sprinkle a little sugar and cinnamon on top. Enjoy!

title: christmas morning casserole
directions: Put crumbled crackers in bottom of casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over crackers.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: crab quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9-inch pie pan with cooking spray.
Combine 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese with paprika and set aside.
Stack and cut sheets of phyllo dough in half.
Place one square of phyllo in pie pan. Coat with cooking spray and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon cheese mixture.
Layer remaining squares and cheese mixture in the same manner.
Combine egg whites with Ricotta, flour and milk.
Stir in crabmeat, Swiss cheese and scallions. Sprinkle with Parmesan and a squirt of lemon juice. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool for 10 minutes.

title: poor professor's casserole
directions: Place buttered bread on bottom of large casserole.
Beat eggs, salt, mustard, milk and cheese together.
Pour over bread. Refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Serve immediately.

title: christmas pie
directions: Use 1/2
of
the crust to line a 9-inch pie pan.
Saute onion in	1
tablespoon
margarine.
Add	veal and pork; brown slightly. Add
seasonings,
flour, water, milk and egg; bring to a
boil. Spread
evenly
in	crust.	Arrange diced chicken over this. Cover
with remaining pastry;
turn under edge and seal.
Cut slits
in
top.
Preheat
oven to 375°; bake for 1 hour.
Let stand
for 10 minutes before cutting.
May also be served cold. Serves 8.

title: buttermilk fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter, Karo, salt and buttermilk in saucepan. Cook until soft ball stage.
Take from heat and allow to cool. Beat until creamy.
Add vanilla and nuts; pour on buttered plate. Slice when cold.

title: spinach fritata
directions: *May substitute 3 small squash; cook until tender.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil.
Make into 1/4 cup patties (about 8).
Fry 3 minutes per side until golden brown.

title: buttermilk chocolate cake
directions: Bring to boil margarine, cocoa and water.
Pour this over 2 cups of sugar and 2 cups of flour.
Then add eggs, buttermilk and soda.
Mix together.
Bake at 300° in greased and floured 12 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoon 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Cool.
Yields 7 dozen.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; rinse and drain.
Melt butter; stir in flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
When well blended, add milk slowly, stirring constantly over low heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Add cheese and Worcestershire sauce; stir until cheese has melted.
Add drained macaroni; pour mixture into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until begins to brown.

title: bacon ranch bread bites
directions: Roll bread dough into 1/2 inch thick rectangle. Brush top of dough with oil. Cut dough with sharp knife into 1 inch pieces.

title: theona's congealed salad
directions: Pour hot water on jello; stir quickly to melt.
Stir until dissolved; add sugar.
Let cool slightly.
Add coconut, pineapple and oranges; stir.
Add nuts.
Fold in sour cream.
Mix well. Pour into 4-cup mold.
Chill until congealed.
Keeps well.

title: cobbler pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until top is brown.

title: oven-barbecued chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a single layer.
Combine all other ingredients, pour over chicken and bake, uncovered, at 375° for approximately 1 hour (or until done).

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Top with buttered cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix sugar and eggs until creamy. Add milk and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Mix in melted butter.
Bake in 8-inch pie shell made or already made (bought).
Cook in a 325° oven until golden brown on top and set.

title: pineapple crush cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on box.
Beat cream cheese, instant vanilla pudding and 2 cups milk in small bowl. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spread on each layer.
Spoon 1 can crushed pineapple over layers.
Spread whipped topping on sides and top; refrigerate.

title: omelet
directions: Mix anything you want, such as ham, bologna, onions, broccoli or cheese.
Fry in pan until middle is not runny.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat eggs in creamed sugar and butter.
Add 1/2 dry ingredients (sifted).
Add mashed bananas, rest of flour and nuts. Bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: speedy dinner rolls
directions: Put yeast, warm water and sugar in a large bowl; let stand until dissolved.
Add butter, then flour, dry milk and salt.
Beat well with mixer.
Shape into rolls and place on greased baking sheet.
Let rise in warm place until about double in size.
Bake at 425° about 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli until tender; drain.
Put in large mixing bowl. Add butter, soup, Cheez Whiz, 1 teaspoon garlic powder, pinch of salt and dash of pepper.
Mix well.
Pour in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: malacca chicken
directions: Clean and truss the chicken.
Rub it all over with a mixture of the combined spices and salt.
Brown the chicken in oil in a large pot.
To the pot, add chicken cube, boiling water, soy sauce and garlic.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour, basting occasionally. Add the potatoes to the pot.
Simmer and baste until the potatoes are done.

title: banana pudding(quick and easy)
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk, prepared pudding and Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mixture.
If desired, crush some vanilla wafers to put on top to finish pudding.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Prepare all ingredients separately.
Salad is better prepared the day before.
To thaw green peas, dip in boiling water and drain.
Start to layer salad using enough lettuce to cover bottom of container.
Layer remainder as you want but, making a middle layer of lettuce.
End the layers with lettuce on top.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour onto a floured board. Knead for 1 minute. Cut out, using drinking glass top or round biscuit/donut cutter. Place in greased baking pan and sprinkle each biscuit with a little oil. Bake at 450° for 30 minutes. Makes 12 biscuits.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar.

title: no cook icing
directions: Beat egg white and 1 cup 10x sugar until stiff.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: carribean jerk meatballs with pineapple chutney
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients except chutney; mix well.
Gently shape mixture into 1-inch balls. In large shallow baking pan, arrange meatballs in a single layer. In a small bowl, spoon about 1/4 cup chutney; brush meatballs with chutney.
Bake, rotating balls once or twice, until cooked through and brown, 15 to 20 minutes.
Place under broiler briefly to brown if needed.
Arrange on serving platter; insert wooden picks.
Spoon rest of chutney into serving bowl or pineapple shell.
Makes about 24 meatballs.
See Pineapple Chutney Sauce.

title: frito pie
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet until just done; drain.
Stir in chili seasoning and stir until mixed.
Add the tomato sauce and cover; let simmer about 10 minutes.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, place 1/2 of the chili.
Chop the onion and spread over chili. Cover with a layer of Fritos and 1/2 cup cheese.
Put remaining chili on casserole; top with a heavy layer of Fritos.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake pie shell for 8 minutes.
In a large skillet, combine meat, green peppers, onion and seasoned salt.
Cook and stir over medium heat until meat browns.
Pour off fat.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Remove from heat; stir in tomato sauce and eggs.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and arrange onion rings on top of pie. Bake 5 more minutes.

title: window washer
directions: Add cold water to make 1 gallon.
Add a few drops of food coloring if desired.
Cheap and easy!

title: onion appetizer
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend sour cream and cream cheese together.
Add taco mix. Pour into a 2-quart Pyrex dish.
Chop dried beef and place on taco mixture.
Layer lettuce, tomatoes and cheese to top of bowl. Better if made 3 or 4 hours ahead.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Cook shells and drain well.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer over low heat 5 to 7 minutes.
Mixture will burn easily, so keep heat low.
May be refrigerated and served later.

title: million dollar cake
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Make a paste with the food coloring and cocoa; add to sugar mixture.
Alternate with flour and buttermilk and next teaspoon vanilla.
Mix vinegar with soda and add.
Bake at 350°.

title: date balls
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg.
Stir (don't beat). Add dates.
Cook over low heat about 10 minutes. Add pecans.
Cook 1 more minute.
Pour onto wax paper to cool.
When cool enough, shape into balls. Roll in coconut.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: fantastic chicken sauce
directions: Mix together sauce ingredients; spread chicken pieces in baking pan and spoon sauce over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste once or twice.
Serve 8.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Mix gelatin and water well.
Add sherbet.
Chill until slightly firm and add to drained fruits.
Add nuts, if desired. Makes 2 quart molds.

title: dumplings
directions: Make like biscuits.
Roll out thin on well floured cloth.
Let dry out before cutting.

title: hot artichoke crabmeat dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise. Mix well. Press in garlic. Drain artichokes and crabmeat; chop. Grate Parmesan cheese. Slice green onions. Zest lemon to measure 1 teaspoon zest. Add artichokes, crabmeat, cheese, onions, lemon zest and black pepper to cream cheese mixture. Spoon into baking dish. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown around edges. Sprinkle with red peppers and additional green onions. Serve with Baked Pita Chips.

title: banana orange smoothie
directions: Put all ingredients in strong blender carafe.
Whirl at highest speed until completely liquid.
Serve with straws and spoons.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Heat an 8-inch cast-iron skillet in a 400° oven 5 minutes. Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Set aside.
Combine eggs and next 3 ingredients, stirring until moistened.
Remove skillet and coat with cooking spray.
Pour batter into hot skillet.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 8 servings.
Contains 178 calories per serving (21% from fat).
